// SECTION 4 — ENTRY TRIGGER & PRICE MEMORY  v4.7
//
// v4.7 (19 Jul 2026): BLUE-SKY / BREAKOUT-PIVOT ruling (Jay, APOLLOHOSP: 'small pullbacks
//   from ATHs' kept reading SKIP-no-room). A Stage-2 leader (above the 30WMA + 200DMA)
//   consolidating within ath_prox_pct (3%) of its 52W high is a CONTINUATION PIVOT, not
//   distribution — the 'supply band' it sits in IS the prior high, meant to BREAK. S4 was
//   applying RANGE logic (in supply -> no room -> SKIP) to a MOMENTUM breakout. Now: an
//   in-supply state near the ATH in a Stage-2 uptrend reframes to 'BREAKOUT PIVOT — don't
//   buy HERE (into the resistance); arm a buy-STOP above the band ceiling; blue sky above
//   (reward = measured move / trail, not the next level)'. Only Stage-2; a Stage 3/4 lower
//   high stays a real SKIP. Applies to both the GO branch and the armed branch. New input
//   ath_prox_pct. (S4 correctly still flags buying HERE, below the ATH, as into-supply.)
//
//
// v4.6 (19 Jul 2026): ABBOTINDIA reconciliation (GM 'No location' vs S4 'TAKE IT strong').
//   • EXT-ATR UNIT BUGFIX: over-extension divided the distance to the DAILY EMA20 by the
//     75m CHART ATR -> inflated ~3x (verdict said '8.8 ATR' while Price-vs-EMA20 said
//     '+5.6% Norm'). Now uses atrD_tf (daily ATR) on intraday charts, so the ATR read
//     matches the % read and a 75m vs daily chart agree.
//   • WEAK-LOCATION GUARD: a GO whose location rests ONLY on the AVWAP/EMA (price NOT in
//     a demand zone or on a fresh S/R level) is a MOMENTUM/breakout entry, not the
//     pullback-into-a-Daily+-zone the house methodology wants. The verdict now downgrades
//     TAKE IT -> 'CAUTION — momentum/chase' with the reason. This is exactly why the GM
//     (which does not count AVWAP as location) read 'No location' — both are now
//     internally consistent, and S4 stops calling a between-zones breakout 'TAKE IT strong'.
//
//
// v4.5 (19 Jul 2026): JAY'S REVIEW BATCH #3 (queries 8-refine, 12b).
//   • #8 REFINE: S/R touch COUNT is pivots-only (already true); the wick-fit line no
//     longer drifts to the mean when a new pivot's wick misses the running band — it
//     stays on the maximal threadable wick-set (the touch still counts). Mean-drag only
//     when sr_wick_fit is OFF.
//   • #12b TRADE-TYPE PLAN (ported from Risk Shield Active-Exits is_swing + Risk
//     Allocator canon): a name that is VOLATILE (ATR% > swing_atr_max 4), FAR off the
//     52W high (> swing_off52_max 30%), or BELOW the 200-DMA -> SWING; else POSITIONAL.
//     The type sets: SL fallback/cap multiple (swing 2.5×ATR / positional 4.0×ATR —
//     the flat 2.5× cap was strangling positional holds), and R-multiple TARGETS used
//     when no structural overhead exists (swing 3R/5R · positional 5R/10R; Recovery T2
//     = the 52W high when nearer). Structural overhead still wins when present. Trade
//     type shows in the Plan row + verdict digest. use_tradetype_plan OFF = pre-#12b.
//
//
// v4.4 (19 Jul 2026): JAY'S REVIEW BATCH #2 (queries 2-refinement, 7, 8, 10, 12-part 1).
//   • #2b CONTROLLING = M/W/D ONLY (house rule): native zones on an INTRADAY chart can
//     never be Controlling, whatever controllingMinTf says — a 75/125m base is never the
//     dominant structural zone. HTF zones shown on intraday still can (they carry their TF).
//   • #7 SAME-BASE DEDUP (dedupSameBase, on): two pattern zones cut from the SAME base
//     (3-candle + 2-candle reads of one formation) — a new pattern zone overlapping an
//     existing same-TF same-dir pattern zone by >= 50% of the smaller width is skipped
//     (first formation wins). Adjacent/lightly-overlapping zones untouched.
//   • #8 S/R WICK-FIT (sr_wick_fit, on): the level line is placed at the midpoint of the
//     INTERSECTION of its member pivots' wick bands — the one price that threads EVERY
//     member wick (max-wick placement). Non-intersecting touches still count; line stays.
//   • #10 DAILY-BATTERY AGREEMENT as +1 confluence (cf_w_dailypa) — MTF grade, not gate:
//     a 75/125m trigger firing while the DAILY battery for the same path is also live.
//     (The hard "daily must agree" toggle was rejected: daily patterns confirm at EOD,
//     gating an intraday trigger on them makes every entry late — anti-Holy-Grail.)
//   • #12a DYNAMIC RISK (Commander_Risk_Allocator_v2.0 §9 port): Qty row risk% is now
//     active = max(regime × max(volDisc × kelly, 0.75), 0.25×base). Kelly 0.75-1.25×
//     (Stage-2 uptrend / RS improving / vol>1.1×); ATR>3% discount 3/ATR%; CNX500
//     bear-regime −0.25%. Breakdown shown in the Qty row; max-allocation cap added
//     (size_max_alloc). use_dyn_risk OFF = flat base. (#12b — catalyst-canon targets
//     T1/T2/T3 — next batch: S4 must first learn the catalyst family; see notes.)
//
// v4.3 (19 Jul 2026): JAY'S REVIEW BATCH #1 (queries 1-4, 13 of the 14-item list).
//   • #1 THE "MUST CLEAR" LEVEL IS NOW DRAWN. The verdict cited an obstacle ("must
//     clear 1439.95") that existed only as panel text — the level is now a red dashed
//     line + label on the chart (the supply-band ceiling when inside supply, else the
//     nearest overhead when it blocks room). Sense it → draw it.
//   • #2 CONTROLLING ZONES WERE STRUCTURALLY DEAD — REAL BUG. The D/W/M security calls
//     passed ctrlAllowed=FALSE, so an HTF zone could NEVER be Controlling by ANY
//     criterion (incl. trend-reversal, which Jay correctly noticed was never counting);
//     and on a 75/125m chart controllingMinTf="Daily" disabled native zones too. Fixed:
//     D/W/M now pass ctrlAllowDaily/Weekly/Monthly. EXPECT Controlling zones to appear.
//   • #3 OVER-EXTENSION now feeds the VERDICT: new input ext_atr_max (4.0 × ATR above
//     the daily EMA20 = chasing, matches the GM Step-4 ceiling). A GO while extended
//     carries an amber chase-risk caveat; the digest prints "+x.xATR vEMA20⚠". It does
//     NOT gate the GO (anti-Holy-Grail).
//   • #4 EMA20-DISTANCE ZONE-QUALITY MALUS — the mirror of the proximity bonus: EMA20
//     on the WRONG side of a zone and > emaFarAtr (3.0 own-TF ATR) away (below-and-away
//     from a DZ / above-and-away from an SZ) now SUBTRACTS emaFarMalus (10) from the
//     zone score. An orphaned zone is a weaker zone.
//   • #13 ROUND NUMBERS as location confluence (cf_w_round, +1): within 0.3% of a
//     price-scaled round step (100 above 5000 · 50 above 1000 · 10 above 100). "Rnd"
//     appears in the Confluence breakdown; cf_max updated.
//
// v4.2 (18 Jul 2026): VERDICT now RULES instead of naming the first failing gate.
//   Jay: "let the Verdict field give a clear direction, based on all the key metrics
//   above." The old line named only the binding gate — on CDSL it read "WAIT — volume
//   below floor", which invites "so buy it when volume arrives"; but that same bar was
//   INSIDE supply with -0.1R of room, where clearing volume would NOT make it a trade.
//   The verdict now weighs the GATES together with a QUALITY OVERLAY (room/R + in-supply,
//   arrival style + delta) and states DIRECTION first, then the reason, then the
//   disqualifier. Five rulings:
//     TAKE IT      - GO + a house gate cleared (swing >=2R / positional >=20% ROI),
//                    annotated with the arrival read.
//     SKIP         - GO but either in supply / <1R room, or NEITHER house gate: the
//                    entry is clean and the payoff is not worth the risk.
//     NOT TRADEABLE- not GO AND in supply / <1R: says plainly that clearing the blocking
//                    gate alone will not make it a trade (the CDSL case).
//     LOW QUALITY  - not GO, room OK, but a GRIND arrival with bleeding delta.
//     ARM          - not GO, everything else clean: names the ONE missing gate, the room,
//                    the arrival, and what to watch for.
//   Colour follows the ruling (green take / red skip / amber wait), so the row is
//   readable at a glance without parsing the sentence.
//   + ARRIVAL ROW MOVED UP — "Arrival · Δ" was row 26 (below Diagnostics, buried). It is
//     a LOCATION-QUALITY read, so it now sits at row 14, directly ABOVE the TRIGGER row,
//     next to the other location/quality fields. Rows 14..25 shifted +1 (TRIGGER 15 ·
//     Plan 16 · Entry 17 · Qty 18 · PA 19-22 · Structure 23 · STATUS 24 · VERDICT 25 ·
//     Diagnostics 26). Verified: rows 0..26 written exactly once, no duplicates, no gaps
//     (the v3.4 collision failure mode — checked BOTH f_row() and raw table.cell()).
//   + VERDICT IS MULTI-LINE — a single long sentence stretched the panel across the chart
//     and covered price. The ruling is now assembled as separate lines (headline / reason /
//     disqualifier / metrics / action) joined with \n inside ONE cell, so the panel stays
//     narrow no matter how much the verdict has to say.
//   + VERDICT WEIGHS THE FULL PANEL — not just the blocking gate. A new metrics digest
//     line reports WHICH location sources are holding price (DZ / S-R / AVWAP / EMA20,
//     + ★ctrl and ×N-TF confluence), the room in R, arrival style + delta, RV vs floor,
//     confluence x/y and the PA Σ for the active path — so the ruling is auditable
//     without re-scanning the rows above it.
//
// v4.1 (18 Jul 2026): ** CRITICAL BUGFIX — the PA battery was reading a STALE bar. **
//   Symptom (Jay, CDSL): Golden Matcher showed Recovery Sum +3 ("Higher-Low / 2B")
//   while S4 — on the SAME Recovery path, same symbol — showed Sum 0. Recurring, and
//   NOT a formula drift: the Python and Pine batteries are formula-identical (verified
//   line-by-line for the 17 bull patterns; the 2B windows also match exactly —
//   l.iloc[-10:] == ta.lowest(low,10) and l.iloc[-40:-10] == ta.lowest(low,30)[10]).
//   ROOT CAUSE: `int _o = confirm_daily ? 1 : 0` was applied to f_daily_pa's return
//   UNCONDITIONALLY — i.e. to BOTH the daily-security call (d_*, where it is correct:
//   read the last CLOSED daily bar) AND the chart-TF local call (loc_*, where it is
//   WRONG). With use_chart_tf ON + confirm_daily ON (both DEFAULTS), the chart-TF
//   battery therefore evaluated the bar BEFORE the last closed one. Proof: CDSL 2B
//   scores +3 on the last bar and 0 on bar[-2] — on daily AND 75m alike.
//   Worse, during live hours it COMPOUNDED with use_closed_candle's own [_so] display
//   shift => the battery could read up to TWO bars stale, silently eating triggers
//   (the likely reason GM->S4 GO conversion collapsed).
//   confirm_daily's own tooltip already stated it "applies only when 'Use chart
//   timeframe' is OFF" — the code simply never honoured it.
//   FIX: f_daily_pa takes a `confirmShift` parameter. The DAILY security call passes
//   true (keeps the last-closed-daily read); the CHART-TF call passes false (no shift
//   — use_closed_candle is what protects that path from the forming bar).
//   EXPECT MORE PA FIRES / MORE GOs after this. Recompile required.
//
// v4.0 (18 Jul 2026): ARRIVAL STYLE + ORDER-FLOW FOOTPRINT (bar-level proxy).
//   Quality-of-zones factors #4 (arrival style) and #5 (order-flow) — from the
//   "how price returns matters as much as the zone" list.
//   • ARRIVAL STYLE (pure geometry, fully real): the approach leg into the zone price
//     is at — velocity in ATR/bar (distance covered / bars). FAST (>= arr_vel_fast) =
//     high-velocity drop into demand / rally into supply → sharp rejection likely.
//     GRIND (<= arr_vel_slow) = slow stair-step → momentum absorbing → bleed-through
//     risk. NORMAL between. Mirrored for supply.
//   • ORDER-FLOW DELTA (intrabar up/down-volume PROXY): request.security_lower_tf pulls
//     lower-TF sub-bars (of_ltf, default 1-min) and classifies each sub-bar's volume
//     buy/sell by its close vs open — this chart bar's delta = sum(up) - sum(down),
//     the same method as TV's built-in Up/Down Volume. Summed over of_win bars, plus a
//     delta-DIVERGENCE check (price lower-low but delta higher-low at demand = buyers
//     absorbing). Reads ABSORBING Δ+ / BLEEDING Δ− / NEUTRAL. NOT true tick/aggressor
//     delta — Pine cannot access order-flow on ANY TV plan; this is bar-classified.
//   • Panel: NEW "Arrival · Δ" row (row 26; e.g. "FAST 0.63 ATR/bar · absorbing Δ+").
//     Two new confluence weights: cf_w_arrival (sharp arrival at a zone) + cf_w_absorb
//     (absorbing delta), each default 1, gated by show_arrival (hide = ignore). They
//     GRADE the GO, they do not GATE it. New group "Arrival & Order-Flow".
//   NOTE: of_ltf must be LOWER than the chart TF (default 1-min is safe on 75/125m/D/W/M;
//   do not apply on a <= 1-min chart). Intrabar history is capped (~100k sub-bars), so the
//   delta is reliable on recent bars — which is all the arrival read needs.
//
// v3.9 (18 Jul 2026): S/R & PATTERNS — wick-pierce touches + rectangles (#30, #31).
//   • #30 S/R WICK-PIERCE TOUCHES. A pivot used to merge into a level only when its
//     EXTREME was within Cluster tolerance. Now it also counts when the level line
//     PIERCES the pivot's wick (upper wick of a high, lower wick of a low) — so one line
//     threads the wicks of MORE pivots and the touch count reflects the real number it
//     holds. A wick-pierce touch is COUNTED but does NOT drag the level's price mean (the
//     line stays where it threads the wicks); only a near-extreme touch nudges it. Still
//     PIVOT wicks only — never arbitrary bars. Input sr_wick_touch (default on). NOTE this
//     feeds the MTTWR grade → more touches reach 'primed to break' sooner (by design).
//   • #31 RECTANGLES AS PATTERNS. The geometry read already classified 'Range / rectangle'
//     (flat highs + flat lows) but only named it. That case is now DRAWN as a box (flat
//     top/bottom at the mean of the two highs/lows, from the earliest pivot, extended
//     right); every other shape keeps the two #59 connector lines. Toggle drawGeomLines.
//   • #36/#40 D/W/M PATTERN FUNNEL. The diagnostics row funnel was NATIVE-only, so a missing
//     Daily/Weekly/Monthly pattern zone couldn't be seen. Added a per-TF pattern funnel:
//     "pat D d/c·L  W d/c·L  M d/c·L" (detected via the security call / created / live).
//     d=0 → a detection gate rejected it (leg/base/width/leg-in); d>0 c=0 → EMA/RS or dedup;
//     c>0 with low L → removal. This is how #36/#40 become self-diagnosing.
//
// v3.8 (18 Jul 2026): DETECTION PASS #2 — HTF-zone over-removal + phantom geometry
//   (issues #25/#40/#42 and #59), diagnosed from live CoalIndia-W / Caplipoint-W /
//   Anandrathi-M / Acutaas screenshots (the diagnostics row made this readable).
//   • #25/#40/#42 WEEKLY & MONTHLY ZONES WERE BEING RETIRED BY A *DAILY* EMA20/pivot
//     cross. The tested rule's EMA/level check (rules 2 & 3) applied to every D/W/M zone
//     but always referenced the DAILY EMA20 — so a WEEKLY demand zone died the moment
//     price closed above the daily EMA20. CoalIndia-W showed 3 of 37 weekly zones alive
//     (removed: lvlX 28 · violated 33); Caplipoint-W 3 of 19. Now the EMA/level cross
//     applies to DAILY zones only; WEEKLY & MONTHLY zones are judged by TRAVEL (in their
//     OWN TF's ATR) + VIOLATION, like native intraday zones. EXPECT MANY MORE weekly and
//     monthly zones to persist — a persistence change; report the live-count delta.
//   • #59 PHANTOM GEOMETRY. The panel named a shape ("Rising channel / wedge", which
//     fires on almost any trend) but nothing was drawn — it read as phantom. The two
//     pivot connectors that produce the classification are now DRAWN (dashed, extended
//     right) so the named shape is visible. Toggle drawGeomLines (default on).
//   • PIVOT-ZONE TOGGLE surfaced: the existing useStructural gate (which already turns ALL
//     pivot zones on/off) was relabelled "Draw Pivot (Structural) zones" with an isolation
//     tooltip — uncheck it to see ONLY pattern DZ/SZ while diagnosing why one isn't marking.
//   • DAILY/INTRADAY ZONES UNDER-MARKING → per-TF leg-in. The leg-in gate was one global
//     1.0×ATR (raised from 0.3 on 17-Jul) — the biggest recent detection tighten, and it
//     collided with #35 (you wanted 1.2 to kill a spurious MONTHLY base). One knob can't be
//     both loose for intraday/daily and strict for monthly. Split into legin_ltf (0.6,
//     intraday+daily → more zones) and legin_htf (1.2, weekly+monthly → no spurious). The
//     native call picks by chart TF. EXPECT MORE daily/intraday zones — report natC d delta.
//
// v3.7 (18 Jul 2026): DETECTION PASS #1 — narrow-zone rescue + recency score + verifications
//   (#34, #27, and #29/#35/#39/#43 confirmed already-correct — no behaviour change on those four).
//   • #27 RECENCY (score decays with age). Two factors now measure a zone: AGE (the ageing
//     cap) and RECENCY. z.strength holds the intrinsic score; the DISPLAYED score (label +
//     panel Support-Zone grade) decays linearly from formation to the TF's ageing cap,
//     floored at 0, so a fresher zone outscores an equal-merit older one. Inputs
//     recencyDecay (on) + recencyMaxDrop (20). Score-only — cannot blackout a zone.
//   • #34 NARROW-ZONE WICK-TO-WICK. Distals were already wicks; the proximal defaulted to
//     the BODY extreme, so a thin-bodied base produced a body-to-wick zone below the width
//     FLOOR and was REJECTED. Now, when that body zone is thinner than the floor, the
//     proximal is widened out to the base's own wick (demand: wick high; supply: wick low)
//     so the true wick-to-wick zone is drawn instead of dropped. Input narrowWickToWick
//     (default on). EXPECT MORE ZONES on charts with thin bases — this is a detection
//     change; report the zone-count delta (turn on the diagnostics row).
//   • #39 ANSWERED (no change): pivot zones do NOT override demand/supply zones. Pattern
//     zones are created first (native/D/W/M) and always survive; pivot zones are created
//     AFTER and are skipped when they overlap a same-TF, same-direction pattern zone.
//   • #29 VERIFIED: auto S/R keeps a 40-pivot pool PER timeframe (sr_pool) and computes
//     Monthly + Weekly + Daily levels via request.security — not daily-only.
//   • #35: the leg-in gate is exposed (v3.8 splits it per-TF: legin_ltf / legin_htf).
//     Set it to 1.2 to drop the spurious ACUTAAS-monthly base (Jay's finding); left at the
//     1.0 default globally so it does not tighten every other symbol.
//   • #43 VERIFIED: the average-leg rescue already enforces the wicky-FT cancel rule —
//     noRevBull/noRevBear reject a follow-through that CLOSES back through the leg-out's
//     opposite extreme (a pierce that closes back inside is fine).
//
// v3.6 (17 Jul 2026): ZONE-MARKING PASS #1 — load UX + visibility (issues #37, #41, #47).
//   • #47 LOAD NO LONGER FORCES A DRAW. The manual Box + Trendline anchors used
//     input.time/input.price(confirm=true), which prompts a click-to-place on EVERY
//     add and CANCELS the whole indicator on Esc ("forces me to draw a Trendline first,
//     else it closes"). Pine has no conditional confirm, so all 12 anchors are now plain
//     numeric inputs (0 = off, entered in the settings dialog). Loading is instant.
//   • #37 ZONE FILL TRANSPARENCY is now an input (zoneFillTransp, default 88) instead of
//     the hard-wired 93-96 near-clear fills; per-TF spread preserved (Monthly most
//     opaque). The controlling-zone opacity floor was 90 (calibrated for the old range)
//     and would have INVERTED against a low base — retuned to 60 so controlling always
//     reads more opaque than its base.
//   • #41 SHOW TESTED ZONES IN GREY (show_tested_grey, default off). Default still
//     DELETES a zone the moment it is tested (declutter). ON = the tested zone is
//     recoloured grey + dotted and FROZEN in place (new Zone.tested field) so every
//     valid zone that ever formed can be verified. Grey zones are excluded from the
//     trigger, support, and the live DZ/SZ counts (the per-bar scan skips z.tested).
//   • #61 TRIGGER row now amber for EVERY waiting state incl. no-PA (was grey), matching
//     the STATUS row — grey read as "inactive", amber = "live, waiting for the gate".
//   • #62 ANALYSIS row slimmed to VERDICT-only. The CONTEXT / LOCATION / SETUP / RISK
//     lines restated the Structure, Support, STATUS and Entry rows verbatim ("repeat of
//     the field outputs, not useful") — removed. Kept the one synthesis no other row
//     states: swing vs positional per the house rules. New show_analysis toggle (default
//     on); row renamed VERDICT.
//   • #26 VERIFIED PRESENT (no change): all three Controlling criteria already wired —
//     leads-to-ATH (isNewATH), trend reversal (isTrendShiftUp/Down), breaks-opposing.
//
// v3.5 (17 Jul 2026): PRE-PANEL ISSUE PASS (issues #1, #4).
//   • #1 TRIGGER PATH-SPECIFICITY. GO already required a PA pattern (go = any_pa and
//     support_pass and vol_ok and bar_ok) — it was never location-only. But the two
//     batteries SHARE four patterns (Spring / Engulf / 3-Bar / Pocket), so a GO resting
//     only on those legitimately HOLDS across a Bull<->Recovery flip, which read as
//     "the trigger ignores the path". Now surfaced: the TRIGGER row appends "⇄both"
//     (shared-only, holds either path) or "Bull-only" / "Rec-only" (path-exclusive,
//     drops if you flip away). New series pa_bull_excl / pa_rec_excl / pa_shared_only —
//     no new panel cells, so the v3.4 renumber stays collision-free.
//   • #4 Daily zone label colour yellow -> LIGHT BLUE (#4FC3F7), distinct from the 125m
//     aqua and 75m lime. Applied to both the tfTag=="D" and the native-daily branches.
//   (Already in-file from the v3.1-v3.4 issue pass: #2 follow-through split
//    ftLagBars/ftMaxRescue, #3 Controlling pullback rule ctrlMinLowerHighs, #5
//    last-closed-candle use_closed_candle — verified present, not re-touched here.)
//
// v3.4 (17 Jul 2026): PANEL REBUILD — and the audit finding behind it. FOUR rows
//   were INVISIBLE: f_row(13/15/16/17) wrote S/R · Confluence · Diagnostics ·
//   Pattern|Geometry, and raw table.cell(pnl, 0/1, 13/15/16/17) writes for TRIGGER
//   and the PA grid overwrote all four. Every row added on 17-Jul had silently
//   collided with a pre-existing cell write and never rendered. The dup-check that
//   passed had scanned only `f_row(N,` and never saw the raw table.cell writes —
//   it was looking at half the writes. The panel is renumbered 0..29, unique, and
//   the check now covers BOTH write forms.
//   • Zones (MTF) row now carries the TRADEABLE read (IN DEMAND ★ctrl ⚡ ×2TF ·
//     8 DZ / 3 SZ live). The detection funnel that lived there was troubleshooting
//     instrumentation, not a trading input — it is on an optional Diagnostics row
//     (`show_diag`, default off) with the removal attribution.
//   • "Auto basis" was inside `if mode == "Auto"` → the row rendered BLANK on a
//     manual Bull/Recovery setting, which reads as missing data rather than n/a.
//     Now "Structure basis", ALWAYS written; it says whether Auto picked the mode.
//   • PLAN split: the Plan row states the METHOD in words; Entry / Stop-loss /
//     Target 1 / Target 2 carry the NUMBERS. Prices are stated once, in the rows
//     that exist to hold them. T2 = the SECOND overhead (new `_ovh2`), and reads
//     "open — no 2nd obstacle" rather than inventing one.
//   • NEW ANALYSIS row under STATUS: context · location · setup · risk · verdict,
//     built from the same [_so]-shifted values the rows show, so it can never
//     narrate a different bar than the panel above it. The verdict applies BOTH
//     house rules — swing needs >= 2.0R, positional needs >= 20% ROI to T1 — and
//     says plainly when a clean entry is not worth the risk.
//
// v3.3 (17 Jul 2026): COMPREHENSIVE AUDIT PASS — 25 fixes from a three-way
//   adversarial audit (zones/lifecycle · S/R/FVG/pivots/trendlines · patterns/GO/
//   Room/Plan). Headliners: level TF-constants were trading-time vs the calendar
//   chartSec (Weekly levels hidden on Weekly charts, Monthly charts blank); S/R slot
//   demotion had no dedup (one cluster -> two lines, wrong price + wrong grade fed to
//   the plan); gapBonus was mathematically dead and FVG was tested on gap-bridged
//   prices (both must read RAW prices - a gap is what the bridge erases); the width
//   band read the LIVE bar's ATR (stranded 'forming' previews); Room read the forming
//   bar while the Plan read the closed one; alertcondition(go) fired intrabar; the
//   Plan had no T1/R:R and silently snapped a 3.0-tested stop to 2.5xATR unflagged;
//   the controlling breaksOpposing promotion was dead at the default Min-TF setting;
//   zone tested/violation deletions ran on FORMING bars (live chart vs reloaded chart
//   disagreed); score gating leaks (show_intraday / show_flag / TL-vs-S/R double
//   count). Full list in the session log.
//
// v3.2 (16 Jul 2026): HORIZONTAL S/R LEVELS absorbed from Commander Chart Markup,
//   which is being RETIRED into this file. S4 becomes the single markup surface —
//   zones + levels (+ trendlines and patterns to follow). The two tools previously
//   CONTRADICTED each other on the same chart: S4 deletes a zone the moment it is
//   tested, while Chart Markup promoted a level *because* it had been tested.
//
//   • TIMEFRAME-SCOPED, both auto and manual. A level shows on its own timeframe
//     and every LOWER one, never upward: Monthly everywhere · Weekly on W and
//     below · Daily on D and below (a Daily level NEVER appears on a Weekly
//     chart). Reuses this file's existing chartSec guardrail constants rather than
//     declaring a second set that could drift.
//   • THE TIMEFRAME IS THE CONVICTION. It rides into the panel's S/R row, because
//     a stop resting on a WEEKLY level is a deeper distal → wider stop → SIZE DOWN
//     (Gate 4). The same price off a DAILY shelf is a tighter stop and a bigger
//     position. Line weight says it visually too (M 3px / W 2px / D 1px).
//   • TESTS WEAKEN A LEVEL — the inversion. Chart Markup ranked S/R by touch count
//     (more = stronger), the exact opposite of the house rule: "MTTWR / MTTWS —
//     Multiple Times Tested Weak Resistance / Support (a level tested so often it
//     is primed to break)". Here: 1 test = FRESH (strongest) · 2..n-1 = TESTED
//     (weakening) · >= n = MTTWR, drawn dashed and EXCLUDED from support, because
//     leaning a stop on a level primed to break is the mistake the grade exists to
//     prevent. Deliberate split from ZONES: a zone is FUEL and is consumed by a
//     test (deleted); a level is PRICE MEMORY and survives it, weakened. That is
//     how "delete tested zones" and "count tests for MTTWR" are both true.
//   • DEEP POOL. Chart Markup capped pivots at 16 (~4-6 months of daily), so a
//     level from 8 months back was unreachable at ANY setting — the single biggest
//     reason its S/R felt immature. Each TF now clusters its own 40-pivot pool at
//     its own ATR scale: a weekly level comes from weekly swings.
//   • ROLE IS DERIVED (price vs close), never fixed at detection, so a level flips
//     Support↔Resistance when price closes through it (the R-flip→S rule).
//   • MANUAL tier (4 draggable input.price slots per TF) OUTRANKS auto on any
//     timeframe you have marked — your hand-drawn levels ARE the location layer
//     (Gate 2); auto is the fallback for a TF you have not marked yet. Marked TFs
//     suppress their auto pair entirely rather than drawing both.
//   • SIGNAL CHANGE, not just drawing: near_sr joins support_pass, so the GO gate
//     gains a source and will fire on names v3.1 skipped. Intended (a marked level
//     IS a location) — but expect MORE GOs than v3.1.
//   max_lines_count 100 → 150 to carry the level lines.
//
//   CONFLUENCE SCORE — the conditions Jay eyeballs now COUNT, instead of being
//   decoration. Until now AVWAP/intraday were a bare "⏱" that gated nothing, Fib
//   was hard-commented "indication only, never gates", and ⚡/controlling/pinch
//   were labels. A 2-confluence GO and an 8-confluence GO rendered IDENTICALLY.
//     - The score GRADES, it does NOT GATE. GO still fires on P·L·V·B alone. The
//       anti-Holy-Grail ruling stands ("GO = (Event OR Intraday) AND Volume — NOT
//       all 3"): requiring more conditions yields a trigger that never fires, which
//       is a different failure, not a safer one. The score answers "how strong is
//       this live trigger" — the question the ⏱ was silently refusing to answer.
//     - WEIGHTED BY KIND, because a flat count would be dishonest. TIMING events
//       (+2: AVWAP trigger, intraday leg) are things HAPPENING — they are the entry
//       itself. QUALITY/LOCATION (+1: ⚡ FVG zone, controlling zone, fresh S/R,
//       EMA20, AVWAP, Fib, pinch, strong RV, multi-TF overlap) are things being
//       TRUE. Three proximity tags are not worth one real AVWAP bounce.
//     - Panel: TRIGGER reads "GO ★strong 8/13"; a "Confluence" row names WHICH
//       fired (a bare score is its own black box). Chart: GO★ (bright, larger) vs
//       GO. Alert carries "conf n/max". Every weight is an input; 0 drops that
//       confluence. cf_max recomputes from the weights so "x/y" stays honest.
//
//   TESTED-RULE REBUILD — found by the funnel on a live 75m chart: 685 native zones
//   created, ONE alive. A 0.15% survival rate is not a "tested" rule, it is a
//   delete-everything rule. The three rules are OR'd so the LOOSEST always wins, and
//   NOT ONE of them was scaled to the zone's own timeframe or size:
//     1. TRAVEL was measured in ZONE-WIDTHS — inverted. The travel needed scaled with
//        the zone's own size, so a 3pt zone died on a 6pt move while a 30pt zone
//        survived it: the most PRECISE zones were retired fastest. Now measured in
//        ATR (`testedTravelMode`, default ATR) — and in the ZONE's OWN timeframe's
//        ATR (atrD_tf/atrW_tf/atrM_tf), because using the CHART's would retire a
//        Monthly zone on a 2×(75m ATR) move. (Zone-width scaling got the HTF case
//        right by accident — monthly zones are wide — but was wrong within a TF.)
//        Legacy mode retained so pre-v3.2 behaviour stays reproducible.
//     2/3. The EMA20 / pivot rules test a close across a DAILY reference. Letting
//        those adjudicate a 75-min zone is a category error: a 75m base is not
//        consumed because price crossed a DAILY EMA20 — that event says nothing
//        about that base. Now HTF-zones-only (`tested_tf_match`, default ON); native
//        intraday zones are judged on travel and violation alone.
//   Removal attribution (age · travel · emaX · lvlX · violated) — on the optional
//   Diagnostics row (`show_diag`, v3.4; it was row 16 until the panel rebuild). The
//   d/f/m/L funnel proved a zone was created-then-removed but was SILENT on WHICH of
//   the four exits took it, reducing diagnosis to arguing from a screenshot. Counted
//   per rule that was true, so overlaps show (the rules are not mutually exclusive,
//   and the sum can exceed the removal count).
//
//   TRENDLINES — MANUAL ONLY (see the note at grpTL). The Chart Markup auto-fitter
//   is NOT ported: it was rewritten nine times and never converged, because "which
//   two pivots" is chart-specific rather than a global setting. One support + one
//   resistance line, each with its own TF tag, click-to-place, TF-guardrailed like
//   the levels. Projected to the current bar it joins the SAME nearest-S/R pool the
//   horizontals use — a trendline is just a level whose price moves — so it reaches
//   the plan, the support gate and the score with no consumer knowing it is diagonal.
//
//   PROVISIONAL ZONE PREVIEW (`prov_zone`, default ON). ft >= 1 means a leg-out must
//   be at least one bar back, so a leg-out on the LAST bar could never be a candidate
//   — the newest zone stayed invisible until a fresh bar existed. Intraday that is one
//   bar; at a session close it is until the next session; at FRIDAY's close it is the
//   entire WEEKEND, which is exactly when the zone marking happens.
//     - AFTER the normal search fails, on the last CONFIRMED bar only, the engine also
//       tries ft=0. ORDER MATTERS: last, never first — the loop takes the shortest
//       successful ft, so trying 0 first would let a brand-new preview shadow an older
//       REAL formation ft=1 was about to find.
//     - Only STRONG legs preview, and that is correct rather than a compromise:
//       `strongFT` and `hasFVG` both need a bar AFTER the leg-out, so they are
//       unmeasurable here. That is time, not something code can shortcut. A strong leg
//       needs no follow-through — which is exactly why it can be read at its close.
//     - It is a PREVIEW: dashed, does NOT latch, does NOT enter activeZones, does NOT
//       gate support_pass/GO, and is absent from the zone counts. NOT latching is what
//       permits the upgrade — advancing lastNativeTime would block the real find and
//       freeze the zone at its provisional reading forever. The real zone is created
//       normally on the next bar, with FT and FVG finally measurable.
//     - NATIVE only. On a Daily chart the daily zones ARE native (useDailyZ is false
//       there), likewise Weekly — so weekend marking is covered without relying on
//       barstate.isconfirmed inside a request.security context, where it is unreliable.
//
//   DISPLAY — LAYER MASTER SWITCHES (grpDisp): one per layer, for triage. OFF
//   removes a layer from the DECISION as well as the chart (support gate, plan,
//   confluence, and cf_max's ceiling). Deliberate: a layer judged untrustworthy must
//   not keep steering a trade from behind a hidden drawing — "not shown" and "not
//   counted" have to mean the same thing or the switch is a lie. (d_markers is the
//   one exception, and is labelled as such: it hides on-candle labels only, the PA
//   battery keeps running and the panel keeps reading.)
//
// v3.1 (16 Jul 2026): ZONE MARKING FINE-TUNE. Five corrections to the ported IZE
//   engine, driven by a WELCORP M/W/125m review against the marking methodology.
//
//   1. CONTROLLING now requires a PULLBACK — it must LEAD TO a new ATH, not
//      CONTINUE one (house rule). Previously `isNewATH` only tested "leg-out close
//      > ATH before the base", with NO test for a pullback, lower highs, or
//      non-continuation — so in a sustained run every qualifying base made a new
//      ATH, promoted, and demoted the last one. Now all three must hold: the base
//      forms below the prior ATH, >= `ctrlMinLowerHighs` bars printed a lower high
//      since that ATH, and the leg-out closes through it. Mirrored for supply/ATL.
//      EXPECT CONTROLLING TO BE RARE on a strong trender — that is the rule working.
//
//   2. EXCLUSIVE CONTROLLING is now genuinely NEAREST-ATH. It demoted the incumbent
//      unconditionally (last-one-wins) while the comment claimed "closest to the
//      current ATH". A new zone must actually be nearer (higher DZ / lower SZ) or
//      the incumbent keeps the title.
//
//   3. FOLLOW-THROUGH is a variable-length RESCUE search, not a fixed offset. The
//      old "Follow-Through Bars Required" input was really a detection offset —
//      raising it slid the window into the past rather than demanding more FT, and
//      0 silently killed the average-leg rescue AND the whole FVG subsystem. Split
//      into "Confirmation lag" (min 1) + "Max follow-through rescue bars"; the
//      engine now tries the shortest lag first, so a strong leg-out fires with zero
//      FT and a weak one can be rescued by 2-3 FT bars — and is then the LEG-OUT
//      rather than a base candle, which NARROWS the zone.
//
//   3b. INVISIBLE CANDLES are now UNIVERSAL and MANDATORY for zone detection, and
//      the "Use Invisible Candles" toggle is GONE. Marking zones on gap-bridged
//      price is the methodology, not a preference, so it is no longer switchable.
//      Two bugs this closes:
//        - f_structZone used RAW OHLC throughout and was never even passed the flag,
//          so every PvL/PvH zone ignored the setting while pattern zones honoured
//          it — the two detectors literally disagreed about where price had been.
//          It now derives eff_* identically to f_detectZone, INCLUDING the pivots
//          (here the pivot IS the zone geometry, not just a BOS confirmation).
//        - A detection toggle could silently desync the engine from the overlay.
//      NOTE: the FVG/pivot subsystem (f_zones) deliberately stays on raw OHLC — an
//      FVG *is* a gap, and bridging it would erase the very thing being detected.
//
//   3c. NEW "Draw Invisible Candles (gap-bridged overlay)" checkbox (Zones — Visual,
//      default OFF) plots the gap-bridged candles, so you can SEE what the engine
//      sees without a second indicator (e.g. CG-GapFill). Same derivation as the
//      detectors' eff_* series, so the overlay can NEVER disagree with the zones.
//      VIEW ONLY: unticking it hides the candles, it does not change a single zone.
//      To see ONLY these: Chart Settings → Symbol → uncheck Body / Borders / Wick.
//
//   4. STRUCTURAL (PvL/PvH) zones are constrained + visually distinct. They emit
//      from a bare pivot — no leg-in, no base, no leg-out — and used to bypass the
//      width band entirely while scoring 60..100 (a flat 60 floor on a different
//      scale), so every PvL read 86-93pts and out-ranked real pattern zones. Now:
//      per-TF width band honoured (floor scaled by `structMinWMult`), scored
//      40..75, and drawn with a DASHED border. New struct D/C/L panel diagnostic.
//
//   5. ★ (confluence) is meaningful again. The EMA20 term granted +10 to any demand
//      zone sitting entirely BELOW the daily EMA20 regardless of distance — i.e.
//      every demand zone in an uptrend — so ★ was a near-constant ★10. It is now
//      PROXIMITY only. Also: volume score floored at 0 (it silently subtracted up
//      to -12 for a below-average-volume leg-out); dead touch-counter layer,
//      markTested/expireDrawings/isExpired, and the dead bullLegOut/bearLegOut
//      twin of the live ERC gates removed; violation-marker text now says "dot".
// ============================================================================
// v3.0 (15 Jul 2026): INSTITUTIONAL DEMAND/SUPPLY ZONES replace the built-in
//   Order-Block support source. The proven zone-detection subsystem from the
//   Institutional Zone Engine v4.2 (f_detectZone / RBR·DBR·RBD·DBD patterns +
//   pivot-based structural zones, requested on Chart + Daily + Weekly + Monthly)
//   is ported in WHOLESALE and drawn as multi-timeframe zones. What changed vs
//   the IZE source and vs S4 v2.9.1:
//     • OB (order block) is REMOVED as a support source; IZE demand/supply zones
//       take its place. FVG + pivot-lines ("other S/R key levels") are KEPT
//       (f_zones still runs) and continue to count toward the support gate.
//     • The IZE Trade-Intelligence PANEL is NOT ported (per Jay). Only the
//       decision-relevant zone values feed the S4 panel (take / drop / hold).
//     • NEW "tested" rule for a demand/supply zone (replaces IZE's mark-tested-on-
//       first-re-entry). A zone is marked TESTED only after price REACTED off it
//       (entered then left) AND then confirmed by ANY of:
//         (1) price travelled >= testedTravelMult (default 2.0) x the zone width
//             away from the zone, or
//         (2) price CLOSED across the daily EMA20 after the reaction, or
//         (3) price CLOSED across a strong S/R key level (nearest pivot high/low)
//             after the reaction.
//       A TESTED zone is DELETED outright (declutter rule) — not greyed — so every
//       zone still on the chart is by definition fresh and un-reacted, and there is
//       no touch counter. Violation (close beyond the distal) likewise deletes the
//       zone and drops a small faint RED DOT at the distal on the breaking bar.
//     • NEW panel rows (decision context, sourced from the zones):
//         - "Room for Trade"      : v67.4.12-style verdict (BLUE SKY / CLEAR /
//           ⚠ NO ROOM) using the nearest OPPOSING overhead — across HTF supply
//           zones, flipped-pivot resistance and the HTF pivot high — plus the room
//           in % and the risk multiple (reward-to-overhead / demand-zone width;
//           flags >= 2R). (This single row merges the earlier Room Threshold row.)
//         - "Price vs EMA20"      : v67.4.12-style proximity state (daily EMA20
//           anchor on 75/125m, chart EMA20 on daily) — RESISTANCE / SUPPORT /
//           NEAR / ABOVE / BELOW + OverExtended. EMA20 also acts as a dynamic S/R
//           source in the support gate + Trigger.
//         - "Zones (MTF)"         : demand / supply / controlling counts.
//         - "Support Zone"        : fresh demand zone + FVG + pivot + AVWAP + EMA20,
//           with a ~Fib (38.2/50/61.8) indication tag (indication only, never gates).
//     • Zone visuals: near-transparent backgrounds, labels centred inside the zone
//       body (10-space indent), on-chart S4/GO markers limited to the latest 30 bars,
//       intraday chart-TF zones drawn only when aligned with a 75/125m FVG, and an
//       HTF zone can never be re-tagged "Controlling" from lower-TF context.
//     • indicator() box/label/line caps raised to 500/500/100 for the MTF zones.
//   Everything else (AVWAP price memory, the 17+recovery PA battery, the intraday
//   10-EMA + TTM-squeeze trigger, the combined GO gate, alerts) is unchanged from
//   v2.9.1 below.
// ============================================================================
// v2.9.1 (10 Jul 2026): FORMAT-STRING BUG FIX (pre-existing). The panel used
//   str.tostring(x, "#.1") / "#.2" — but "1"/"2" are NOT valid Pine format digits
//   (only "#" and "0" are), so Pine rounded the value to a WHOLE number and
//   appended a LITERAL ".1"/".2". Result: RV 0.94 rendered as "1.2", nearest-
//   support 0.23% as "0.1%", off52 as "N.1" — a fake constant decimal on every
//   field. This is what made "RV 1.2 / floor 1.2 but V· (no volume)" look insane
//   (the true RV was 0.94, correctly below the floor). Fixed: "#.2"->"0.00",
//   "#.1"->"0.0" so the panel shows the real number. (The "#.0" fields were fine —
//   "0" IS a valid format digit.) Verified against live 75m data: SUMICHEM bar
//   vol 736,443 / 50-SMA ~780,411 = RV ~0.94.
// v2.9 (10 Jul 2026): ON-CANDLE "GO" NOW MATCHES THE PANEL. Previously the teal
//   "GO" candle marker fired on the INTRADAY leg alone (10-EMA reclaim + squeeze),
//   so it could print while the panel TRIGGER correctly said "no volume" / "no
//   support" — the marker and the panel disagreed. Fixed: the "GO" marker now
//   fires ONLY on the combined gate `go` (= panel TRIGGER = GO: a leg fired AND
//   volume AND support). A chart "GO" now always means TAKE THE TRADE. The
//   intraday momentum LEG, when it fires but the gate is NOT met, shows as a small
//   cyan triangle (no text) so it can never be mistaken for a tradeable GO.
//   Also in v2.9:
//   - STATUS row restored (bottom of panel) — a verbatim one-line summary of every
//     gate (E/V/I/Sup), the RV vs floor, mode + Σ, and the blocking reason in words.
//   - RV row + the volume gate now BOTH use the TRADING-TIMEFRAME RV (chart_rv, e.g.
//     the live 75/125m bar), labelled with the TF — was yesterday's confirmed daily
//     RV in the display vs a different RV in the gate. Panel RV == the RV that gates.
//   - New input `auto_require_below_200` (default ON) to relax the Auto→Recovery
//     200-DMA requirement. Pine can't read the Golden Matcher's live path, so for
//     names where GM disagrees, set Mode = Bull/Recovery MANUALLY (authoritative).
// v2.8 (10 Jul 2026): `use_chart_tf` now defaults ON, so the Pine PA battery
//   runs on the chart TF (75/125m) out of the box — MATCHING the Golden Matcher,
//   whose Trigger TF also defaults to 75m. (On a Daily chart the toggle is a
//   no-op: chart TF = daily. The Auto path / Stage-2 Launch / 30-WMA Reclaim /
//   support zones remain Daily/Weekly regardless — verified.)
// v2.7 (10 Jul 2026): REVIEW of Gemini's v2.5/v2.6 + 2 parity fixes so the Pine
//   chart-TF battery matches the Golden Matcher Python exactly:
//   - v2.5 (responsive triggers) & v2.6 (`use_chart_tf`) KEPT — sound. The Auto
//     path (auto_rec), Stage-2 Launch (kLAU) and 30-WMA Reclaim (kRECLAIM) all
//     correctly stay Daily/Weekly regardless of use_chart_tf, and the OB/FVG/
//     pivot support ZONES stay Daily/Weekly (structural). TF-aware volume + the
//     relaxed squeeze window are the right responsiveness fixes.
//   - FIX 1: HTF (Power Play, "100% in 8 weeks") is positional → now SUPPRESSED
//     in chart-TF mode (it was the one positional pattern leaking to 75/125m;
//     matches the GM Python's intraday=True).
//   - FIX 2: the chart-TF engulf now uses the DAILY EMA20/EMA10 (passed into
//     f_daily_pa) — honours the DNA "EMA20 is a daily anchor" rule and matches
//     the GM Python's ema20_ref, instead of a fresh intraday EMA20.
// v2.6 (10 Jul 2026): TIMEFRAME-AWARE PA PATTERNS:
//   - Added `use_chart_tf` toggle. When ON, the 17 PA patterns and recovery
//     extras (such as VDU, Climax, Spring) are calculated on the active chart
//     timeframe (e.g. 75m/125m) instead of daily. This matches the Golden Matcher's
//     behavior when its Trigger TF is set to 75m/125m.
// v2.5 (10 Jul 2026): RESPONSIVE INTRADAY TRIGGERS (fix for restrictive signals):
//   - Added `require_squeeze` toggle (default ON). When OFF, a high-volume 10-EMA
//     reclaim on the intraday chart can fire the GO signal immediately.
//   - Relaxed Squeeze Trigger Window: allows entry while momentum is actively
//     rising out of the squeeze (rather than only the single fire candle).
//   - Timeframe-Aware Volume: uses real-time 75m/125m relative volume instead of
//     daily relative volume. Prevents morning breakouts from being blocked by
//     incomplete daily volume bars.
// v2.4 (10 Jul 2026): Zones now START AT THEIR FORMATION CANDLE. f_zones()
//   captures the origin bar time of each OB (the down-candle), FVG (the 3-bar
//   gap's middle candle) and pivot (the pivot-low bar), and the boxes/lines are
//   drawn from that time and extend right — so a zone begins at the candles that
//   made it (not the fixed 180/540-day lookback of v2.1, which started "from
//   nowhere"). The fixed window survives only as a fallback if a formation time
//   is missing. Flipped pivots keep their original pivot's origin time.
// ============================================================================
// v2.3 (9 Jul 2026): AUTO PATH ↔ GOLDEN MATCHER PARITY. Auto now mirrors the
//   GM's structural Bull-vs-Recovery split by adding the 200-DMA discriminant:
//   a name ABOVE its 200-DMA resolves Bull (matches GM's Bull-by-default /
//   accumulation-above-200DMA), and only a genuinely beaten-down turn (>= floor
//   off 52wk high AND 30-WMA not repaired AND BELOW the 200-DMA) flips to
//   Recovery. Stops a shallow bull PULLBACK (10-15% off highs, still above the
//   200-DMA) from mis-resolving Recovery while GM stays Bull. Auto-basis panel
//   row shows the 200-DMA state; manual Mode override unchanged. Residual gap
//   (documented): Pine can't see RFF, so an early recovery that already reclaimed
//   the 200-DMA resolves Bull here vs Recovery on GM — override manually.
//   (NB: REJECTED Gemini's "double-shift" fix — its timeframe.isdaily gate
//   reintroduces the intraday repaint; the [1] offset is TF-independent.)
// v2.2 (9 Jul 2026): FULL ZONE LIFECYCLE — FRESH → TESTED → VIOLATED.
//   FRESH: formed, not revisited — tradeable (the first tap is the setup).
//   TESTED: price ENTERED then LEFT (one mitigation) → greys out + EXCLUDED from
//     require_support / the GO trigger (only fresh zones qualify). The current
//     first tap still reads fresh; it greys once price leaves.
//   VIOLATED: a bar CLOSES below the zone's distal (bottom) → DELETED immediately
//     (stops drawing + counting). A wick below that closes back inside is a
//     spring, NOT a violation — the zone survives. Weekly zones are violated only
//     on a WEEKLY close below (f_zones runs per-TF), Daily on a daily close.
//   Pivot lines are NEVER deleted (structural): tested → stay as support;
//   VIOLATED (close below) → FLIP to resistance (maroon "Pivot S→R", previous-
//   support-now-resistance) and stay, cleared only when price reclaims (close
//   above). Mirrored 1:1 into the GM Python (ob_tested/fvg_tested; pivot/pivot_res).
// v2.1 (9 Jul 2026): SUPPORT ZONES ON DAILY *AND* WEEKLY, drawn as PERSISTENT
//   horizontal bands. The OB/FVG/pivot trackers were extracted into f_zones()
//   and are now requested on BOTH "D" and "W" (the trading TF is 75/125-min, but
//   demand zones come from Daily + Weekly structure). Zones are drawn with
//   xloc.bar_time + extend.right, so each renders as a FULL-WIDTH band at its
//   price on ANY chart timeframe (not a bar_index box that shrinks on intraday).
//   Weekly = solid/thick (bigger structural demand), Daily = dashed/thin.
//   `require_support` now passes on a Daily OR Weekly OR AVWAP zone; the Support
//   Zone panel row shows "D:.. W:.." and the GO alert names the timeframe. Also
//   fixed the weekly Stage-2-Launch offset (a `timeframe.isweekly` gate had made
//   75/125-min charts repaint the weekly crossover — now TF-independent). New
//   `show_zones` toggle. Mirrored 1:1 into the GM Python (`detect_support_zones_dw`).
// v2.0 (9 Jul 2026): AUTOMATED SUPPORT ZONES — Steps 1 & 2 of the Golden Matcher
//   Guided Execution (mark the demand zone / set the alert) are now drawn for you:
//     • Daily Order Block  — last down-candle before a volume displacement up.
//     • Daily FVG          — 3-bar bullish fair-value gap (high[2] < low).
//     • Pivot Support      — confirmed ta.pivotlow(5,5), invalidated on close-below.
//   Each is stateful (invalidates on a close below the zone), drawn as a box/line
//   near the last bar, and shown in a new "Support Zone" panel row. New input
//   `require_support` (default ON) gates GO on price being inside/near a support
//   level — automating "is price at a real demand zone?". Two fixes over the
//   initial cut: (a) the confirmed-daily offset is timeframe-independent again
//   (a `timeframe.isdaily` gate had made 75/125-min charts repaint the battery
//   through the session); (b) an AVWAP support now counts toward `support_pass`,
//   so an AVWAP bounce isn't suppressed for lacking an OB/FVG. GO alert names the
//   zone. Mirrored 1:1 into the Golden Matcher Python (`_detect_support_zones`).
// v1.9 (9 Jul 2026): GM-parity + alert upgrades (audit follow-up):
//   - Higher-Low/2B gains the base-proximity ceiling (recent low <= prior base
//     low * 1.10) — without it the pattern fired on almost every green day of
//     an uptrend (same fix applied to pa_patterns.py the same day; zero drift).
//   - Stage-2 Launch now requires the Stage-2 proxy (close above a RISING
//     30-WMA proxy) — mirrors Python's `"2" in stage` gate; previously LAU
//     could fire on a Stage-4 dead-cat bounce crossing the 30-WMA.
//   - Auto-mode 10% off-52WH floor is now an input (auto_dd_floor) — keep it
//     in sync with GM recovery CONFIG min_stock_correction_pct.
//   - New "Auto basis" panel row: shows off52% + 30-WMA state so the Auto
//     Bull/Recovery resolution is explainable at a glance.
//   - Self-describing GO alert(): names mode + which leg fired (AVWAP/intraday)
//     + RV on the GO rising edge. New Σ-strengthening alert when ANOTHER
//     pattern joins while one is already live (pa_fire only caught the first).
// v1.8 (9 Jul 2026): AUTO rule fixed — v1.7's "off52>=15 AND below SMA150" was
//   self-defeating (recovery names at Step 5 have confirmed the turn and often
//   reclaimed SMA150 -> the best recoveries resolved Bull, e.g. CIPLA). Now:
//   Recovery when off52 >= 10 (the GM recovery CONTEXT gate) AND trend-not-repaired
//   (below the 30-WMA proxy OR its 10-day slope falling). Fully repaired = Bull.
// v1.7 (8 Jul 2026): Mode gains AUTO (new default) — infers the path from price
//   structure: >=15% off the 52-week high AND below the 30-WMA proxy (SMA150) ->
//   Recovery battery, else Bull. Mirrors the Golden Matcher's recovery CONTEXT gate.
//   Panel header shows what Auto resolved to: "PA · RECOVERY (auto·EOD)" etc.
//   Manual Bull/Recovery still available as overrides.
// v1.6 (8 Jul 2026): UNIFIED Bull/Recovery. New "Mode" input swaps the PA battery:
//   Bull = the 17 continuation/breakout conditions; Recovery = 10 capitulation-reversal
//   + Wyckoff-accumulation (Climax Reversal, Wyckoff Spring, Higher-Low/2B, Base-Breakout
//   SOS/JAC, Bull Engulf, Hammer-at-support, 3-Bar Rev, Pocket, Volume-Dry-Up, 30-WMA
//   reclaim). Shared plumbing (AVWAP price memory, RV, intraday trigger, TRIGGER gate)
//   is identical; only the battery + panel grid change. Mirrors the Golden Matcher's
//   Bull compute_workflow (17) and Recovery compute_recovery_workflow (10) — zero drift.
// v1.5 (8 Jul 2026): TRIGGER row is now the COMBINED gate — Event(E) + Volume(V) +
//   Intraday(I), each shown ✓/·, colour-coded. GO = a trigger fired (E or I) AND
//   volume (V) — NOT all three at once (avoids a rarely-gettable "Holy Grail").
//   Volume floor is a tunable input (rv_floor, default RV 1.0). RV is now its own
//   colour-coded field. Plan prints only when TRIGGER = GO.
// v1.4 (8 Jul 2026): PA battery expanded 11 → 17 — added the strong v67-cascade
//   triggers the curated 11 omitted: Wyckoff Spring(+3), Gap-Up BO(+3), 50-SMA
//   Undercut(+2), Hammer@50(+2), Hammer@200(+2), Breakout-Confirmed(+2). Panel now
//   shows ALL 17 as a compact grid with per-condition fired(✓)/quiet(·) — no
//   aggregation hides a quiet condition. (Golden Matcher _detect_pa_patterns
//   expanded to the same 17 for zero drift.)
// v1.3 (8 Jul 2026): "Confirmed daily only" toggle (default ON) — the daily PA
//   battery reads the LAST CLOSED daily bar, so patterns no longer repaint on the
//   forming intraday bar. OFF = live developing-bar view. Matches the GM EOD read.
//   Consolidated TRIGGER row + Plan gated to actionable triggers only. Dark theme.
//
// Precision ENTRY layer applied AFTER the Golden Matcher filters a name to Step 5.
//
//   A. DAILY PA PATTERN BATTERY — the SAME conditions surfaced in the Golden
//      Matcher "Full Metric" panel (weinstein_commander_web_v4.0._detect_pa_patterns /
//      _detect_recovery_pa_patterns, 1:1 port of Dashboard v67.4.12). Zero-drift: when a
//      name reaches Step 5, this Pine panel shows the identical patterns firing.
//        Power Play : ★★ HTF(+4) · Strong Close(+2)
//        Momentum   : VCP-BO(+3) · Stage-2 Launch(+3) · Pocket(+2) · Liq Sweep(+2)
//        Reversal   : Bull Engulf-gated(+2) · 3-Bar Rev(+2)
//        Coil       : Inside-3(+2) · True NR7(+1) · ★ IB-NR7(+2)
//      Σ tier shown (Jay's rule: patterns are BONUSES, 11/11 is not the benchmark).
//      NOTE: VCP dry-up uses ta.vwma(VOLUME,5) < sma(volume,50) — the CORRECT
//      canonical formula (pa_field_validator.py). The dashboard .py mirror has a
//      latent (c*v) bug that makes its dry leg a no-op; Pine here is correct.
//   B. Anchored-VWAP PINCH (Low/BO/Gap) + bounce / R2G trigger.
//   C. INTRADAY timing (75/125-min): rising-10-EMA reclaim + TTM squeeze up.
// ============================================================================
//@version=6
indicator("Section 4 Entry Trigger and Price Memory v4.8", shorttitle="S4 Entry", overlay=true, max_boxes_count=500, max_lines_count=160, max_labels_count=500, max_bars_back=300)

// ==========================================================================
// DISPLAY — CATEGORY MASTER SWITCHES  (triage / declutter)
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
// One switch per layer, so a layer that is not earning its keep can be taken
// out of service while you keep trading on the ones that are.
//
// IMPORTANT: OFF removes a layer from the DECISION as well as the chart — the
// support gate, the plan's stop/target, and the confluence score. That is
// deliberate. A layer you have judged untrustworthy must not keep quietly
// steering a trade from behind a hidden drawing; "not shown" and "not counted"
// have to mean the same thing, or turning something off becomes a lie.
//
// These sit ABOVE the per-feature toggles further down and AND with them.
// ==========================================================================
grpDisp = "Display — layers (turn off what isn't working)"
d_zones   = input.bool(true, "Demand / Supply zones (MTF)", group=grpDisp, tooltip="The IZE zone engine (RBR/DBR/RBD/DBD + structural pivot zones), all timeframes. OFF also drops zones from the support gate and the confluence score.")
d_sr      = input.bool(true, "S/R lines (auto + manual)",   group=grpDisp, tooltip="Horizontal levels, all timeframes, both auto-detected and your manual ones. OFF also drops them from the nearest-S/R pickers, the plan and the score.")
d_tl      = input.bool(true, "Trendlines (manual)",         group=grpDisp, tooltip="Your click-to-place trendlines. OFF also drops them from the pickers, the plan and the score.")
d_lvls    = input.bool(true, "FVG / pivot levels",          group=grpDisp, tooltip="Daily/Weekly FVG boxes and pivot S/R. OFF also drops them from the support gate.")
d_avwap   = input.bool(true, "Anchored VWAPs",              group=grpDisp, tooltip="The three AVWAP curves + the pinch read. OFF also drops AVWAP from the support gate and the score.")
d_markers = input.bool(true, "Chart markers (GO / PA / triggers)", group=grpDisp, tooltip="The on-candle labels only. This does NOT change the signal — the PA battery keeps running and the panel keeps reading. Purely visual decluttering.")
d_pat     = input.bool(true, "Patterns (flag / geometry / box)", group=grpDisp, tooltip="The flag detector, the pivot-based geometry read (triangle / wedge / channel / range) and your manual consolidation box. OFF also drops the flag from the confluence score.")
d_panel   = input.bool(true, "Panel",                       group=grpDisp)

grpAV = "Anchored VWAPs"
show_low  = input.bool(true, "AVWAP · Stage-1 Low",  group=grpAV, inline="l")
show_bo   = input.bool(true, "AVWAP · Breakout",     group=grpAV, inline="b")
show_gap  = input.bool(true, "AVWAP · Gap-up",       group=grpAV, inline="g")
low_look  = input.int(252, "Low-anchor lookback (days)", minval=40, group=grpAV)
bo_look   = input.int(40,  "Breakout-anchor lookback (days)", minval=10, group=grpAV)
gap_pct   = input.float(3.0, "Gap-up min %", minval=0.5, step=0.5, group=grpAV)
gap_volx  = input.float(1.5, "Gap-up vol x 50d avg", minval=1.0, step=0.25, group=grpAV)

grpPA = "Daily PA battery (Golden Matcher)"
mode      = input.string("Auto", "Mode", options=["Auto", "Bull", "Recovery"], group=grpPA,
     tooltip="Auto = infer the path from price structure (>=15% off the 52-week high AND below the 30-WMA proxy -> Recovery, else Bull) — mirrors the Golden Matcher's recovery CONTEXT gate; the panel header shows which battery Auto resolved to. Bull = force the 17 continuation/breakout conditions. Recovery = force the 10 capitulation-reversal + Wyckoff-accumulation conditions. Everything else (AVWAP price memory, RV, intraday trigger) is shared.")
show_pa   = input.bool(true, "Detect the PA patterns", group=grpPA)
use_chart_tf = input.bool(true, "Use chart timeframe for PA patterns", group=grpPA,
     tooltip="ON (default v2.8) = the PA battery is calculated on the current chart timeframe (75/125m) to MATCH the Golden Matcher, whose Trigger TF also defaults to 75m. HTF stays suppressed and the engulf keeps its daily EMA20 anchor. OFF = always Daily (EOD). On a Daily chart this toggle is a no-op (chart TF = daily).")
confirm_daily = input.bool(true, "Confirmed daily only (no intraday repaint)", group=grpPA,
     tooltip="ON = read the LAST CLOSED daily bar (matches the Golden Matcher's EOD read; no forming-bar flicker). OFF = live developing daily bar (repaints intraday). Applies only when 'Use chart timeframe' is OFF.")
rv_floor  = input.float(1.0, "Volume floor (RV) for a valid trigger", minval=0.0, step=0.25, group=grpPA,
     tooltip="A trigger only counts as GO if relative volume >= this. 1.0 = average day. A real breakout usually has RV > 1.25. Lower it (e.g. 0.8) if you find it too strict; raise it to demand stronger participation.")
auto_dd_floor = input.float(10.0, "Auto: min % off 52W high for Recovery", minval=0.0, step=1.0, group=grpPA,
     tooltip="Auto mode resolves to the RECOVERY battery when the stock is at least this % off its 52-week high (and the 30-WMA proxy is not repaired). Keep in sync with the Golden Matcher recovery CONFIG min_stock_correction_pct (10).")
auto_require_below_200 = input.bool(true, "Auto: also require price BELOW 200-DMA for Recovery", group=grpPA,
     tooltip="v2.9. ON (default) = Auto only flips to Recovery when price is BELOW its 200-DMA (stops a shallow bull PULLBACK, still above the 200-DMA, from mis-resolving Recovery — this is why Auto stays on the Bull path for most names). Turn OFF if you want early recoveries that have ALREADY reclaimed the 200-DMA to resolve Recovery. NOTE: Pine cannot see the Golden Matcher's live Bull/Recovery decision — for names where GM disagrees with Auto, set Mode = Bull or Recovery MANUALLY when you create the alert (that override is authoritative).")

grpPZ = "Pinch & entry zone"
pinch_pct = input.float(2.5, "Pinch tolerance (% spread across AVWAPs)", minval=0.5, step=0.5, group=grpPZ)
plan_slbuf_pct = input.float(0.5, "Plan: SL buffer below the structural level (%)", minval=0.1, maxval=2.0, step=0.1, group=grpPZ, tooltip="The Plan places the SL this far below the structural level (zone distal / swing low). Dedicated input: it was previously borrowed from the AVWAP touch tolerance, so widening that band silently widened every stop.")
entry_method = input.string("Buy-stop (confirmation)", "Plan: entry method", options=["Buy-stop (confirmation)", "Retest (pullback limit)"], group=grpPZ, tooltip="#retest (Jay, 23-Jul, A/B): how the Plan tells you to ENTER once GO fires.\n• Buy-stop (confirmation) [DEFAULT, house doctrine] — arm a buy-STOP above the confirmed trigger bar's HIGH; you only fill if price continues UP through the high. Avoids the false-breakout trap (no resting limit at a level that keeps falling). Higher entry.\n• Retest (pullback limit) — arm a buy-LIMIT at the confirmed trigger bar's CLOSE; you fill only if price pulls BACK to value. Lower entry / better R. Backtest (replay.py) found retest beat buy-stop on matched alpha across every family (-0.02→+0.38%), BUT the sim cannot model the false-breakout whipsaw the buy-stop avoids — this toggle is to TRIAL retest live, not a directive. Trigger is unchanged (a real GO still has to fire first); only the fill instruction changes.")
bool use_retest = entry_method == "Retest (pullback limit)"
tol_pct   = input.float(1.0, "Support-touch tolerance (% around AVWAP)", minval=0.25, step=0.25, group=grpPZ)
require_support = input.bool(true, "Require Price in Support Zone (OB/FVG/Pivot)", group=grpPZ, tooltip="If ON, the GO entry trigger will only fire if the close is inside or within 1.5% of an active Order Block, Fair Value Gap, Pivot Support (Daily OR Weekly) or AVWAP. This automates Steps 1 & 2 of the Guided Execution checklist.")
ext_atr_max = input.float(4.0, "Over-extended above EMA20 (× ATR)", group=grpPZ, minval=1.0, maxval=10.0, step=0.5, tooltip="#3 (19-Jul): price further than this many chart-ATRs ABOVE the daily EMA20 is CHASING, even at a valid location — some GOs were firing well extended from value. Does NOT gate the GO (anti-Holy-Grail); it feeds the VERDICT: a GO while extended carries a chase-risk caveat / downgrades quality, and the extension prints in the metrics digest. Matches the GM's Step-4 EMA20 ceiling (4 ATR).")
ath_prox_pct = input.float(3.0, "Blue-sky breakout: within % of 52W high", group=grpPZ, minval=0.5, maxval=10.0, step=0.5, tooltip="#ATH (Jay, 19-Jul): a Stage-2 leader (above a rising 30WMA + 200DMA) consolidating within this % of its 52-week high is a BREAKOUT PIVOT, not distribution. The 'supply zone' there IS the prior high — meant to BREAK, not reject. When price is in that supply band, the verdict reframes 'SKIP · no room' into 'BREAKOUT PIVOT' (arm the buy-stop above the band ceiling; blue sky above), instead of applying range logic to a momentum setup. Only fires in a Stage-2 uptrend — a Stage 3/4 name at a lower high stays a real SKIP.")
show_zones = input.bool(true, "Draw OB / FVG / Pivot zones (Daily + Weekly)", group=grpPZ, tooltip="Draws the auto support zones: Daily = dashed thin, Weekly = solid thick (bigger structural demand). Trading TF stays 75/125-min.")

grpIN = "Intraday trigger (apply on 75/125-min)"
show_intraday = input.bool(true, "Show intraday 10-EMA + TTM-squeeze trigger", group=grpIN)
require_squeeze = input.bool(true, "Require TTM Squeeze to fire", group=grpIN, tooltip="If ON, the intraday trigger requires a TTM squeeze release. If OFF, a high-volume 10-EMA reclaim alone can trigger the entry on the 75/125m chart.")
ema_len   = input.int(10, "Intraday EMA length", minval=3, group=grpIN)
bb_mult   = input.float(2.0, "BB mult", step=0.5, group=grpIN)
kc_mult   = input.float(1.5, "KC mult", step=0.5, group=grpIN)
sqz_len   = input.int(20, "Squeeze length", minval=5, group=grpIN)

grpV = "Display"
use_closed_candle = input.bool(true, "Signals from last CLOSED candle (no intraday repaint)", group=grpV, tooltip="ON (default): the TRIGGER / GO / RV / STATUS and the on-chart GO markers are read from the LAST CLOSED chart candle, so a shortlisted signal does NOT drop the moment a new bar opens (the forming bar has little volume / an undeveloped pattern). The signal only updates when the current bar CLOSES. OFF: live forming-bar values (repaint intraday).")
show_panel = input.bool(true, "Entry panel", group=grpV)
panel_pos  = input.string("bottom_right", "Panel position", options=["top_right","top_left","bottom_right","bottom_left"], group=grpV)
c_low  = input.color(#42a5f5, "Low",  group=grpV, inline="c")
c_bo   = input.color(#ab47bc, "BO",   group=grpV, inline="c")
c_gap  = input.color(#ff9800, "Gap",  group=grpV, inline="c")

// ==========================================================================
// Z0. INSTITUTIONAL ZONE ENGINE — INPUTS  (ported from Zone Engine v4.2)
// ==========================================================================
// These drive the demand/supply zone subsystem (Z1–Z6 below). Defaults match
// the Institutional Zone Engine v4.2 so zone geometry is identical. The IZE
// panel/webhook/reversal machinery is intentionally NOT ported (S4 has its own).
grpZG = "Zones — Geometry (Zone Engine)"
ercMult        = input.float(1.2,  "Leg Candle Min Range (× ATR14)",  group=grpZG, minval=0.5, step=0.1, tooltip="A 'leg' candle's True Range must exceed ATR14 by this multiple. Lower = more zones.")
legBodyRatio   = input.float(0.75, "Min Leg Body / Range (Strong)",   group=grpZG, minval=0.50, maxval=1.0, step=0.05)
legBodyAvg     = input.float(0.55, "Min Leg Body (Average + Follow)", group=grpZG, minval=0.30, maxval=0.90, step=0.05, tooltip="Average legs (>= this but < Strong) accepted only with strong follow-through. Also the leg-IN body threshold.")
legInMaxWickR  = input.float(1.0,  "Max Leg-In Wick / Body",          group=grpZG, minval=0.2, maxval=3.0, step=0.1)
// PER-TF leg-in strictness. The leg-in gate was a single global 1.0×ATR (raised from
// 0.3 on 17-Jul) — the biggest recent detection tighten, and it collided with #35: you
// wanted 1.2 to kill a spurious MONTHLY base, but the same knob then starved DAILY and
// INTRADAY zones (Jay's "many daily/intraday zones not being marked"). Now split: a loose
// leg-in for intraday+daily (more zones) and a strict one for weekly+monthly (no spurious).
legin_ltf      = input.float(0.6,  "Leg-IN min range — intraday/daily (× ATR14)", group=grpZG, minval=0.2, maxval=3.0, step=0.1, tooltip="The leg-in must BE a leg, but a moderate one qualifies on the fast timeframes where a strict 1.0-1.2 gate was silently dropping valid daily/intraday demand & supply zones. Lower = more zones. Watch natC d on the diagnostics row.")
legin_htf      = input.float(1.0,  "Leg-IN min range — weekly/monthly (× ATR14)", group=grpZG, minval=0.3, maxval=3.0, step=0.1, tooltip="Leg-in strictness for the HTF zones. DEFAULT 1.0 (restored) — 1.2 was applied globally off ONE spurious ACUTAAS monthly zone (#35), which tightened weekly/monthly detection on EVERY symbol. Raise it to 1.2 on a chart where you actually see a spurious HTF base; do not carry that globally. The levers exist to STRENGTHEN identification, not to filter everything out.")
base_rng_atr   = input.float(0.6,  "Base small-range max (× ATR14)",  group=grpZG, minval=0.2, maxval=1.5, step=0.1, tooltip="A candle counts as BASE when its body/range is small OR its true range is below this many ATR. Was hardcoded. The hard base veto stays '''Max Base TR''' (2.5).")
strongFTMult   = input.float(0.75, "Strong Follow-Through (× ATR)",   group=grpZG, minval=0.3, maxval=3.0, step=0.1)
bodyRatio      = input.float(0.65, "Max Base Body / Range",           group=grpZG, minval=0.10, maxval=0.90, step=0.05)
maxBaseTR      = input.float(2.5,  "Max Base TR (× ATR)",             group=grpZG, minval=0.5, maxval=5.0, step=0.1)
minBase        = input.int(1,      "Min Base Candles",                 group=grpZG, minval=1, maxval=20)
maxBase        = input.int(6,      "Max Base Candles",                 group=grpZG, minval=1, maxval=20)
baseStreak     = input.int(0,      "Non-Base Tolerance (candles)",     group=grpZG, minval=0, maxval=5)
// The old single "Follow-Through Bars Required" input conflated two unrelated roles and
// misdescribed both: it was really a FIXED detection offset, so raising it slid the whole
// window into the past instead of demanding more follow-through, and setting it to 0
// silently disabled the average-leg rescue AND the entire FVG subsystem. Split in two:
ftLagBars   = input.int(1, "Confirmation lag (bars)",         group=grpZG, minval=1, maxval=5, tooltip="How many CLOSED bars must pass after a leg-out before its zone is drawn. 1 = the zone appears on the bar after the leg-out closes (non-repainting).\n\nThis is a detection LAG, not a follow-through requirement — a strong leg-out needs no follow-through at any setting.\n\nMinimum is 1 by design: at 0 the leg-out would be the still-forming bar (repaint), and an FVG around it could not be measured (there is no bar after it yet).")
ftMaxRescue = input.int(2, "Max follow-through rescue bars",  group=grpZG, minval=0, maxval=4, tooltip="Follow-through is a RESCUE, never a requirement.\n\nA STRONG leg-out (body/range >= 'Min Leg Body / Range') is accepted on its own with zero follow-through.\n\nAn AVERAGE leg-out (body >= 'Min Leg Body (Average + Follow)' but below Strong) is rejected on its own, and may instead be rescued by up to this many bars of follow-through (net displacement > 'Strong Follow-Through × ATR', with no close back through the leg-out's opposite extreme). When it is rescued it becomes the LEG-OUT rather than a base candle, so the zone is NARROWER.\n\n0 = no rescue: only strong leg-outs ever form zones.")
prov_zone   = input.bool(true, "Preview a leg-out on the LAST closed bar", group=grpZG, tooltip="A zone needs its leg-out to be at least one bar back (Confirmation lag), so the NEWEST zone cannot appear until a fresh bar exists. Intraday that is one bar. At a session close it is until the next session — and at FRIDAY's close, the whole weekend, which is exactly when you mark zones.\n\nON: after the normal search finds nothing, on the last CLOSED bar the engine also checks whether that bar is a STRONG leg-out, and draws the zone DASHED as a preview.\n\nIt is a PREVIEW, not a zone: it does NOT gate GO / support and is NOT in the zone counts. The real zone is created normally on the next bar, once follow-through and the FVG can actually be measured — both need a bar AFTER the leg-out to exist, which is time, not something code can shortcut.\n\nOnly STRONG leg-outs preview, and that is the honest limit: a weak leg needs follow-through to qualify, and there is none yet.")
// (No "Use Invisible Candles" toggle: zone detection ALWAYS uses gap-bridged OHLC —
//  that is the marking methodology, not a preference. See "Draw Invisible Candles"
//  under Zones — Visual to show them on the chart.)
proxLineMode   = input.string("Body Extreme", "Proximal Line Source",  group=grpZG, options=["Body Extreme", "Wick Extreme"])
// (distLineMode RETIRED 17-Jul: all distals are wick distals by house rule — the
//  Body option silently mislabelled half the stops it was ever applied to.)
dedupSameBase = input.bool(true, "Dedup zones cut from the same base", group=grpZG, tooltip="#7 (19-Jul): two pattern zones carved from the SAME base candles (one counting 3, one counting 2) are a single formation read twice — only one is correct. A new pattern zone overlapping an existing same-TF, same-direction pattern zone by >= 50% of the smaller zone's width is skipped (first formation wins). Adjacent / lightly-overlapping zones are untouched. OFF = pre-#7 behaviour (both drawn).")
narrowWickToWick = input.bool(true, "Narrow zones: draw wick-to-wick", group=grpZG, tooltip="#34: the distal is always a wick; the proximal defaults to the BODY extreme. When a thin-bodied base makes the body-to-wick zone narrower than the per-TF width FLOOR, the proximal is widened out to the base's own wick (wick-to-wick), rescuing a precise zone that would otherwise be rejected as too narrow. OFF = reject narrow zones as before.")

// Per-TF zone-width band (× ATR14 of that TF). A pattern zone is only accepted when
// its width (proximal−distal) is between Min and Max × the TF's ATR. Tighter maxima
// on LTF force crisp entries; wider on HTF allow broad institutional bases. Native
// chart-TF zones pick the pair matching the chart timeframe (75m / 125m / D / W / M).
grpZW = "Zones — Width Band (× ATR14, per timeframe)"
minZW_M   = input.float(0.5,  "Monthly — Min Width",  group=grpZW, minval=0.0, step=0.1,  inline="m")
maxZW_M   = input.float(4.0,  "Max",                  group=grpZW, minval=0.5, step=0.1,  inline="m")
minZW_W   = input.float(0.4,  "Weekly — Min Width",   group=grpZW, minval=0.0, step=0.1,  inline="w")
maxZW_W   = input.float(3.5,  "Max",                  group=grpZW, minval=0.5, step=0.1,  inline="w")
minZW_D   = input.float(0.3,  "Daily — Min Width",    group=grpZW, minval=0.0, step=0.1,  inline="d")
maxZW_D   = input.float(3.0,  "Max",                  group=grpZW, minval=0.5, step=0.1,  inline="d")
minZW_125 = input.float(0.25, "125-min — Min Width",  group=grpZW, minval=0.0, step=0.05, inline="i125")
maxZW_125 = input.float(2.5,  "Max",                  group=grpZW, minval=0.5, step=0.1,  inline="i125")
minZW_75  = input.float(0.2,  "75-min — Min Width",   group=grpZW, minval=0.0, step=0.05, inline="i75")
maxZW_75  = input.float(2.0,  "Max",                  group=grpZW, minval=0.5, step=0.1,  inline="i75")

grpZF = "Zones — Native-TF Filters (Zone Engine)"
volMult    = input.float(0.0,  "Volume Surge (× 20-bar Avg)",  group=grpZF, minval=0.0, step=0.1, tooltip="0 = disabled. When > 0 the leg-out volume must exceed this × 20-bar average.")
useEMA     = input.bool(false,  "Require Daily EMA20 Alignment", group=grpZF)
useRS      = input.bool(false,  "Require Nifty 500 RS Positive", group=grpZF)
requireBOS = input.bool(false,  "Require Break of Structure",    group=grpZF)

grpZM = "Zones — Multi-Timeframe (HTF visible on LTF only)"
showChartZones = input.bool(true,  "Chart-TF Zones",   group=grpZM)
showDaily      = input.bool(true,  "Daily HTF Zones",  group=grpZM)
showWeekly     = input.bool(true,  "Weekly HTF Zones", group=grpZM)
showMonthly    = input.bool(true,  "Monthly HTF Zones", group=grpZM)
require_intraday_fvg = input.bool(false, "Intraday: require leg-out FVG (hard Polygraph gate)", group=grpZM, tooltip="OFF (default, Option C): ALL qualifying intraday pattern zones are drawn; the FVG-Polygraph-qualified ones (leg-out left a 75/125m FVG) are TAGGED with ⚡ + a brighter border, but not filtered out. ON (Option A): on a 75/125m chart only FVG-backed native zones are drawn (the strict FVG Polygraph Test).")

grpZC = "Zones — Confluence Scoring (Zone Engine)"
htfBoost         = input.int(15,   "HTF Overlap Bonus (pts)",        group=grpZC, minval=0, maxval=50)
sameTfBoost      = input.int(5,    "Same-TF Overlap Bonus (pts)",    group=grpZC, minval=0, maxval=25)
emaProxBoost     = input.int(10,   "EMA20 Directional Bonus (pts)",  group=grpZC, minval=0, maxval=30)
emaProxThreshATR = input.float(0.5, "EMA20 'Nearby' Threshold (× ATR)", group=grpZC, minval=0.1, maxval=2.0, step=0.1)
gapBonus         = input.int(10,   "Leg-Out Gap Bonus (pts)",        group=grpZC, minval=0, maxval=25)
fvgBonus         = input.int(15,   "Fair Value Gap (FVG) Bonus (pts)", group=grpZC, minval=0, maxval=25)
maxConfBoost     = input.int(50,   "Max Confluence Bonus (cap)",     group=grpZC, minval=0, maxval=80)
emaFarAtr        = input.float(3.0, "EMA20 'Far' Threshold (× own-TF ATR)", group=grpZC, minval=0.5, maxval=10.0, step=0.5, tooltip="#4 (19-Jul): the MIRROR of the proximity bonus. When the daily EMA20 sits on the WRONG side of the zone and further than this (EMA20 below-and-away from a demand zone; above-and-away from supply), the zone is orphaned from value — price would be badly extended by the time it returns — so its quality is REDUCED.")
emaFarMalus      = input.int(10,   "EMA20 'Far' Penalty (pts)",      group=grpZC, minval=0, maxval=30, tooltip="Points SUBTRACTED from the zone score when the EMA20-far condition above is true. 0 = disable the penalty.")

grpZK = "Zones — Controlling (Zone Engine)"
markControlling       = input.bool(true,  "Mark Controlling Zones",    group=grpZK)
controllingMinTf      = input.string("Daily", "Min Timeframe for Controlling", group=grpZK, options=["Chart", "Daily", "Weekly", "Monthly"])
ctrlMinLowerHighs     = input.int(2, "Controlling: min bars of lower highs since prior ATH", group=grpZK, minval=0, maxval=50, tooltip="HOUSE RULE: a demand zone is Controlling only if it LEADS TO a new ATH — never if it CONTINUES one. Requires this many bars printing a lower high between the previous ATH and the zone's leg-in (i.e. price must have come off the high before the zone formed), the base must sit below that prior ATH, and the leg-out must then close through it. Mirrored for supply (higher lows since the prior ATL).\n\nExpect Controlling to be RARE on a strong trender — that is the rule working.\n\n0 = disable the pullback rule (pre-fix behaviour: any new-ATH leg-out qualifies).")

grpZS = "Zones — State & Tested Rule (S4)"
mitBasis       = input.string("Body Close", "Mitigate On",        group=grpZS, options=["Body Close", "Wick Close", "50% Penetration"])
markViolations = input.bool(true, "Mark Zone Violations (dot)",   group=grpZS, tooltip="When a zone is violated (price closes through the DISTAL edge per 'Mitigate On'), the zone is deleted and a small faint red dot is dropped at the distal price on the breaking bar — the only trace left behind.")
// v3.2 TESTED-RULE REBUILD. The three rules are OR'd, so the LOOSEST always wins —
// and on a live 75m chart that produced 685 zones created and ONE alive (a 0.15%
// survival rate). That is not a "tested" rule, it is a delete-everything rule. Root
// cause: not one of the three was scaled to the zone's OWN timeframe or size.
testedTravelMode = input.string("ATR", "Tested: travel measured in", group=grpZS, options=["ATR", "Zone width"], tooltip="Rule 1 of 3 — how far price must travel from the proximal, after a reaction, before the zone counts as spent.\n\nATR (default): scale-consistent. A 3-point zone and a 30-point zone both need a REAL move to retire.\n\nZone width (legacy, pre-v3.2): travel measured in multiples of the zone's own width — which is INVERTED. The narrower the zone, the smaller the move needed to kill it, so the most precise zones (the ones worth keeping) died fastest. A 3pt zone was retired by a 6pt move.")
testedTravelATR  = input.float(2.0, "Tested: travel × ATR14", group=grpZS, minval=0.5, maxval=10.0, step=0.5, tooltip="Used when travel is measured in ATR. Higher = zones survive longer. Turn on 'Show engine diagnostics row' and watch the removal attribution: if 'travel' dominates and zones you want are vanishing, raise this.")
testedTravelMult = input.float(2.0, "Tested: travel × zone width (legacy)", group=grpZS, minval=0.5, maxval=6.0, step=0.5, tooltip="Only used when 'travel measured in' = Zone width. Retained so the pre-v3.2 behaviour is reproducible, not because it is correct.")
tested_tf_match  = input.bool(true, "Tested rules 2 & 3: HTF zones only", group=grpZS, tooltip="Rules 2 and 3 test a close across the DAILY EMA20 / a DAILY-or-Weekly pivot. Those are HTF references, and letting them adjudicate a 75-min zone is a category error: a 75m base does not stop being valid because price crossed a DAILY EMA20 — that event says nothing about whether that base was consumed.\n\nON (default): rules 2 & 3 apply only to Daily-and-above zones (D/W/M, plus native zones on a Daily+ chart). Native INTRADAY zones are judged on travel and violation alone — the two tests that actually concern them.\n\nOFF: pre-v3.2 behaviour — the Daily references judge every zone on every timeframe.")
strongPivotTF  = input.string("Daily", "Tested: strong S/R pivot TF", group=grpZS, options=["Daily", "Weekly"], tooltip="Rule 3 of 3: a strong Support/Resistance = the most recent CONFIRMED pivot high/low on THIS higher timeframe (the normal swing-S/R definition). After a reaction, a demand zone is tested once price CLOSES above the nearest HTF pivot high sitting above the zone; a supply zone once price closes below the nearest HTF pivot low below it.")

grpZAge = "Zones — Ageing (calendar, per timeframe)"
age_monthly_days = input.int(1460, "Monthly zone max age (days)", group=grpZAge, minval=30, tooltip="A zone ages out this many calendar days after its FORMATION. Monthly default 1460 = 4 years.")
age_weekly_days  = input.int(730,  "Weekly zone max age (days)",  group=grpZAge, minval=30, tooltip="Default 730 = 2 years.")
age_daily_days   = input.int(182,  "Daily zone max age (days)",   group=grpZAge, minval=15, tooltip="Default 182 = 6 months.")
age_125_days     = input.int(28,   "125-min zone max age (days)", group=grpZAge, minval=3,  tooltip="Native chart-TF zones when the chart is 125-min (or higher intraday). Default 28 = 4 weeks.")
age_75_days      = input.int(21,   "75-min zone max age (days)",  group=grpZAge, minval=3,  tooltip="Native chart-TF zones when the chart is 75-min (or lower intraday). Default 21 = 3 weeks.")

// ==========================================================================
// S/R LEVELS — absorbed from Commander Chart Markup (v3.2), which is retired.
// AUTO-DETECT is the seed; the MANUAL tier below is the correction. Both are
// TIMEFRAME-SCOPED: a level shows on its own TF and every LOWER one, never
// upward (Monthly everywhere · Weekly on W and below · Daily on D and below).
// The timeframe IS the conviction — it rides to the panel because a stop on a
// WEEKLY level is a deeper distal → wider stop → SIZE DOWN (Gate 4).
// ==========================================================================
// ==========================================================================
// CONFLUENCE SCORE weights. The score GRADES a live GO, it never gates one —
// GO still fires on P·L·V·B alone (anti-Holy-Grail). TIMING events are worth
// more than LOCATION facts: an AVWAP bounce is something HAPPENING; being near
// the EMA20 is something being TRUE. Set any weight to 0 to drop that
// confluence from the score entirely.
// ==========================================================================
grpCF = "Trigger — Confluence Score"
show_cf     = input.bool(true, "Show confluence score", group=grpCF)
show_diag   = input.bool(false, "Show engine diagnostics row", group=grpCF, tooltip="The zone-detection funnel (natC d/f/m/L · struct D/C/L) and the removal attribution (age/travel/emaX/lvlX/violated). Troubleshooting instrumentation — it answers 'why did that zone vanish', not 'should I take this trade'. Off by default; the Zones (MTF) row now carries the tradeable read instead.")
show_analysis = input.bool(true, "Show VERDICT row", group=grpCF, tooltip="#62: the one synthesized line no other row states — swing vs positional decided by the house rules (swing >= 2.0R · positional >= 20% ROI to T1). The old ANALYSIS row also restated CONTEXT / SETUP / RISK, which are already the Structure, STATUS and Entry rows above — that repetition is gone. Turn this off to hide the verdict too.")

grpSize = "Position Sizing"
size_cap  = input.float(0.0, "Capital (₹)", group=grpSize, minval=0.0, tooltip="Total capital the 0.25% risk is taken against. 0 = hide the Qty row. The Qty is computed from the panel's own Entry and SL, so it is the same trade the plan describes.")
size_risk = input.float(0.25, "Risk per trade (%) — BASE", group=grpSize, minval=0.05, maxval=5.0, step=0.05, tooltip="House rule = 0.25%. With Dynamic Risk ON this is the BASE that the Risk-Allocator adjustments scale (0.75×–1.25× Kelly · ATR>3% volatility discount · −0.25% bear-regime discount, floored at 0.25× base). Qty = Capital × Active Risk% / (Entry − SL).")
use_dyn_risk = input.bool(true, "Dynamic risk (Commander Risk Allocator rules)", group=grpSize, tooltip="#12 (19-Jul), ported from Commander_Risk_Allocator_v2.0:\n• KELLY 0.75×–1.25×: +1 pt each for Stage-2 uptrend (above a rising 150-SMA and the 200-SMA), RS improving, volume > 1.1× average → 3 pts = 1.25× · 2 = 1.0× · else 0.75×.\n• VOLATILITY discount: when daily ATR > 3% of price, risk scales by 3/ATR% (a 6%-ATR name risks half).\n• REGIME discount: −0.25% when the CNX500 is below its 200-SMA or the 50<200 (bear market).\nCombined floor = 0.25× base. OFF = flat base risk (pre-#12).")
size_max_alloc = input.float(0.0, "Max allocation per trade (₹)", group=grpSize, minval=0.0, step=10000.0, tooltip="Risk-Allocator capital cap: Qty = min(risk-based qty, this ÷ Entry). 0 = no cap.")

grpTT = "Trade Type & Targets (Swing / Positional)"
use_tradetype_plan = input.bool(true, "Classify Swing/Positional → set SL width & targets", group=grpTT, tooltip="#12b (19-Jul), ported from the Risk Shield Active-Exits classifier + the Commander Risk Allocator canon. A VOLATILE name (daily ATR% high), one FAR off its 52-week high, or one BELOW its 200-DMA trades on a SWING clock — tighter stop, nearer targets. A tight, near-structure leader trades POSITIONAL — wider stop, further targets. The trade type sets the SL fallback/cap multiple and the R-multiple targets (used when no structural overhead exists). OFF = flat 2.5×ATR + structural-only targets (pre-#12b).")
swing_atr_max   = input.float(4.0,  "Swing if daily ATR% >",       group=grpTT, minval=1.0, maxval=15.0, step=0.5, tooltip="Risk Shield rule: ATR > this % of price = a volatile name that belongs on a swing clock.")
swing_off52_max = input.float(30.0, "Swing if % off 52W-high >",   group=grpTT, minval=5.0, maxval=90.0, step=5.0, tooltip="Far off the high (a proxy for 'far from structure', the Risk Shield's dist_from_200>30 rule) → swing.")
tt_sl_swing     = input.float(2.5,  "Swing: SL fallback/cap (× ATR)",     group=grpTT, minval=1.0, maxval=6.0, step=0.5, tooltip="When there is no structural level below (or to cap an over-wide structural stop): swing uses a tighter ATR stop.")
tt_sl_pos       = input.float(4.0,  "Positional: SL fallback/cap (× ATR)",group=grpTT, minval=1.5, maxval=8.0, step=0.5, tooltip="Positional trades need room (the validation lesson: tight stops on long holds give back edge). Wider ATR fallback/cap. Risk Allocator POS = 4.0.")
tt_t1r_swing    = input.float(3.0,  "Swing: T1 (R)",     group=grpTT, minval=1.0, maxval=10.0, step=0.5)
tt_t2r_swing    = input.float(5.0,  "Swing: T2 (R)",     group=grpTT, minval=1.0, maxval=15.0, step=0.5)
tt_t1r_pos      = input.float(5.0,  "Positional: T1 (R)",group=grpTT, minval=1.0, maxval=15.0, step=0.5)
tt_t2r_pos      = input.float(10.0, "Positional: T2 (R)",group=grpTT, minval=1.0, maxval=25.0, step=0.5)
cf_strong   = input.int(6, "Score for a STRONG trigger", group=grpCF, minval=1, maxval=20, tooltip="At or above this the TRIGGER row reads 'GO ★strong'. Purely a read-out — it does NOT gate the GO.")
cf_w_avwap  = input.int(2, "AVWAP trigger (timing)",      group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_intra  = input.int(2, "Intraday leg (timing)",       group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_fvg    = input.int(1, "⚡ FVG-qualified zone",        group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_ctrl   = input.int(1, "Controlling zone",            group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_sr     = input.int(1, "At a fresh S/R level",        group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_ema    = input.int(1, "At EMA20 dynamic support",    group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_avwl   = input.int(1, "Sitting on an AVWAP",         group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_fib    = input.int(1, "At a Fib (38.2/50/61.8)",     group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_pinch  = input.int(1, "AVWAP pinch",                 group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_rv     = input.int(1, "RV strong (expanding)",       group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5)
cf_w_mtf    = input.int(1, "Multi-TF zone overlap (2+)",  group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5, tooltip="Price inside demand zones on 2+ DISTINCT timeframes at once — e.g. a daily zone sitting inside a weekly one.")
cf_w_tl     = input.int(1, "On your manual trendline",    group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5, tooltip="Price sitting on the support trendline YOU drew. A line you placed by hand is a deliberate read, so it counts like any other location confluence.")
cf_w_flag   = input.int(1, "Bull flag",                   group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5, tooltip="A qualified bull flag (pole + tight + counter-trend drift + dry volume + proportional retrace). Not part of the PA battery, so this does not double-count with the P gate.")
cf_rv_strong= input.float(1.25, "RV counts as 'strong' at", group=grpCF, minval=1.0, step=0.05, tooltip="The GO gate only needs RV >= the floor (volume PRESENT). This is the higher bar for volume EXPANDING, which is what earns the point.")
cf_w_arrival= input.int(1, "Sharp arrival at a zone",     group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5, tooltip="Confluence point when price arrived into the zone FAST — a high-velocity drop into demand (or rally into supply), which tends to produce a sharp, immediate rejection. A slow stair-step (GRIND) does NOT earn it. Configured in the 'Arrival & Order-Flow' group.")
cf_w_dailypa= input.int(1, "Daily battery agrees",        group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5, tooltip="#10 (19-Jul): when the chart-TF (75/125m) trigger fires AND the DAILY battery for the same path also has a pattern live, the trigger has multi-timeframe agreement — a stronger signal. GRADE not GATE (a daily pattern confirms only at the daily close; hard-requiring it would make every intraday trigger late — the anti-Holy-Grail ruling). Only counted on an intraday chart with 'Use chart timeframe' ON (elsewhere the battery IS the daily one). 0 = off.")
cf_w_round  = input.int(1, "At a round number",           group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5, tooltip="#13 (19-Jul): price within 0.3% of a psychological round number (step scales with price: 100 above 5000 · 50 above 1000 · 10 above 100 · 1 above 10). Round numbers attract resting orders and act as magnet/reaction levels — a location confluence, +1 like the other location facts.")
cf_w_absorb = input.int(1, "Absorbing (Δ order-flow)",    group=grpCF, minval=0, maxval=5, tooltip="Confluence point when the intrabar up/down-volume delta shows the level being ABSORBED — Δ+ (net buying) or a bullish delta divergence (price lower low, delta higher low) at a demand zone; mirror at supply. This is a bar-classified volume-delta PROXY (via request.security_lower_tf), not true tick/aggressor order-flow, which Pine cannot access on any TradingView plan.")

// ==========================================================================
// ARRIVAL STYLE + ORDER-FLOW FOOTPRINT (bar-level proxy)
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
// "How price returns to a zone matters as much as the zone." A FAST, high-ATR
// drop into demand tends to reject sharply; a slow, stair-stepping GRIND lets
// momentum ABSORB the level and raises bleed-through risk. Arrival Style is pure
// price geometry (fully real). The order-flow read is an intrabar UP/DOWN-VOLUME
// DELTA (each sub-bar's volume classified buy/sell by its own close vs open, via
// request.security_lower_tf) — the same method TradingView's built-in Up/Down
// Volume uses. It is a PROXY: bar-classified, not true tick/aggressor delta (no
// TV plan exposes that to Pine). Seconds-resolution data (Premium) makes the
// intrabar TF granular; a coarser of_ltf gives more history.
// ==========================================================================
grpAF = "Arrival & Order-Flow (bar-level proxy)"
show_arrival = input.bool(true, "Show Arrival · Δ row", group=grpAF)
arr_look     = input.int(20, "Arrival lookback (swing bars)", group=grpAF, minval=5, maxval=100, tooltip="How far back to find the swing extreme that the approach leg is measured from (swing high for a demand arrival, swing low for supply).")
arr_vel_fast = input.float(0.5,  "FAST arrival >= (ATR/bar)",  group=grpAF, minval=0.1, step=0.05, tooltip="Approach velocity = distance covered (in ATR) / bars taken. At or above this it is a FAST/impulsive arrival — a sharp rejection is more likely.")
arr_vel_slow = input.float(0.22, "GRIND arrival <= (ATR/bar)", group=grpAF, minval=0.05, step=0.02, tooltip="At or below this the approach is a slow stair-step — momentum is absorbing into the level, higher bleed-through risk. Between the two thresholds = NORMAL.")
of_ltf       = input.timeframe("1", "Order-flow intrabar TF", group=grpAF, tooltip="The lower timeframe whose bars are classified up/down for the delta. Must be LOWER than the chart TF. '1' = 1-minute sub-bars (good for a 75/125m chart). Set '1S'/'5S' (Premium seconds) for finer delta, or '5' for more history — request.security_lower_tf caps total intrabars (~100k), so a finer TF trades history for granularity; the arrival read only needs recent bars.")
of_win       = input.int(5, "Delta window (bars in the arrival)", group=grpAF, minval=2, maxval=20, tooltip="How many recent bars the arrival delta is summed over, and the lookback for the delta-divergence check.")

grpSR = "S/R Levels — Auto"
show_sr_lv   = input.bool(true, "Draw auto S/R levels", group=grpSR)
sr_pool      = input.int(40, "Levels tracked per timeframe", group=grpSR, minval=8, maxval=120, tooltip="How many recent pivots each timeframe keeps for clustering. Chart Markup capped this at 16 — about 4-6 months of daily bars — so a level from 8 months back was UNREACHABLE at any setting. That was the single biggest reason its S/R felt immature. 40 per timeframe, and each TF clusters its own pivots at its own scale.")
sr_tol       = input.float(0.6, "Cluster tolerance (× ATR14)", group=grpSR, minval=0.1, step=0.1, tooltip="How close two pivots must be to count as the same level. Measured in that TIMEFRAME's own ATR.")
sr_wick_fit  = input.bool(true, "Place the line to thread maximum wicks", group=grpSR, tooltip="#8 (19-Jul): the level line is placed at the midpoint of the INTERSECTION of its member pivots' wick bands (body-top..high for highs, low..body-bottom for lows) — the one price that threads EVERY member wick, truly representing the reaction level. When a new touch's band does not intersect, the line stays put and the touch still counts. OFF = touch-mean placement (pre-#8).")
sr_wick_touch= input.bool(true, "Count wick-pierce touches (max pivot touches)", group=grpSR, tooltip="#30: a pivot also counts toward a level when the level line PIERCES that pivot's wick (the upper wick of a pivot high, the lower wick of a pivot low), not only when the pivot's extreme is within Cluster tolerance. One line can then thread the wicks of MORE pivots, so the touch count reflects the real number it holds. A wick-pierce touch is COUNTED but does not drag the level's price (the line stays where it threads the wicks); only a near-extreme touch nudges it. Still PIVOT wicks only — never arbitrary bars. OFF = extreme-within-tolerance only (pre-#30).")
sr_pv        = input.int(5, "Pivot length (each side)", group=grpSR, minval=2, maxval=20)
sr_min_touch = input.int(2, "Min touches for a level (pivot touches)", group=grpSR, minval=2, maxval=6, tooltip="A single pivot is a SWING POINT, not a level — it takes a SECOND touch to prove price respects it. Without this gate every pivot became a 'level' and the chart filled with one-touch lines that were never S/R at all.\n\nTouches are always PIVOT touches: the engine clusters confirmed pivot highs/lows, never arbitrary bars that drifted close.\n\nThis also anchors the grade: minTouch touches = FRESH (the level just proved itself and is unspent), more = weakening, >= the MTTWR count = primed to break.")
sr_minspace  = input.int(5, "Distinct-test spacing (bars)", group=grpSR, minval=1, maxval=30, tooltip="Two touches closer together than this count as ONE test (Bulkowski). Stops a cluster of wicks a few bars apart from inflating a level's grade.")
sr_mttwr_n   = input.int(6, "MTTWR: tests before a level is 'primed to break'", group=grpSR, minval=2, maxval=12, tooltip="HOUSE RULE, and the opposite of how most tools score S/R: tests WEAKEN a level, they do not strengthen it. 'MTTWR / MTTWS — Multiple Times Tested Weak Resistance / Support (a level tested so often it's primed to break)'.\n\n1 test = FRESH (strongest as S/R) · 2..n-1 = TESTED (valid, weakening) · >= n = MTTWR (spent as a floor; now a BREAKOUT candidate) — and MTTWR is EXCLUDED from the support picker.\n\nDEFAULT RAISED 4 -> 6 (18-Jul): measured on live data, a 40-pivot pool over ~2y graded 40-45% of ALL levels MTTWR, so the nearest support below price was almost always excluded and near_sr effectively never fired — the location gate silently lost a source. At 6, a genuine 5-touch shelf 0.2% under price (e.g. RELIANCE 1324) is correctly usable again. Lower it only if you find levels being leaned on that should have been spent.")
// Clamp: with sr_min_touch >= sr_mttwr_n (both individually legal), every level
// that EXISTS is already MTTWR -> excluded from the picker -> the panel reads
// '-' with no explanation. The effective MTTWR count is forced above min-touch.
int mttwrEff = math.max(sr_mttwr_n, sr_min_touch + 1)
sr_show_M    = input.bool(true, "Show Monthly levels", group=grpSR, inline="tf")
sr_show_W    = input.bool(true, "Weekly",              group=grpSR, inline="tf")
sr_show_D    = input.bool(true, "Daily",               group=grpSR, inline="tf")

grpSRM = "S/R Levels — MANUAL · MONTHLY  (0 = off; shows on ALL timeframes)"
sr_on = input.bool(true, "Enable manual levels (override auto)", group=grpSRM, tooltip="Manual levels OUTRANK auto ones on a side you have marked: your hand-drawn levels ARE the location layer (Gate 2), the auto ones are the fallback for a side you have not marked yet. A side you leave blank still falls back to auto.\n\nType the price once (from the panel), then drag the handle on the chart.")
mv1 = input.price(0.0, "Monthly level 1", group=grpSRM)
mv2 = input.price(0.0, "Monthly level 2", group=grpSRM)
mv3 = input.price(0.0, "Monthly level 3", group=grpSRM)
mv4 = input.price(0.0, "Monthly level 4", group=grpSRM)

grpSRW = "S/R Levels — MANUAL · WEEKLY  (shows on Weekly and below)"
wv1 = input.price(0.0, "Weekly level 1", group=grpSRW)
wv2 = input.price(0.0, "Weekly level 2", group=grpSRW)
wv3 = input.price(0.0, "Weekly level 3", group=grpSRW)
wv4 = input.price(0.0, "Weekly level 4", group=grpSRW)

grpSRD = "S/R Levels — MANUAL · DAILY  (shows on Daily and below; hidden on W/M)"
dv1 = input.price(0.0, "Daily level 1", group=grpSRD)
dv2 = input.price(0.0, "Daily level 2", group=grpSRD)
dv3 = input.price(0.0, "Daily level 3", group=grpSRD)
dv4 = input.price(0.0, "Daily level 4", group=grpSRD)

// ==========================================================================
// TRENDLINES — MANUAL ONLY, by deliberate decision.
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Commander Chart Markup rewrote its auto-fitter NINE times (v1.0/1.7/1.8/1.9/
// 2.0/2.3/2.4/2.6/2.7) and still never produced the line Jay would trade. It
// could not: a horizontal level is ONE number, but a trendline is two anchors
// plus a slope, and "which two pivots" has no global answer — it is chart-
// specific. Every field test moved the weights and broke the previous fix. Its
// own guide concedes it: "Auto-trendlines are read-only guides... hand-draw the
// line you'll trade." So the fitter is NOT ported. The answer was never a better
// algorithm — it was making the line ADJUSTABLE and MACHINE-READABLE.
//
// #47: the anchors were input.time/input.price(confirm=true) = a click-to-place on
// add — but that forced a draw on EVERY load and cancelled the indicator on Esc, so
// confirm was removed. The anchors are now plain numeric inputs (0 = off): type the
// two time/price pairs in the settings dialog to draw. The line is still draggable
// once drawn, and — the point — the engine READS it: it feeds the nearest S/R
// pickers, the PLAN's stop/target, and the confluence score.
//
// ONE pair (support + resistance), each with its own TF tag: a chart has one
// tradeable trendline, and 8 prompts is already the ceiling of tolerable. Same
// guardrail as the levels — shows on its own TF and below, never upward.
// ==========================================================================
// ==========================================================================
// PATTERNS. Deliberately SMALL — S4's PA battery already carries 17 bull + 10
// recovery patterns INCLUDING VCP, so most of what Chart Markup had was either
// already here, something Jay does not trade (Cup & Handle / H&S — his own docs
// call them "heuristic CANDIDATES (false-positive-prone)... eyeball candidates"),
// or structurally broken (its Double-Top only ever examined the LAST TWO pivots,
// so a textbook DT four pivots back was invisible at any tolerance).
// Only three things were worth carrying across:
//   1. FLAG — genuinely missing, and Jay marks them by hand ("Consolidation Box
//      (flag under ATH)"). Chart Markup's version fired on ANY quiet 6-bar range
//      after a 4-ATR move — including a drift WITH the trend, which is not a flag.
//      This one demands the four things that actually define one.
//   2. GEOMETRY — rebuilt from PIVOT SEQUENCES, not from fitted trendline slopes.
//      Chart Markup derived it from its auto-fitter (now deleted) and wrote it to
//      `geom`, never to `pats` — so triangles/wedges could NEVER appear in its
//      PATTERNS row. It also had no ascending/descending/symmetrical split at all.
//   3. Manual consolidation BOX — you draw these; the engine should read them.
// ==========================================================================
grpPAT = "Patterns"
show_flag   = input.bool(true, "Detect flags", group=grpPAT)
flag_pole   = input.int(10,   "Pole lookback (bars)",            group=grpPAT, minval=4, maxval=60)
flag_cons   = input.int(6,    "Consolidation bars",              group=grpPAT, minval=3, maxval=30)
flag_poleA  = input.float(4.0,"Min pole size (× ATR)",           group=grpPAT, minval=1.0, step=0.5)
flag_rngA   = input.float(2.5,"Max consolidation range (× ATR)", group=grpPAT, minval=0.5, step=0.5)
flag_retr   = input.float(0.5,"Max flag retrace (× pole)",       group=grpPAT, minval=0.1, maxval=0.9, step=0.05, tooltip="Pole:flag proportionality. A consolidation that gives back more than this fraction of the pole is not a flag — it is a reversal. Chart Markup had no such check.")
flag_volDry = input.float(0.85,"Max flag volume vs pole (ratio)",group=grpPAT, minval=0.1, maxval=2.0, step=0.05, tooltip="A real flag DRIES UP: average volume through the consolidation must be below this fraction of the pole's. Chart Markup checked no volume at all.")
flag_drift  = input.bool(true, "Require counter-trend drift",    group=grpPAT, tooltip="THE thing that makes a flag a flag: the consolidation must slope AGAINST the pole (a bull flag drifts DOWN). Chart Markup accepted any tight range after an impulse — including a drift WITH the trend, which is a continuation, not a flag.")
show_geom   = input.bool(true, "Geometry read (triangle / wedge / channel / range)", group=grpPAT)
drawGeomLines = input.bool(true, "Draw the geometry lines (not just name them)", group=grpPAT, tooltip="#59: the panel names a shape (e.g. 'Rising channel / wedge') from the last two pivot highs + lows. Without drawing it, the name reads as a phantom — 'no such pattern on the chart'. ON draws the two pivot connectors (extended right) so the named shape is VISIBLE and you can judge it. OFF keeps the name only (old behaviour).")
geo_pv      = input.int(5,    "Geometry pivot length",           group=grpPAT, minval=2, maxval=20)
geo_flat    = input.float(0.3,"Flat tolerance (× ATR)",          group=grpPAT, minval=0.05, step=0.05, tooltip="Two consecutive pivots within this distance count as FLAT (equal) — which is what separates an ascending triangle (flat highs) from a symmetrical one (falling highs).")
geo_maxage  = input.int(120, "Geometry max pivot age (bars)",     group=grpPAT, minval=20, maxval=500, tooltip="The 4 pivots feeding the geometry read must ALL be younger than this. Without it the last two highs could be six months older than the last two lows and still be confidently classified as a triangle.")

// #47: confirm=true forced a click-to-place on EVERY add and cancelled the whole
// indicator on Esc ("it forces me to draw a Trendline first, else it closes"). Pine
// has no conditional confirm, so the anchors are now plain numeric inputs: 0 = off,
// enter time/price in the settings dialog to draw. Loading is instant; the manual
// tools are opt-in via their coordinates, not a load-time gate.
grpBOX = "Consolidation Box — MANUAL  (enter coords in settings; 0 = off)"
box_on = input.bool(true, "Enable manual box", group=grpBOX)
box_t1 = input.time(0,    "Box start time",  group=grpBOX)
box_t2 = input.time(0,    "Box end time",    group=grpBOX)
box_hi = input.price(0.0, "Box top",         group=grpBOX)
box_lo = input.price(0.0, "Box bottom",      group=grpBOX)

grpTL = "Trendlines — MANUAL  (enter coords in settings; price 0 = off)"
tl_on  = input.bool(true, "Enable manual trendlines", group=grpTL, tooltip="There is no auto-fit. See the note in the source: nine rewrites of the Chart Markup fitter never converged, because the right anchors are chart-specific, not a global setting.\n\nAnchors are numeric (0 = off) — enter time/price in this dialog. confirm/click-to-place was removed because it forced a draw on every add and closed the indicator on Esc.")
tls_tf = input.string("Daily", "Support TL — timeframe", options=["Monthly", "Weekly", "Daily"], group=grpTL, tooltip="The TF a line is drawn on IS its weight. Shows on this timeframe and every LOWER one, never upward — a Daily trendline never renders on a Weekly chart.")
tls_t1 = input.time(0,    "Support TL — anchor 1 (swing low) time",   group=grpTL)
tls_p1 = input.price(0.0, "Support TL — anchor 1 price",              group=grpTL)
tls_t2 = input.time(0,    "Support TL — anchor 2 (higher low) time",  group=grpTL)
tls_p2 = input.price(0.0, "Support TL — anchor 2 price",              group=grpTL)
tlr_tf = input.string("Daily", "Resistance TL — timeframe", options=["Monthly", "Weekly", "Daily"], group=grpTL)
tlr_t1 = input.time(0,    "Resistance TL — anchor 1 (swing high) time", group=grpTL)
tlr_p1 = input.price(0.0, "Resistance TL — anchor 1 price",             group=grpTL)
tlr_t2 = input.time(0,    "Resistance TL — anchor 2 (lower high) time", group=grpTL)
tlr_p2 = input.price(0.0, "Resistance TL — anchor 2 price",             group=grpTL)

grpZP = "Zones — Structural (Pivot-Based)"
useStructural   = input.bool(true,  "Draw Pivot (Structural) zones",  group=grpZP, tooltip="Master on/off for ALL pivot (PvH/PvL) zones — the weaker, dashed shelves that come from a bare swing high/low with no leg-base-leg. Uncheck to hide EVERY pivot zone on all timeframes (it stops their creation, so a recompile leaves none on the chart).\n\nUSE THIS TO ISOLATE: turn pivot zones OFF to see ONLY the pattern demand/supply zones (RBR/DBR/RBD/DBD). If a pattern DZ/SZ still doesn't mark with pivots off, the issue is in pattern detection (leg/base/width gates), not a pivot zone hiding or overriding it. Turn the diagnostics row on and read natC d/f/m/L + struct D/C/L alongside.")
pivotLeft       = input.int(5,      "Pivot Left Bars",              group=grpZP, minval=2, maxval=30)
pivotRight      = input.int(3,      "Pivot Right Bars",             group=grpZP, minval=2, maxval=20)
pivotMinMoveATR = input.float(1.0,  "Min Move from Pivot (× ATR)",  group=grpZP, minval=0.2, maxval=10.0, step=0.1)
structPadBars   = input.int(3,      "Zone Pad Bars (each side)",    group=grpZP, minval=0, maxval=15)
structTopThrATR = input.float(1.5,  "Pivot Body-Top Tolerance (× ATR)",   group=grpZP, minval=0.2, maxval=5.0, step=0.1)
structDeepThrATR= input.float(1.5,  "Pivot Body-Bottom Tolerance (× ATR)", group=grpZP, minval=0.5, maxval=8.0, step=0.1)
structMinWMult  = input.float(0.5,  "Structural width floor (× the TF's Min Width)", group=grpZP, minval=0.1, maxval=1.0, step=0.05, tooltip="Structural (pivot) zones now honour the same per-TF width band as pattern zones — they previously bypassed it completely. But a pivot zone's width is body-to-low of ONE candle, so it is legitimately narrower than a leg-base-leg formation: this scales the band's FLOOR down for structural zones only (0.5 = half the TF's Min Width). The band's CEILING is shared unchanged.\n\nIf structural zones vanish after an update, LOWER this — do not disable the band. Watch the 'structD/structL' counters on the Zones (MTF) panel row.")

grpZV = "Zones — Visual (Zone Engine)"
showZonesIZE    = input.bool(true, "Draw Demand/Supply Zones (MTF)", group=grpZV)
showLabels      = input.bool(true, "Show Zone Info Labels",          group=grpZV)
zoneFillTransp  = input.int(88, "Zone fill transparency (0 = solid, 100 = clear)", group=grpZV, minval=60, maxval=98, tooltip="#37: base transparency of the zone BACKGROUND fill. Lower = more opaque / more visible. Per-TF spread is applied on top (Monthly most opaque, chart-native most transparent). Was hard-wired to 93-96 (nearly clear); default 88 makes the fills read without hiding the candles.")
show_tested_grey= input.bool(false, "Show tested zones in grey (verify all zones drawn)", group=grpZV, tooltip="#41: OFF (default) = a zone is DELETED the moment it is tested (declutter — only fresh, tradeable zones stay on the chart). ON = a tested zone is recoloured GREY, dotted border, and FROZEN in place instead of deleted, so you can confirm EVERY valid zone that ever formed was marked correctly. Grey zones are excluded from the trigger and the live DZ/SZ counts — they are a verification overlay only.")
recencyDecay    = input.bool(true, "Recency: decay zone score as it ages", group=grpZV, tooltip="#27: two factors measure a zone — AGE (how long until it is aged off the chart) and RECENCY (a fresh zone is a stronger zone). A newly formed zone shows its FULL score; it loses points linearly as it ages toward its timeframe's ageing cap, floored at 0. Reflected in BOTH the on-chart label and the panel's Support Zone quality grade. OFF = static score (pre-#27).")
recencyMaxDrop  = input.int(20, "Recency: max score drop at full age", group=grpZV, minval=0, maxval=60, tooltip="The full penalty a zone carries once it reaches its timeframe's ageing cap. A zone at HALF its lifespan loses half of this. 20 = a 90-pt fresh zone reads ~80 at half-life and ~70 when nearly aged out — enough to break score ties toward the fresher zone without demoting a genuinely strong old base out of contention.")
drawInvCandles  = input.bool(false, "Draw Invisible Candles (gap-bridged overlay)", group=grpZV, tooltip="Plots the GAP-BRIDGED candles the zone engine reads: each bar's open re-anchored at the previous close, high/low expanded to cover the gap. A small-bodied gap day is really a big leg candle, and this is how you SEE that.\n\nVIEW ONLY. Zone detection ALWAYS uses these candles whether or not this is ticked — it is the marking methodology, not an option — so the overlay can never disagree with what the engine reads. Turning this off hides the candles, it does not change a single zone.\n\nTo see ONLY these candles, hide the native ones: Chart Settings → Symbol → uncheck Body / Borders / Wick.")
invCandleUp     = input.color(color.new(#26a69a, 0), "Invisible candle — up",   group=grpZV, inline="ic")
invCandleDn     = input.color(color.new(#ef5350, 0), "down",                    group=grpZV, inline="ic")
// (v3.0: tested zones are REMOVED from the chart, not greyed — the old
// "Show Tested Zones" toggle was retired.)

// ==========================================================================
// Z1. ZONE ENGINE — TIMEFRAME GUARDRAILS + SHARED STATE
// ==========================================================================
int chartSec   = timeframe.in_seconds(timeframe.period)
int dailySec   = 86400
// CALENDAR seconds, to match timeframe.in_seconds(). The old 432000/1900800 were
// TRADING-day approximations (5x/22x 86400); compared against the calendar chartSec
// they hid Weekly levels on the Weekly chart and blanked the Monthly chart entirely.
// (Zone guardrail behaviour is unchanged by this on every standard TF - verified.)
int weeklySec  = 604800
int monthlySec = 2592000
bool useDailyZ   = showDaily   and dailySec   > chartSec
bool useWeeklyZ  = showWeekly  and weeklySec  > chartSec
bool useMonthlyZ = showMonthly and monthlySec > chartSec
// S/R LEVELS use the SAME guardrail — HTF propagates DOWN, LTF never renders UP —
// reusing the constants above rather than declaring a second set that could drift.
// `>=` not `>`: unlike a zone, a hand-typed Daily level has no separate "native"
// path, so it MUST still render on a Daily chart.
bool useLvM = monthlySec >= chartSec
bool useLvW = weeklySec  >= chartSec
bool useLvD = dailySec   >= chartSec
bool ctrlAllowChart   = controllingMinTf == "Chart"
bool ctrlAllowDaily   = ctrlAllowChart or controllingMinTf == "Daily"
bool ctrlAllowWeekly  = ctrlAllowDaily or controllingMinTf == "Weekly"
bool ctrlAllowMonthly = true
float chart_atr = ta.atr(14)
// v3.2: PER-TIMEFRAME ATR for the tested-travel rule. The travel a zone must see
// before it counts as spent has to be measured in the ZONE's own scale — not the
// chart's. On a 75m chart, `chart_atr` would retire a MONTHLY zone on a 2×(75m ATR)
// move, which is nothing. (This is the one thing the old zone-width scaling got
// right by accident: monthly zones are wide, so 2×width was large. It was still
// wrong WITHIN a timeframe — a narrow 75m zone died on a tiny move.)
float atrD_tf = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", ta.atr(14), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
float atrW_tf = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "W", ta.atr(14), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
float atrM_tf = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "M", ta.atr(14), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
float chartEMA20 = ta.ema(close, 20)   // chart-TF EMA20 (used by the Price-vs-EMA20 panel row on a Daily chart)

// Daily EMA20 (DNA: EMA20 is a DAILY anchor) — used by the zones AND the Price-vs-
// EMA20 panel row / the new tested rule (rule 2).
float dailyEMA20 = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", ta.ema(close, 20), ignore_invalid_symbol=true)
// #10: EMA20 as a DYNAMIC S/R level — daily EMA20 on 75/125m (DNA anchor), chart
// EMA20 on a Daily chart. Feeds the support consideration + the Trigger.
float dyn_ema = timeframe.isintraday ? dailyEMA20 : chartEMA20
// Nifty 500 RS slope (for the optional useRS zone filter).
float n500Close  = request.security("NSE:CNX500", "D", close, ignore_invalid_symbol=true)
float rsRatio    = not na(n500Close) and n500Close > 0 ? close / n500Close : na
float rsLR_diff  = ta.linreg(rsRatio, 60, 0) - ta.linreg(rsRatio, 60, 1)
float rsSlope    = nz(rsLR_diff, 0.0)

// HTF pivots (feed the "tested" rule 3 = close across a strong HTF pivot S/R).
// The last CONFIRMED pivot high/low on the chosen higher timeframe = a normal
// swing Support/Resistance level. Requested on Daily or Weekly per input.
f_htf_piv() =>
    float ph = ta.pivothigh(high, 5, 5)
    float pl = ta.pivotlow(low, 5, 5)
    var float lph = na
    var float lpl = na
    if not na(ph)
        lph := ph
    if not na(pl)
        lpl := pl
    [lph, lpl]
string _strongTF = strongPivotTF == "Weekly" ? "W" : "D"
[lastPH, lastPL] = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, _strongTF, f_htf_piv(), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)

// ==========================================================================
// Z2. ZONE ENGINE — TYPES  (Zone extended with S4 reaction-tracking fields)
// ==========================================================================
type Zone
    float  proximal
    float  distal
    int    originBar
    int    originTime
    bool   isDemand
    int    strength
    int    confBonus
    int    nBase
    string pattern
    string tf
    bool   isControlling
    box    drawing
    label  infoLabel
    bool   wasInZone
    bool   reacted       // S4: price entered then left the zone (a reaction occurred)
    float  reactRef      // S4: proximal captured at the reaction (travel reference)
    float  strongLvl     // S4: nearest strong pivot level to watch (tested rule 3)
    bool   emaPre        // S4: at reaction, price on the pre-cross side of EMA20 (rule 2)
    bool   hasFVG        // S4: leg-out left an FVG → FVG-Polygraph-qualified (⚡ tag)
    bool   tested        // #41: greyed tested state (kept for verification, excluded from trigger)

type ZoneSig
    int    zoneTime
    float  proximal
    float  distal
    bool   isDemand
    int    rawScore
    string pattern
    int    nBase
    int    bStart
    int    baseStartTime
    bool   isControlling
    bool   hasFVG        // S4: leg-out left an FVG (imbalance) — gates intraday chart-TF zones
    bool   isProv        // v3.2: found at ft=0 (leg-out = the last CLOSED bar) → PREVIEW only

var array<Zone> activeZones = array.new<Zone>()

// v3.2 REMOVAL ATTRIBUTION (native chart-TF zones only). The d/f/m/L funnel proves a
// zone was created and later removed, but is SILENT on which of the four exits took
// it — which reduced the last diagnosis to guesswork across three OR'd tested-rules.
// These name the culprit: age / travel / ema-cross / level-cross / violation.
var int _rmAge = 0
var int _rmTrv = 0
var int _rmEma = 0
var int _rmLvl = 0
var int _rmVio = 0

// ==========================================================================
// Z0b. HORIZONTAL S/R LEVELS — timeframe-scoped, fresh-graded
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Absorbed from Commander Chart Markup (which is being retired into this file).
// Two things are DELIBERATELY different from that engine, because both were
// backwards:
//
//  1. TEST COUNT IS A WEAKNESS, NOT A STRENGTH. Chart Markup ranked levels by
//     touch count — more touches = stronger — which inverts the house rule:
//     "MTTWR / MTTWS — Multiple Times Tested Weak Resistance / Support (a level
//     tested so often it's primed to break)". Here a level's tests GRADE it:
//        1 test  → FRESH   (the forming pivot only; strongest as S/R)
//        2..n-1  → TESTED  (still valid, weakening)
//        >= n    → MTTWR   (spent as S/R; now a BREAKOUT candidate, not a floor)
//     Note the deliberate split from ZONES: a zone is FUEL and is consumed by a
//     test (S4 deletes it). A horizontal level is PRICE MEMORY — it survives the
//     test but weakens. That is how "delete tested zones" and "count tests for
//     MTTWR" are both true at once.
//
//  2. THE POOL IS DEEP. Chart Markup capped pivots at 16 (~4-6 months of daily),
//     so a level from 8 months back was structurally unreachable at any setting —
//     the single biggest reason its S/R felt immature. Levels are found inside a
//     per-TF request.security context here, so each timeframe brings its OWN deep
//     history and the daily pool no longer has to reach back years by itself.
//
// ROLE (Support vs Resistance) is DERIVED from price, never fixed at detection,
// so a level flips correctly when price closes through it (the R-flip→S rule).
// ==========================================================================
// Each slot carries four things, because drawing and grading both need more than a
// price: the TEST count (grade), the FIRST-touch time (where the ray starts — a level
// should not be drawn back through history where it was not yet in play), and whether
// the cluster came from pivot HIGHS or LOWS (its ORIGIN — the only way to know a level
// has FLIPPED, since role itself is derived from price and forgets where it came from).
type SRSig
    float a1        // nearest level ABOVE
    int   a1t       // touch count
    int   a1x       // TIME of its first touch
    bool  a1h       // origin = pivot HIGHS (else lows)
    float a2
    int   a2t
    int   a2x
    bool  a2h
    float b1        // nearest level BELOW
    int   b1t
    int   b1x
    bool  b1h
    float b2
    int   b2t
    int   b2x
    bool  b2h

// Cluster pivots into horizontal levels and return the two nearest each side of
// price, with their test counts. Runs natively AND inside request.security, so
// each timeframe clusters ITS OWN pivots at ITS OWN ATR scale — a weekly level is
// found from weekly swings, not by squinting at daily ones.
f_srLevels(simple int pvL, simple int pvR, simple int poolN, simple float tolAtr, simple int minSpace, simple int minTouch, simple bool wickTouch) =>
    a = ta.atr(14)
    // ta.* unconditional every bar (Pine consistency rule).
    float ph = ta.pivothigh(high, pvL, pvR)
    float pl = ta.pivotlow(low,  pvL, pvR)
    // PERSISTENT LEVEL OBJECTS (v3.3 — the grade-drift fix). The old engine kept a
    // rolling 40-PIVOT pool and re-clustered it every bar, so a level's touch count
    // DECAYED as its old members were evicted: MTTWR could quietly downgrade itself
    // to "fresh" — and re-enter the picker as a stop candidate — with no price having
    // touched it. Levels are now first-class objects: a confirmed pivot either MERGES
    // into the level it belongs to (cumulative count — never decays; running-mean
    // price; first-touch time kept, so the ray no longer creeps) or CREATES one.
    // Capacity is a cap on LEVELS (poolN, evicting the oldest first-touch), and since
    // levels are far scarcer than pivots, 40 levels holds YEARS of structure.
    // Merging-on-arrival also makes levels >= tol apart by construction, which
    // retires the slot-dedup patch the old clustering needed.
    var array<float> Lp = array.new<float>()   // level price (running mean of touches)
    var array<int>   Lc = array.new<int>()     // CUMULATIVE touch count
    var array<int>   Lt = array.new<int>()     // first-touch TIME (ray anchor + origin)
    var array<bool>  Lh = array.new<bool>()    // origin: born from a pivot HIGH
    var array<int>   Lb = array.new<int>()     // last-touch bar (distinct-test spacing)
    // #8 wick-fit: running INTERSECTION of the member pivots' wick bands. A line inside
    // this interval threads EVERY member wick — placed at its midpoint (sr_wick_fit).
    var array<float> Lil = array.new<float>()  // intersection low
    var array<float> Lih = array.new<float>()  // intersection high
    float tol = tolAtr * a
    if not na(ph) and not na(a) and a > 0
        // #30: match a level by EXTREME within tol OR by the level PIERCING the pivot's
        // upper wick (body-top..high). Nearest-to-extreme wins among candidates. A
        // pierce-only touch is counted but does NOT drag the level's mean.
        float _wkLo = wickTouch ? math.max(open[pvR], close[pvR]) : ph
        int _j = -1
        float _bd = 1e15
        bool _pierceOnly = false
        if array.size(Lp) > 0
            for i2 = 0 to array.size(Lp) - 1
                float _lp   = array.get(Lp, i2)
                float _d    = math.abs(_lp - ph)
                bool  _near = _d <= tol
                bool  _prc  = wickTouch and _lp <= ph and _lp >= _wkLo
                if (_near or _prc) and _d < _bd
                    _bd := _d
                    _j := i2
                    _pierceOnly := _prc and not _near
        float _bTop = math.max(open[pvR], close[pvR])   // wick band = body-top .. high
        if _j >= 0
            if bar_index - pvR - array.get(Lb, _j) >= minSpace
                int _c = array.get(Lc, _j) + 1
                // #8: place the line to thread the MAXIMUM wicks — intersect this
                // pivot's wick band with the level's running intersection; when it
                // holds, the line moves to the midpoint (threads every member wick).
                // When it doesn't, keep the interval and fall back to the mean drag.
                float _nl = math.max(array.get(Lil, _j), _bTop)
                float _nh = math.min(array.get(Lih, _j), ph)
                // #8 (Jay, 19-Jul): thread the MAX wicks "to the extent possible". When the
                // new pivot's wick band still intersects the running band, shrink+re-centre
                // (one more wick threaded). When it does NOT, the touch STILL COUNTS (Lc++
                // below — count is pivots-only) but the line STAYS put on the max-wick set;
                // it must NOT drift to the mean. Mean-drag only when wick-fit is OFF.
                if sr_wick_fit and _nl <= _nh
                    array.set(Lil, _j, _nl)
                    array.set(Lih, _j, _nh)
                    array.set(Lp, _j, (_nl + _nh) / 2.0)
                else if not sr_wick_fit and not _pierceOnly
                    array.set(Lp, _j, (array.get(Lp, _j) * (_c - 1) + ph) / _c)
                array.set(Lc, _j, _c)
                array.set(Lb, _j, bar_index - pvR)
        else
            array.push(Lp, ph)
            array.push(Lc, 1)
            array.push(Lt, time[pvR])
            array.push(Lh, true)
            array.push(Lb, bar_index - pvR)
            array.push(Lil, _bTop)
            array.push(Lih, ph)
    if not na(pl) and not na(a) and a > 0
        // #30 mirror: match by EXTREME within tol OR the level piercing the pivot's LOWER
        // wick (low..body-bottom). Pierce-only touch counted, does not drag the mean.
        float _wkHi = wickTouch ? math.min(open[pvR], close[pvR]) : pl
        int _j = -1
        float _bd = 1e15
        bool _pierceOnly = false
        if array.size(Lp) > 0
            for i2 = 0 to array.size(Lp) - 1
                float _lp   = array.get(Lp, i2)
                float _d    = math.abs(_lp - pl)
                bool  _near = _d <= tol
                bool  _prc  = wickTouch and _lp >= pl and _lp <= _wkHi
                if (_near or _prc) and _d < _bd
                    _bd := _d
                    _j := i2
                    _pierceOnly := _prc and not _near
        float _bBot = math.min(open[pvR], close[pvR])   // wick band = low .. body-bottom
        if _j >= 0
            if bar_index - pvR - array.get(Lb, _j) >= minSpace
                int _c = array.get(Lc, _j) + 1
                float _nl = math.max(array.get(Lil, _j), pl)
                float _nh = math.min(array.get(Lih, _j), _bBot)
                if sr_wick_fit and _nl <= _nh
                    array.set(Lil, _j, _nl)
                    array.set(Lih, _j, _nh)
                    array.set(Lp, _j, (_nl + _nh) / 2.0)
                else if not sr_wick_fit and not _pierceOnly
                    array.set(Lp, _j, (array.get(Lp, _j) * (_c - 1) + pl) / _c)
                array.set(Lc, _j, _c)
                array.set(Lb, _j, bar_index - pvR)
        else
            array.push(Lp, pl)
            array.push(Lc, 1)
            array.push(Lt, time[pvR])
            array.push(Lh, false)
            array.push(Lb, bar_index - pvR)
            array.push(Lil, pl)
            array.push(Lih, _bBot)
    // Cap on LEVELS: evict the one that came into play longest ago.
    while array.size(Lp) > poolN
        int _old = 0
        for i2 = 1 to array.size(Lp) - 1
            if array.get(Lt, i2) < array.get(Lt, _old)
                _old := i2
        array.remove(Lp, _old)
        array.remove(Lc, _old)
        array.remove(Lt, _old)
        array.remove(Lh, _old)
        array.remove(Lb, _old)
        array.remove(Lil, _old)
        array.remove(Lih, _old)
    // SELECT the two nearest qualified levels per side. NEAREST, not most-tested —
    // ranking by touch count is the inversion this engine exists to remove. The
    // min-touch gate stays: one pivot is a swing point, not a level.
    float a1 = na
    float a2 = na
    float b1 = na
    float b2 = na
    int   a1t = 0
    int   a2t = 0
    int   b1t = 0
    int   b2t = 0
    int   a1x = 0
    int   a2x = 0
    int   b1x = 0
    int   b2x = 0
    bool  a1h = false
    bool  a2h = false
    bool  b1h = false
    bool  b2h = false
    if array.size(Lp) > 0
        for i2 = 0 to array.size(Lp) - 1
            float lvl = array.get(Lp, i2)
            int   c   = array.get(Lc, i2)
            if c >= minTouch
                if lvl > close
                    if na(a1) or lvl < a1
                        a2 := a1
                        a2t := a1t
                        a2x := a1x
                        a2h := a1h
                        a1 := lvl
                        a1t := c
                        a1x := array.get(Lt, i2)
                        a1h := array.get(Lh, i2)
                    else if na(a2) or lvl < a2
                        a2 := lvl
                        a2t := c
                        a2x := array.get(Lt, i2)
                        a2h := array.get(Lh, i2)
                else if lvl < close
                    if na(b1) or lvl > b1
                        b2 := b1
                        b2t := b1t
                        b2x := b1x
                        b2h := b1h
                        b1 := lvl
                        b1t := c
                        b1x := array.get(Lt, i2)
                        b1h := array.get(Lh, i2)
                    else if na(b2) or lvl > b2
                        b2 := lvl
                        b2t := c
                        b2x := array.get(Lt, i2)
                        b2h := array.get(Lh, i2)
    SRSig.new(a1, a1t, a1x, a1h, a2, a2t, a2x, a2h, b1, b1t, b1x, b1h, b2, b2t, b2x, b2h)

// ==========================================================================
// Z3. ZONE ENGINE — LABEL + METHODS
// ==========================================================================
// NOTE: there is no touch counter. Zones are DELETED the moment they are tested (see the
// state block below), so a "T n/max" token could never render. The old touchCount field and
// the controllingMaxTouches input were dead weight and have been removed.
f_buildLabel(string tf, bool isDemand, string pattern, int score, int nBase, int confBonus, bool isControlling, bool hasFVG) =>
    chartTfName = timeframe.ismonthly ? "Monthly" : timeframe.isweekly ? "Weekly" :
                  timeframe.isdaily   ? "Daily"   : timeframe.period
    tfName   = tf == "M" ? "Monthly" : tf == "W" ? "Weekly" : tf == "D" ? "Daily" : chartTfName
    zType    = isDemand ? "DZ" : "SZ"
    bonusTag = confBonus > 0 ? " ★" + str.tostring(confBonus) : ""
    prefix   = isControlling ? "Controlling " : ""
    fvgTag   = hasFVG ? " ⚡" : ""            // FVG-Polygraph-qualified leg-out
    baseInfo = nBase > 0 ? str.tostring(nBase) + "B" : "Pivot"
    line1    = prefix + tfName + " " + zType + fvgTag
    line2    = pattern + "  " + str.tostring(score) + "pts  " + baseInfo + bonusTag
    // 10-space indent so the text starts inside the zone body, offset from the left edge.
    "          " + line1 + "\n          " + line2

method checkMitigation(Zone z, float _close, float _low, float _high, string _mitBasis) =>
    switch _mitBasis
        "Body Close"      => z.isDemand ? _close < z.distal                      : _close > z.distal
        "Wick Close"      => z.isDemand ? _low   < z.distal                      : _high  > z.distal
        "50% Penetration" => z.isDemand ? _close < (z.proximal + z.distal) / 2.0 : _close > (z.proximal + z.distal) / 2.0
        => false

method deleteDrawings(Zone z) =>
    box.delete(z.drawing)
    if not na(z.infoLabel)
        label.delete(z.infoLabel)

// ==========================================================================
// Z4. ZONE ENGINE — UNIVERSAL DETECTION FUNCTION  (verbatim from IZE v4.2)
// ==========================================================================
f_detectZone(simple float ercM,  simple int minB,  simple int maxB, simple float bodyR,
             simple float legBodyR, simple float legBodyAvgR, simple float strongFTMul,
             simple float minW,  simple float maxW, simple float volM,
             simple bool needBOS,
             simple string proxMode, simple int ftLag, simple int ftRescue,
             simple bool ctrlAllowed, simple bool provOn, simple int nbTol,
             simple float maxBaseTRm, simple float legInWickRatio, simple int fvgBonusPts,
             simple float leginAtrP) =>
    a  = ta.atr(14)
    v  = ta.sma(volume, 20)
    tr = ta.tr
    // INVISIBLE (gap-bridged) CANDLES — ALWAYS ON. Zone marking is defined on bridged
    // price: each bar's open re-anchored at the previous close, high/low expanded to
    // cover the gap, so a small-bodied gap day classifies as the leg candle it really
    // is. This is methodology, not preference — there is deliberately NO toggle. The
    // "Draw Invisible Candles" input (Zones — Visual) controls the VIEW only, so the
    // overlay can never disagree with what the engine reads.
    inv_open  = nz(close[1], open)
    eff_open  = inv_open
    eff_close = close
    eff_high  = math.max(high, inv_open)
    eff_low   = math.min(low,  inv_open)
    eff_body  = math.abs(eff_close - eff_open)
    eff_rng   = eff_high - eff_low
    var float ath = na
    var float atl = na
    ath := na(ath) ? eff_high : math.max(ath, eff_high)
    atl := na(atl) ? eff_low  : math.min(atl, eff_low)
    ma50 = ta.sma(eff_close, 50)
    // Bars since the running extreme last ADVANCED — drives the Controlling pullback rule.
    // Because `ath` is a running max, every bar between the ATH bar and a later bar has a
    // LOWER HIGH by definition. So "N bars of lower highs since the prior ATH" is exactly
    // "the ATH bar is >= N bars older". barssince gives that in O(1) and keeps the history
    // offset shallow (we read it at [liIdx], <= ~8 bars back). Must be called every bar.
    newATHprint = not na(ath[1]) and eff_high > ath[1]
    newATLprint = not na(atl[1]) and eff_low  < atl[1]
    bsATH = ta.barssince(newATHprint)
    bsATL = ta.barssince(newATLprint)
    ph_l = ta.pivothigh(high, 10, 5)
    pl_l = ta.pivotlow(low,  10, 5)
    var float lph = na
    var float lpl = na
    if not na(ph_l)
        lph := ph_l
    if not na(pl_l)
        lpl := pl_l
    var int    sigTime      = 0
    var float  sigProx      = na
    var float  sigDist      = na
    var bool   sigIsDmd     = false
    var int    sigScore     = 0
    var string sigPattern   = ""
    var int    sigNb        = 0
    var int    sigBStart    = 1
    var int    sigBaseTime  = 0
    var bool   sigCtrl      = false
    var bool   sigFVG       = false
    var bool   sigProv      = false
    // ---- VARIABLE-LENGTH FOLLOW-THROUGH RESCUE SEARCH ----
    // `ft` is the offset of the candidate LEG-OUT bar, and therefore also the number
    // of follow-through bars available to judge it (the FT terms below measure from
    // eff_close[ft] to the current bar). We try the SHORTEST ft first and stop at the
    // first zone found, which gives exactly the intended behaviour:
    //   * a STRONG leg-out (body >= legBodyR) needs NO follow-through and is found
    //     immediately at ft = ftLag — one closed bar after it printed.
    //   * an AVERAGE leg-out (legBodyAvgR <= body < legBodyR) fails at ft = ftLag and
    //     gets another chance at ft+1, ft+2 ... where 2-3 bars of follow-through can
    //     rescue it. Because it is then the LEG-OUT and not a base candle, the base
    //     scan starts past it and the resulting zone is NARROWER.
    // Previously ft was a FIXED input, so only one offset was ever tried: a weak
    // leg-out could never be rescued, and raising the input just slid the whole
    // detection window into the past rather than requiring more follow-through.
    bool _found = false
    // ---- PROVISIONAL PASS (v3.2) ----------------------------------------------
    // ft >= 1 means the leg-out must be at least one bar back, so a leg-out on the
    // LAST bar can never be a candidate: the newest zone stays invisible until a
    // fresh bar exists. Intraday that is 75 minutes. At a session close it is until
    // the next session — and at FRIDAY's close it is the whole weekend, which is
    // exactly when the zone marking happens.
    // So AFTER the normal search fails, on the last CONFIRMED bar only, try ft=0.
    // ORDER MATTERS: last, never first. The loop takes the shortest successful ft,
    // so trying 0 first would let a brand-new preview shadow an older REAL formation
    // that ft=1 was about to find.
    // ft=0 self-limits to STRONG legs, and that is correct rather than a compromise:
    // `strongFT` and `hasFVG` both require a bar AFTER the leg-out, so they are
    // unmeasurable here — that is time, not something code can work around. A strong
    // leg needs no follow-through, which is precisely why it can be read at its close.
    bool _provTry = provOn and barstate.islast and barstate.isconfirmed
    for _i = 0 to ftRescue + (_provTry ? 1 : 0)
        if _found
            break
        int ft = _i <= ftRescue ? ftLag + _i : 0
        legBodyPct      = eff_rng[ft] > 0 ? eff_body[ft] / eff_rng[ft] : 0.0
        legBodyStrong   = legBodyPct >= legBodyR
        legBodyAverage  = legBodyPct >= legBodyAvgR and legBodyPct < legBodyR
        legOutBig       = tr[ft] > a[ft] * ercM
        closesUpper     = eff_close[ft] > eff_high[ft] - eff_rng[ft] * 0.25
        closesLower     = eff_close[ft] < eff_low[ft]  + eff_rng[ft] * 0.25
        dirBull         = eff_close[ft] > eff_open[ft]
        dirBear         = eff_close[ft] < eff_open[ft]
        strongFT_bull   = ft > 0 and (eff_close - eff_close[ft]) > a[ft] * strongFTMul
        strongFT_bear   = ft > 0 and (eff_close[ft] - eff_close) > a[ft] * strongFTMul
        // NOTE: the live leg-out gates are bullERC / bearERC below. Do not re-introduce a
        // second "bullLegOut/bearLegOut" pair here — a dead FT-less twin of those gates used
        // to sit at this spot, assigned and never read, so edits to it were silent no-ops.
        bool ftOKbull = true
        bool ftOKbear = true
        if ft > 0
            ercH = eff_high[ft]
            ercL = eff_low[ft]
            ercC = eff_close[ft]
            progBull = eff_close > ercC
            progBear = eff_close < ercC
            bool noRevBull = true
            bool noRevBear = true
            for j = ft - 1 to 0
                if eff_close[j] < ercL
                    noRevBull := false
                if eff_close[j] > ercH
                    noRevBear := false
            ftOKbull := progBull and noRevBull
            ftOKbear := progBear and noRevBear
        bullERC = (legOutBig and dirBull and closesUpper and legBodyStrong) or
                  (legOutBig and dirBull and closesUpper and legBodyAverage and strongFT_bull and ftOKbull)
        bearERC = (legOutBig and dirBear and closesLower and legBodyStrong) or
                  (legOutBig and dirBear and closesLower and legBodyAverage and strongFT_bear and ftOKbear)
        // ===== DEMAND =====
        if bullERC
            volOK = volM > 0.0 ? volume[ft] > v[ft] * volM : true
            bosOK = needBOS ? (not na(lph[ft]) and eff_close[ft] > lph[ft]) : true
            if volOK and bosOK
                float zT = na
                float zTwk = na                 // #34: base's WICK high, for the narrow-zone wick-to-wick rescue
                int   nBC = 0
                int   bS  = ft + 1
                int   nbStreak = 0
                for i = ft + 1 to ft + maxB
                    cRange = eff_rng[i]
                    cBody  = eff_body[i]
                    smallBody  = cRange > 0 and (cBody / cRange) <= bodyR
                    smallRange = tr[i] < a[i] * base_rng_atr
                    isBase = (smallBody or smallRange) and tr[i] < a[i] * maxBaseTRm
                    if isBase
                        nbStreak := 0
                        nBC := nBC + 1
                        bS  := i
                        pVal = proxMode == "Body Extreme" ? math.max(eff_close[i], eff_open[i]) : eff_high[i]
                        zT := na(zT) ? pVal : math.max(zT, pVal)
                        zTwk := na(zTwk) ? eff_high[i] : math.max(zTwk, eff_high[i])
                    else
                        nbStreak := nbStreak + 1
                        if nbStreak > nbTol
                            break
                if nBC >= minB and nBC <= maxB and not na(zT)
                    int liIdx = bS + 1
                    liRng = eff_rng[liIdx]
                    liBody = eff_body[liIdx]
                    liUpWick   = eff_high[liIdx] - math.max(eff_close[liIdx], eff_open[liIdx])
                    liLowWick  = math.min(eff_close[liIdx], eff_open[liIdx]) - eff_low[liIdx]
                    liMaxWick  = math.max(liUpWick, liLowWick)
                    bool legInWickOK = liBody > 0 and liMaxWick <= liBody * legInWickRatio
                    bool legInValid = liRng > 0 and (liBody / liRng) >= legBodyAvgR and tr[liIdx] > a[liIdx] * leginAtrP and legInWickOK
                    bool legInBullish = eff_close[liIdx] > eff_open[liIdx]
                    if legInValid
                        string pat = legInBullish ? "RBR" : "DBR"
                        float zB = na
                        int   distFrom = ft
                        int   distTo   = pat == "DBR" ? liIdx : bS
                        for k = distFrom to distTo
                            lowSide = eff_low[k]     // ALL distals are WICK distals (house rule 17-Jul); scan range is pattern-aware via distTo
                            zB := na(zB) ? lowSide : math.min(zB, lowSide)
                        if not na(zB)
                            // #34 NARROW-ZONE WICK-TO-WICK: the distal is already a wick
                            // (eff_low). If the body-based proximal makes the zone thinner
                            // than the band FLOOR, widen the proximal out to the base's wick
                            // high — a thin-bodied base's true zone runs to its wicks, so
                            // this rescues a precise zone that would otherwise be rejected.
                            if narrowWickToWick and not na(zTwk) and (zT - zB) < a[ft] * minW
                                zT := math.max(zT, zTwk)
                            w = zT - zB
                            if w >= a[ft] * minW and w <= a[ft] * maxW
                                bodyR_legOut = eff_body[ft] / math.max(eff_rng[ft], 0.001)
                                volR  = volume[ft] / math.max(v[ft], 1.0)
                                eP    = int(math.min(bodyR_legOut * 40.0, 40.0))
                                // Volume is a BONUS, floored at 0. It used to be unclamped below
                                // zero, so a below-average-volume leg-out silently subtracted up to
                                // -12 from a zone's structural merit. `volMult` is the intended
                                // volume GATE; scoring shouldn't double as a second, hidden one.
                                vP    = int(math.min(math.max((volR - 1.0) * 12.0, 0.0), 30.0))
                                bP    = nBC == 1 ? 12 : nBC == 2 ? 25 : nBC == 3 ? 25 : nBC == 4 ? 20 : nBC == 5 ? 10 : 5
                                raw   = math.min(eP + vP + bP, 95)
                                gapSize = open[ft] - close[ft + 1]          // RAW prices: the gap-bridge erases the gap (eff_open[ft] IS close[ft+1] -> the old expression was identically 0, gapBonus dead)
                                hasGap  = gapSize > a[ft] * 0.3
                                gapPts  = hasGap ? gapBonus : 0
                                hasFVG  = ft > 0 and low[ft - 1] > high[ft + 1]      // RAW: bridged lows/highs close the very imbalance being tested
                                fvgPts  = hasFVG ? fvgBonusPts : 0
                                int pivBroken = 0
                                for kk = ft + 1 to ft + 30
                                    pk = ph_l[kk]
                                    if not na(pk) and pk > eff_close[bS] and pk < eff_close[ft]
                                        pivBroken := pivBroken + 1
                                multiPivPts = math.min(pivBroken * 5, 15)
                                patPts = pat == "DBR" ? 10 : 0
                                sc = math.min(raw + gapPts + fvgPts + multiPivPts + patPts, 100)
                                // ---- Controlling criterion #1: LEADS TO a new ATH ----
                                // House rule (Jay's trainer): a DZ is Controlling only if it LEADS
                                // TO a new ATH — it cannot be a CONTINUATION of one. Price must have
                                // come off the prior high (lower highs printed) and the base must
                                // form below it; the leg-out then breaks it. A base built while
                                // price is already ratcheting the ATH up is disqualified.
                                float athPrior = ath[liIdx]                       // ATH before this formation began
                                // (a) NON-CONTINUATION: the ATH must not have advanced during the base.
                                bool baseNoNewATH = not na(athPrior) and ath[ft + 1] <= athPrior
                                // (b) PULLBACK: >= ctrlMinLowerHighs bars printed a lower high since the prior ATH.
                                bool pulledBack   = not na(bsATH[liIdx]) and bsATH[liIdx] >= ctrlMinLowerHighs
                                // (c) LEADS TO the new ATH: the leg-out closes through the prior high.
                                bool leadsToATH   = not na(athPrior) and eff_close[ft] > athPrior
                                bool isNewATH     = leadsToATH and baseNoNewATH and pulledBack
                                bool wasBelowMA = true
                                for kk2 = ft + 1 to ft + 20
                                    if not na(ma50[kk2]) and eff_close[kk2] > ma50[kk2]
                                        wasBelowMA := false
                                        break
                                bool isTrendShiftUp = wasBelowMA and not na(ma50[ft]) and eff_close[ft] > ma50[ft]
                                bool isCtrl = ctrlAllowed and (isNewATH or isTrendShiftUp)
                                sigTime     := time[ft]
                                sigProx     := zT
                                sigDist     := zB
                                sigIsDmd    := true
                                sigScore    := sc
                                sigPattern  := pat
                                sigNb       := nBC
                                sigBStart   := bS
                                sigBaseTime := time[bS]
                                sigCtrl     := isCtrl
                                sigFVG      := hasFVG
                                sigProv     := ft == 0
                                _found      := true
        // ===== SUPPLY =====
        if bearERC
            volOK2 = volM > 0.0 ? volume[ft] > v[ft] * volM : true
            bosOK2 = needBOS ? (not na(lpl[ft]) and eff_close[ft] < lpl[ft]) : true
            if volOK2 and bosOK2
                float zB2 = na
                float zB2wk = na                // #34: base's WICK low, for the narrow-zone wick-to-wick rescue
                int   nBC2 = 0
                int   bS2  = ft + 1
                int   nbStreak2 = 0
                for i = ft + 1 to ft + maxB
                    cR2 = eff_rng[i]
                    cB2 = eff_body[i]
                    smallBody2  = cR2 > 0 and (cB2 / cR2) <= bodyR
                    smallRange2 = tr[i] < a[i] * base_rng_atr
                    isBase2 = (smallBody2 or smallRange2) and tr[i] < a[i] * maxBaseTRm
                    if isBase2
                        nbStreak2 := 0
                        nBC2 := nBC2 + 1
                        bS2  := i
                        pVal2 = proxMode == "Body Extreme" ? math.min(eff_close[i], eff_open[i]) : eff_low[i]
                        zB2 := na(zB2) ? pVal2 : math.min(zB2, pVal2)
                        zB2wk := na(zB2wk) ? eff_low[i] : math.min(zB2wk, eff_low[i])
                    else
                        nbStreak2 := nbStreak2 + 1
                        if nbStreak2 > nbTol
                            break
                if nBC2 >= minB and nBC2 <= maxB and not na(zB2)
                    int liIdx2 = bS2 + 1
                    liRng2 = eff_rng[liIdx2]
                    liBody2 = eff_body[liIdx2]
                    liUpWick2  = eff_high[liIdx2] - math.max(eff_close[liIdx2], eff_open[liIdx2])
                    liLowWick2 = math.min(eff_close[liIdx2], eff_open[liIdx2]) - eff_low[liIdx2]
                    liMaxWick2 = math.max(liUpWick2, liLowWick2)
                    bool legInWickOK2 = liBody2 > 0 and liMaxWick2 <= liBody2 * legInWickRatio
                    bool legInValid2 = liRng2 > 0 and (liBody2 / liRng2) >= legBodyAvgR and tr[liIdx2] > a[liIdx2] * leginAtrP and legInWickOK2
                    bool legInBullish2 = eff_close[liIdx2] > eff_open[liIdx2]
                    if legInValid2
                        string pat2 = legInBullish2 ? "RBD" : "DBD"
                        float zT2 = na
                        int   distFrom2 = ft
                        int   distTo2   = pat2 == "RBD" ? liIdx2 : bS2
                        for k = distFrom2 to distTo2
                            highSide = eff_high[k]   // ALL distals are WICK distals — see the demand mirror
                            zT2 := na(zT2) ? highSide : math.max(zT2, highSide)
                        if not na(zT2)
                            // #34 NARROW-ZONE WICK-TO-WICK (supply mirror): widen the
                            // proximal DOWN to the base's wick low when the body zone is
                            // thinner than the band floor. Distal (zT2) is already a wick.
                            if narrowWickToWick and not na(zB2wk) and (zT2 - zB2) < a[ft] * minW
                                zB2 := math.min(zB2, zB2wk)
                            w2 = zT2 - zB2
                            if w2 >= a[ft] * minW and w2 <= a[ft] * maxW
                                bodyR_legOut2 = eff_body[ft] / math.max(eff_rng[ft], 0.001)
                                volR2  = volume[ft] / math.max(v[ft], 1.0)
                                eP2    = int(math.min(bodyR_legOut2 * 40.0, 40.0))
                                vP2    = int(math.min(math.max((volR2 - 1.0) * 12.0, 0.0), 30.0))   // floored at 0 — see the demand mirror
                                bP2    = nBC2 == 1 ? 12 : nBC2 == 2 ? 25 : nBC2 == 3 ? 25 : nBC2 == 4 ? 20 : nBC2 == 5 ? 10 : 5
                                raw2   = math.min(eP2 + vP2 + bP2, 95)
                                gapSize2 = close[ft + 1] - open[ft]         // RAW prices - see the demand mirror
                                hasGap2  = gapSize2 > a[ft] * 0.3
                                gapPts2  = hasGap2 ? gapBonus : 0
                                hasFVG2  = ft > 0 and high[ft - 1] < low[ft + 1]     // RAW - see the demand mirror
                                fvgPts2  = hasFVG2 ? fvgBonusPts : 0
                                int pivBroken2 = 0
                                for kk = ft + 1 to ft + 30
                                    pk = pl_l[kk]
                                    if not na(pk) and pk < eff_close[bS2] and pk > eff_close[ft]
                                        pivBroken2 := pivBroken2 + 1
                                multiPivPts2 = math.min(pivBroken2 * 5, 15)
                                patPts2 = pat2 == "RBD" ? 10 : 0
                                sc2 = math.min(raw2 + gapPts2 + fvgPts2 + multiPivPts2 + patPts2, 100)
                                // ---- Controlling criterion #1 (mirror): LEADS TO a new ATL ----
                                // An SZ is Controlling only if it LEADS TO a new ATL, never if it
                                // continues one: price must have bounced off the prior low (higher
                                // lows printed), the base must form above it, and the leg-out breaks it.
                                float atlPrior = atl[liIdx2]                      // ATL before this formation began
                                bool baseNoNewATL = not na(atlPrior) and atl[ft + 1] >= atlPrior
                                bool pushedUp     = not na(bsATL[liIdx2]) and bsATL[liIdx2] >= ctrlMinLowerHighs
                                bool leadsToATL   = not na(atlPrior) and eff_close[ft] < atlPrior
                                bool isNewATL     = leadsToATL and baseNoNewATL and pushedUp
                                bool wasAboveMA = true
                                for kk2 = ft + 1 to ft + 20
                                    if not na(ma50[kk2]) and eff_close[kk2] < ma50[kk2]
                                        wasAboveMA := false
                                        break
                                bool isTrendShiftDown = wasAboveMA and not na(ma50[ft]) and eff_close[ft] < ma50[ft]
                                bool isCtrl2 = ctrlAllowed and (isNewATL or isTrendShiftDown)
                                sigTime     := time[ft]
                                sigProx     := zB2
                                sigDist     := zT2
                                sigIsDmd    := false
                                sigScore    := sc2
                                sigPattern  := pat2
                                sigNb       := nBC2
                                sigBStart   := bS2
                                sigBaseTime := time[bS2]
                                sigCtrl     := isCtrl2
                                sigFVG      := hasFVG2
                                sigProv     := ft == 0
                                _found      := true
    ZoneSig.new(sigTime, sigProx, sigDist, sigIsDmd, sigScore, sigPattern, sigNb, sigBStart, sigBaseTime, sigCtrl, sigFVG, sigProv)

// ==========================================================================
// Z5. ZONE ENGINE — CONFLUENCE BONUS + CREATION
// ==========================================================================
f_confluenceBoost(float newProx, float newDist, bool newIsDmd, string newTf) =>
    int bonus = 0
    nLo = math.min(newProx, newDist)
    nHi = math.max(newProx, newDist)
    sz = array.size(activeZones)
    if sz > 0
        for i = 0 to sz - 1
            zz = array.get(activeZones, i)
            zLo = math.min(zz.proximal, zz.distal)
            zHi = math.max(zz.proximal, zz.distal)
            overlap = nLo <= zHi and nHi >= zLo
            sameDir = zz.isDemand == newIsDmd
            if overlap and sameDir
                // Direction-aware: the big bonus is for a HIGHER-TF zone overlapping
                // this one. It used to fire for ANY different TF — a Monthly zone was
                // collecting the '+15 HTF overlap' from a 75-minute zone.
                int _rN = newTf == "M" ? 4 : newTf == "W" ? 3 : newTf == "D" ? 2 : 1
                int _rZ = zz.tf == "M" ? 4 : zz.tf == "W" ? 3 : zz.tf == "D" ? 2 : 1
                bonus := bonus + (_rZ > _rN ? htfBoost : sameTfBoost)
    if not na(dailyEMA20) and not na(chart_atr)
        emaInZone = dailyEMA20 >= nLo and dailyEMA20 <= nHi
        edgeDist  = emaInZone ? 0.0 : math.min(math.abs(dailyEMA20 - nLo), math.abs(dailyEMA20 - nHi))
        // The zone's OWN TF ATR — the same v3.2 fix the tested-travel rule got.
        // With the chart ATR, "near the EMA20" for a Monthly zone on a 75m chart
        // meant "touching it": the same zone scored ~10 pts differently per chart TF.
        float _cbAtr = newTf == "M" ? atrM_tf : newTf == "W" ? atrW_tf : newTf == "D" ? atrD_tf : chart_atr
        nearby    = emaInZone or edgeDist <= nz(_cbAtr, chart_atr) * emaProxThreshATR
        // EMA20 confluence = PROXIMITY only. This used to also grant the bonus to any
        // demand zone sitting entirely BELOW the EMA20 (mirror for supply above) — which
        // is every demand zone in an uptrend, regardless of distance. That made ★ a near
        // constant (~everything read ★10) and stripped it of information. Distance to the
        // daily EMA20 is the actual confluence; the half-plane is not.
        if nearby
            bonus := bonus + emaProxBoost
        else
            // #4 (19-Jul): the MIRROR — an ORPHANED zone loses quality. EMA20 on the
            // WRONG side and far away (below-and-away from a DZ / above-and-away from
            // an SZ) means price returns to this zone only when badly extended from
            // value, which weakens the expected reaction.
            bool _farDZ = newIsDmd and dailyEMA20 < nLo and (nLo - dailyEMA20) > nz(_cbAtr, chart_atr) * emaFarAtr
            bool _farSZ = (not newIsDmd) and dailyEMA20 > nHi and (dailyEMA20 - nHi) > nz(_cbAtr, chart_atr) * emaFarAtr
            if _farDZ or _farSZ
                bonus := bonus - emaFarMalus
    math.min(bonus, maxConfBoost)

f_createZone(ZoneSig sig, string tfTag, bool isNative) =>
    bool emaOK = true
    bool rsOK  = true
    if isNative
        emaOK := useEMA ? (sig.isDemand ? close > dailyEMA20 : close < dailyEMA20) : true
        rsOK  := useRS  ? (sig.isDemand ? rsSlope > 0        : rsSlope < 0)        : true
    // Structural dedup — SAME TIMEFRAME ONLY. A pivot zone (PvH/PvL) is skipped only
    // if it overlaps an existing same-direction zone OF THE SAME TF (e.g. a native
    // structural duplicating a native pattern zone at the same level). Cross-TF
    // overlaps are KEPT — a Monthly zone must coexist with a Weekly/Daily zone at the
    // same price (that is confluence, and the HTF zone must survive). This is the fix
    // for HTF zones (esp. Monthly) failing to propagate: with zones now persisting,
    // an any-TF dedup was dropping almost every new HTF zone against some LTF zone.
    bool structDup = false
    if (sig.pattern == "PvH" or sig.pattern == "PvL") and not na(sig.proximal) and not na(sig.distal)
        int _sz = array.size(activeZones)
        if _sz > 0
            for _j = 0 to _sz - 1
                _zo = array.get(activeZones, _j)
                if _zo.isDemand == sig.isDemand and _zo.tf == tfTag
                    float _zHi = math.max(_zo.proximal, _zo.distal)
                    float _zLo = math.min(_zo.proximal, _zo.distal)
                    float _nHi = math.max(sig.proximal, sig.distal)
                    float _nLo = math.min(sig.proximal, sig.distal)
                    if _nHi >= _zLo and _nLo <= _zHi
                        structDup := true
                        break
    // #7 (Jay, 19-Jul): SAME-BASE PATTERN dedup. Two pattern zones cut from the SAME
    // base (one counting 3 base candles, one counting 2) are one formation read twice —
    // only one is correct. Proxy: a new pattern zone whose price range overlaps an
    // existing same-TF, same-direction PATTERN zone by >= 50% of the SMALLER zone's
    // width is the same formation → skip it (first formation wins, matching the
    // pattern-created-first doctrine). Genuinely adjacent / lightly-overlapping zones
    // (< 50%) are kept — overlap itself is not the crime, shared base candles are.
    // Tested (grey) zones are consumed and do not block a fresh read.
    bool patDup = false
    if dedupSameBase and sig.nBase > 0 and sig.pattern != "PvH" and sig.pattern != "PvL" and not na(sig.proximal) and not na(sig.distal)
        int _szP = array.size(activeZones)
        if _szP > 0
            for _jp = 0 to _szP - 1
                _zp = array.get(activeZones, _jp)
                if _zp.isDemand == sig.isDemand and _zp.tf == tfTag and _zp.nBase > 0 and not _zp.tested
                    float _pHi = math.max(_zp.proximal, _zp.distal)
                    float _pLo = math.min(_zp.proximal, _zp.distal)
                    float _qHi = math.max(sig.proximal, sig.distal)
                    float _qLo = math.min(sig.proximal, sig.distal)
                    float _ovl = math.min(_pHi, _qHi) - math.max(_pLo, _qLo)
                    float _minW2 = math.min(_pHi - _pLo, _qHi - _qLo)
                    if _ovl > 0 and _minW2 > 0 and _ovl / _minW2 >= 0.5
                        patDup := true
                        break
    if emaOK and rsOK and not na(sig.proximal) and not na(sig.distal) and not structDup and not patDup
        cBonus     = f_confluenceBoost(sig.proximal, sig.distal, sig.isDemand, tfTag)
        finalScore = math.min(sig.rawScore + cBonus, 100)
        bool breaksOpposing = false
        sz_chk = array.size(activeZones)
        if sz_chk > 0
            for jj = 0 to sz_chk - 1
                zo = array.get(activeZones, jj)
                if zo.isControlling and zo.isDemand != sig.isDemand
                    if sig.isDemand
                        if sig.proximal > zo.distal
                            breaksOpposing := true
                            break
                    else
                        if sig.proximal < zo.distal
                            breaksOpposing := true
                            break
        // The CHART's timeframe decides whether a native zone may be promoted — the
        // same rule the detection side (ctrlAllowNative) uses. The old ternary keyed
        // on tfTag: for a native zone that selected ctrlAllowChart, which means "the
        // Min-TF dropdown is set to Chart", NOT "this chart's TF" — so at the DEFAULT
        // setting (Daily) the breaksOpposing promotion could never fire. The D/W/M
        // branches were dead anyway: isNative is true iff tfTag == "C".
        bool ctrlAllowedHere = markControlling and not timeframe.isintraday and (timeframe.ismonthly ? ctrlAllowMonthly : timeframe.isweekly ? ctrlAllowWeekly : ctrlAllowDaily)
        // #3 CONTROLLING LOCK: an HTF zone's identity must come ONLY from its own
        // timeframe (computed inside f_detectZone via request.security). The chart-
        // level breaksOpposing promotion is a lower-TF alteration, so it is applied
        // to NATIVE (chart-TF) zones only — a Monthly DZ stays "Monthly DZ" on a 75m
        // chart, it can never become "Controlling Monthly DZ" from lower-TF context.
        bool finalCtrl = sig.isControlling or (isNative and breaksOpposing and ctrlAllowedHere)
        // #2 EXCLUSIVE CONTROLLING: only ONE controlling zone per direction — the one
        // NEAREST the ATH (demand) / ATL (supply). `ath` lives inside f_detectZone and is
        // not in scope here, so we use the exact local proxy: for demand the zone nearest
        // the ATH is simply the HIGHEST one (mirror for supply). A new controlling zone
        // only supersedes the incumbent if it is actually nearer; otherwise the incumbent
        // keeps the title and the new zone stays ordinary. (Previously this demoted
        // unconditionally — last-one-wins — which contradicted the stated rule.)
        if finalCtrl
            int _cz = array.size(activeZones)
            // Pass 1 — does the new zone genuinely supersede every same-direction incumbent?
            bool _supersedes = true
            if _cz > 0
                for _k = 0 to _cz - 1
                    _zc = array.get(activeZones, _k)
                    if _zc.isControlling and _zc.isDemand == sig.isDemand
                        bool _newIsNearer = sig.isDemand ? (sig.proximal > _zc.proximal) : (sig.proximal < _zc.proximal)
                        if not _newIsNearer
                            _supersedes := false
            finalCtrl := _supersedes
            // Pass 2 — only demote once we know the new zone wins.
            if _supersedes and _cz > 0
                for _k = 0 to _cz - 1
                    _zc = array.get(activeZones, _k)
                    if _zc.isControlling and _zc.isDemand == sig.isDemand
                        _zc.isControlling := false
                        box.set_border_width(_zc.drawing, 1)
                        box.set_text(_zc.drawing, (showZonesIZE and d_zones and showLabels) ? f_buildLabel(_zc.tf, _zc.isDemand, _zc.pattern, _zc.strength, _zc.nBase, _zc.confBonus, false, _zc.hasFVG) : "")
        basecol = sig.isDemand
             ? (sig.pattern == "DBR" ? color.green : sig.pattern == "RBR" ? color.lime   : color.teal)
             : (sig.pattern == "RBD" ? color.red   : sig.pattern == "DBD" ? color.orange : color.blue)
        // #3 THIN BORDERS + HIGH TRANSPARENCY: backgrounds are nearly clear so candles
        // read straight through; borders are THIN (1px normal, 2px controlling).
        // Option C: an FVG-Polygraph-qualified zone (leg-out left an FVG) gets a BRIGHTER
        // border (lower transparency) + a ⚡ in the label, without being a hard filter.
        // #37 fill transparency is now an input (zoneFillTransp) with the per-TF spread
        // preserved: chart-native most transparent, Monthly most opaque. Clamped <= 98.
        bgAlpha = math.min(zoneFillTransp + (tfTag == "C" ? 3 : tfTag == "D" ? 2 : tfTag == "W" ? 1 : 0), 98)
        bdAlpha = tfTag == "C" ? 25 : tfTag == "D" ? 15 : tfTag == "W" ? 10 : 5
        if sig.hasFVG
            bdAlpha := math.max(bdAlpha - 10, 0)
        bwidth  = finalCtrl ? 2 : 1
        if finalCtrl
            // Controlling zones read 4 steps MORE opaque than their base (lower = more
            // opaque). Floor 60 (= input minval) not 90, so this never inverts against a
            // low zoneFillTransp and makes a controlling fill LESS visible. (#37)
            bgAlpha := math.max(bgAlpha - 4, 60)
        bgC = color.new(basecol, bgAlpha)
        bdC = color.new(basecol, bdAlpha)
        topVal = sig.isDemand ? sig.proximal : sig.distal
        botVal = sig.isDemand ? sig.distal   : sig.proximal
        lblTxt = f_buildLabel(tfTag, sig.isDemand, sig.pattern, finalScore, sig.nBase, cBonus, finalCtrl, sig.hasFVG)
        // Boxes are ALWAYS created (state-management operates on them); showZonesIZE
        // off just renders them fully transparent + blanks the text.
        if not (showZonesIZE and d_zones)
            bgC := color.new(basecol, 100)
            bdC := color.new(basecol, 100)
        // #1/#5/#6 Label = the zone's own BOX TEXT: left-aligned, vertically CENTERED,
        // SMALL font, 10-space indent (from f_buildLabel) — so it sits INSIDE the zone
        // at the left edge, not offset out by a separate label's pointer. FVG boxes use
        // the identical convention; pivot lines mirror it with a small left label.
        string _lblShown = (showZonesIZE and d_zones and showLabels) ? lblTxt : ""
        // #3/#4 per-TF label font colour: Monthly amber · Weekly white · Daily LIGHT BLUE ·
        // 125m cyan · 75m green. Native "C" zones colour by the CHART timeframe.
        color _txtC = tfTag == "M" ? color.new(#FFB300, 0) : tfTag == "W" ? color.new(color.white, 0) : tfTag == "D" ? color.new(#4FC3F7, 0) : timeframe.ismonthly ? color.new(#FFB300, 0) : timeframe.isweekly ? color.new(color.white, 0) : timeframe.isdaily ? color.new(#4FC3F7, 0) : chartSec >= 7500 ? color.new(color.aqua, 0) : color.new(color.lime, 0)
        // STRUCTURAL zones draw with a DASHED border, pattern zones SOLID. A pivot zone
        // has no leg-in / base / leg-out — it is a different, weaker construct — and must
        // never read as a validated leg-base-leg formation at a glance. (The "Pivot" token
        // in the label says the same thing in words.)
        bool _isStruct = sig.pattern == "PvL" or sig.pattern == "PvH"
        _bstyle = _isStruct ? line.style_dashed : line.style_solid
        box bx = na
        if isNative
            leftBar = bar_index - sig.bStart
            bx  := box.new(leftBar, topVal, bar_index, botVal, border_color=bdC, bgcolor=bgC, border_width=bwidth, border_style=_bstyle, extend=extend.right, xloc=xloc.bar_index, text=_lblShown, text_color=_txtC, text_size=size.small, text_halign=text.align_left, text_valign=text.align_center)
        else
            bx  := box.new(sig.baseStartTime, topVal, time, botVal, border_color=bdC, bgcolor=bgC, border_width=bwidth, border_style=_bstyle, extend=extend.right, xloc=xloc.bar_time, text=_lblShown, text_color=_txtC, text_size=size.small, text_halign=text.align_left, text_valign=text.align_center)
        z = Zone.new(sig.proximal, sig.distal, bar_index, sig.baseStartTime, sig.isDemand, finalScore, cBonus, sig.nBase, sig.pattern, tfTag, finalCtrl, bx, na, false, false, na, na, false, sig.hasFVG, false)
        array.push(activeZones, z)

// ==========================================================================
// Z5b. STRUCTURAL (PIVOT-BASED) ZONE DETECTION — as a ZoneSig function so it can
// run natively AND via request.security on D/W/M (mirrors f_detectZone). This is
// what lets HTF structural pivot zones (e.g. a Monthly pivot demand) propagate DOWN
// to the trading timeframes, instead of being native-chart-TF only. Returns the
// most recent structural zone (pivot high → supply, pivot low → demand). Structural
// zones are never controlling and never carry an FVG.
// ==========================================================================
// WIDTH BAND: structural zones now honour the SAME per-TF × ATR14 band as pattern zones
// (they previously bypassed it entirely — the only size gate was minMove, so a pivot could
// emit a zone the pattern engine would have thrown out). structMinWMult scales the band's
// FLOOR down for structural zones, because a pivot zone's width is body-to-low of a single
// candle and is legitimately narrower than a leg-base-leg formation. If the structL counter
// collapses after this change, lower structMinWMult — do NOT remove the band.
f_structZone(simple int pvLeft, simple int pvRight, simple int padBars, simple float topThr, simple float deepThr, simple float minMove, simple float minW, simple float maxW, simple float minWMult) =>
    a = ta.atr(14)
    // INVISIBLE CANDLES (gap-bridged OHLC) — derivation IDENTICAL to f_detectZone, so both
    // detectors read the SAME price structure. This function previously used RAW OHLC
    // throughout and never even received the flag, so every structural PvL/PvH zone was
    // built on un-bridged prices while pattern zones were bridged — the two engines
    // silently disagreed about where price had been, and structural zones ignored the
    // "Use Invisible Candles" setting entirely.
    // The pivot IS the zone here (unlike f_detectZone, where pivots only confirm BOS and
    // score), so the pivots themselves must be found on the bridged series too.
    inv_open  = nz(close[1], open)
    eff_open  = inv_open
    eff_close = close
    eff_high  = math.max(high, inv_open)
    eff_low   = math.min(low,  inv_open)
    // ta.* called unconditionally every bar (Pine consistency rule).
    float ph = ta.pivothigh(eff_high, pvLeft, pvRight)
    float pl = ta.pivotlow(eff_low,  pvLeft, pvRight)
    float lowestSinceH  = ta.lowest(eff_low,  pvRight + 1)
    float highestSinceL = ta.highest(eff_high, pvRight + 1)
    var int    sT      = 0
    var float  sProx   = na
    var float  sDist   = na
    var bool   sDmd    = false
    var int    sScore  = 0
    var string sPat    = ""
    var int    sBStart = 1
    var int    sBaseT  = 0
    // ----- Pivot HIGH → structural SUPPLY -----
    if not na(ph)
        int   pBarH = pvRight
        float sTop  = eff_high[pBarH]
        float sBot  = math.min(eff_close[pBarH], eff_open[pBarH])
        float proxThrH = nz(a[pBarH], a) * topThr
        float deepThrH = nz(a[pBarH], a) * deepThr
        for k = math.max(pBarH - padBars, 0) to pBarH + padBars
            bodyHiK = math.max(eff_close[k], eff_open[k])
            bodyLoK = math.min(eff_close[k], eff_open[k])
            if bodyHiK >= sTop - proxThrH and bodyLoK >= sTop - deepThrH and bodyLoK < sBot
                sBot := bodyLoK
        float wH = sTop - sBot
        if not na(a) and (sTop - lowestSinceH) > a * minMove and wH >= a * minW * minWMult and wH <= a * maxW
            sT      := time
            sProx   := sBot
            sDist   := sTop
            sDmd    := false
            // A structural zone is a WEAKER construct than a validated leg-base-leg
            // formation — it has no leg-in, no base and no leg-out. It used to score
            // 60..100, i.e. a flat 60 floor on a different scale, so every PvL/PvH read
            // 86-93pts and out-ranked real pattern zones. Scored 40..75 it can never
            // out-rank a high-quality RBR/DBR (95-100), which is the correct ordering.
            sScore  := math.min(40 + int((sTop - lowestSinceH) / a * 5.0), 75)
            sPat    := "PvH"
            sBStart := pBarH + padBars
            sBaseT  := time[math.min(pBarH + padBars, bar_index)]
    // ----- Pivot LOW → structural DEMAND -----
    if not na(pl)
        int   pBarL = pvRight
        float dBot  = eff_low[pBarL]
        float dTop  = math.max(eff_close[pBarL], eff_open[pBarL])
        float proxThrL = nz(a[pBarL], a) * topThr
        float deepThrL = nz(a[pBarL], a) * deepThr
        for k = math.max(pBarL - padBars, 0) to pBarL + padBars
            bodyHiK = math.max(eff_close[k], eff_open[k])
            bodyLoK = math.min(eff_close[k], eff_open[k])
            if bodyLoK <= dBot + proxThrL and bodyHiK <= dBot + deepThrL and bodyHiK > dTop
                dTop := bodyHiK
        float wL = dTop - dBot
        if not na(a) and (highestSinceL - dBot) > a * minMove and wL >= a * minW * minWMult and wL <= a * maxW
            sT      := time
            sProx   := dTop
            sDist   := dBot
            sDmd    := true
            sScore  := math.min(40 + int((highestSinceL - dBot) / a * 5.0), 75)   // 40..75 — see the PvH mirror
            sPat    := "PvL"
            sBStart := pBarL + padBars
            sBaseT  := time[math.min(pBarL + padBars, bar_index)]
    ZoneSig.new(sT, sProx, sDist, sDmd, sScore, sPat, 0, sBStart, sBaseT, false, false, false)

// ==========================================================================
// Z6. ZONE ENGINE — REQUEST (native + HTF), DISPATCH, STRUCTURAL, STATE
// ==========================================================================
// #5 CONTROLLING CONSISTENCY: "Controlling" is assessed ONLY on a zone's own
// timeframe — i.e. when the zone is the NATIVE (chart-TF) zone. So the native call
// uses the eligibility of the CHART's actual timeframe, and the HTF (D/W/M) security
// calls pass `false` — a Monthly zone shown on a Weekly/Daily/75m chart is plain
// "Monthly DZ", never "Controlling Monthly DZ". View the monthly chart to see it
// assessed as controlling. This makes the label TF-consistent across views.
// HOUSE RULE (Jay, 19-Jul): Controlling is an M/W/D concept — a 75/125m base is never
// the dominant structural zone. Hard-gated: native zones on an INTRADAY chart can never
// be Controlling, whatever controllingMinTf says. HTF (D/W/M) zones shown on an intraday
// chart CAN be Controlling — they carry their own timeframe.
bool ctrlAllowNative = markControlling and not timeframe.isintraday and (timeframe.ismonthly ? ctrlAllowMonthly : timeframe.isweekly ? ctrlAllowWeekly : ctrlAllowDaily)
// Native chart-TF zone width band = the pair matching the chart timeframe.
float nativeMinW = timeframe.ismonthly ? minZW_M : timeframe.isweekly ? minZW_W : timeframe.isdaily ? minZW_D : chartSec >= 7500 ? minZW_125 : minZW_75
float nativeMaxW = timeframe.ismonthly ? maxZW_M : timeframe.isweekly ? maxZW_W : timeframe.isdaily ? maxZW_D : chartSec >= 7500 ? maxZW_125 : maxZW_75
nativeSig  = f_detectZone(ercMult, minBase, maxBase, bodyRatio, legBodyRatio, legBodyAvg, strongFTMult, nativeMinW, nativeMaxW, volMult, requireBOS, proxLineMode, ftLagBars, ftMaxRescue, ctrlAllowNative, prov_zone, baseStreak, maxBaseTR, legInMaxWickR, fvgBonus, (timeframe.isintraday or timeframe.isdaily ? legin_ltf : legin_htf))
dailySig   = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_detectZone(ercMult, minBase, maxBase, bodyRatio, legBodyRatio, legBodyAvg, strongFTMult, minZW_D, maxZW_D, volMult, requireBOS, proxLineMode, ftLagBars, ftMaxRescue, ctrlAllowDaily, false, baseStreak, maxBaseTR, legInMaxWickR, fvgBonus, legin_ltf), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
weeklySig  = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "W", f_detectZone(ercMult, minBase, maxBase, bodyRatio, legBodyRatio, legBodyAvg, strongFTMult, minZW_W, maxZW_W, volMult, requireBOS, proxLineMode, ftLagBars, ftMaxRescue, ctrlAllowWeekly, false, baseStreak, maxBaseTR, legInMaxWickR, fvgBonus, legin_htf), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
monthlySig = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "M", f_detectZone(ercMult, minBase, maxBase, bodyRatio, legBodyRatio, legBodyAvg, strongFTMult, minZW_M, maxZW_M, volMult, requireBOS, proxLineMode, ftLagBars, ftMaxRescue, ctrlAllowMonthly, false, baseStreak, maxBaseTR, legInMaxWickR, fvgBonus, legin_htf), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)

var int lastNativeTime  = 0
var int lastDailyTime   = 0
var int lastWeeklyTime  = 0
var int lastMonthlyTime = 0
// Diagnostics: how many native chart-TF zones were detected / passed the FVG gate / created.
var int _dbgNatDetected = 0
var int _dbgNatFvgPass  = 0
var int _dbgNatCreated  = 0
// Per-TF PATTERN funnel (#36/#40 diagnosis): detected (a valid ZoneSig from the D/W/M
// security call) vs created (survived EMA/RS + dedup in f_createZone). d=0 → a detection
// gate (leg/base/width/leg-in) rejected it; d>0 c=0 → EMA/RS or dedup; c>0 but low live →
// removal. This is the funnel the native row always had, now for the security TFs too.
var int _dbgPatDDet = 0
var int _dbgPatDCr  = 0
var int _dbgPatWDet = 0
var int _dbgPatWCr  = 0
var int _dbgPatMDet = 0
var int _dbgPatMCr  = 0
// PROVISIONAL PREVIEW: a leg-out on the LAST closed bar. Deliberately does NOT latch
// and does NOT enter activeZones — so it never gates support_pass / GO, and the REAL
// zone is still created normally on the next bar (where ft>=1 can finally measure the
// follow-through and the FVG). Not latching is what allows that upgrade: advancing
// lastNativeTime here would block the real find, freezing the zone at its provisional
// reading forever. Drawn dashed + faint: it says "this is forming, here is where" —
// which is what the weekend markup needs — without pretending it is confirmed.
var box   bxProv = na
var label lbProv = na
if barstate.islast
    box.delete(bxProv)
    label.delete(lbProv)
if showChartZones and d_zones and not na(nativeSig) and nativeSig.isProv and barstate.islast
    color _pc = nativeSig.isDemand ? #26a69a : #ef5350
    float _pTop = nativeSig.isDemand ? nativeSig.proximal : nativeSig.distal
    float _pBot = nativeSig.isDemand ? nativeSig.distal   : nativeSig.proximal
    bxProv := box.new(bar_index - nativeSig.bStart, _pTop, bar_index + 10, _pBot, xloc=xloc.bar_index, extend=extend.right, border_color=color.new(_pc, 30), bgcolor=color.new(_pc, 93), border_width=1, border_style=line.style_dashed)
    lbProv := label.new(bar_index + 10, _pTop, "          " + nativeSig.pattern + " (forming — FT/FVG pending)", xloc=xloc.bar_index, style=label.style_label_left, color=color.new(_pc, 85), textcolor=_pc, size=size.small)

if showChartZones and not na(nativeSig) and not nativeSig.isProv and nativeSig.zoneTime > lastNativeTime
    lastNativeTime := nativeSig.zoneTime
    _dbgNatDetected := _dbgNatDetected + 1
    // FVG POLYGRAPH — Option C (default, require_intraday_fvg OFF): ALL intraday native
    // zones draw; FVG-backed ones are TAGGED (⚡ + brighter border) in f_createZone, not
    // filtered. Option A (toggle ON): on 75/125m only FVG-backed native zones draw.
    if (not timeframe.isintraday) or (not require_intraday_fvg) or nativeSig.hasFVG
        _dbgNatFvgPass := _dbgNatFvgPass + 1
        int _before = array.size(activeZones)
        f_createZone(nativeSig, "C", true)
        if array.size(activeZones) > _before
            _dbgNatCreated := _dbgNatCreated + 1
if useDailyZ and not na(dailySig) and dailySig.zoneTime > lastDailyTime
    lastDailyTime := dailySig.zoneTime
    _dbgPatDDet := _dbgPatDDet + 1
    int _bD = array.size(activeZones)
    f_createZone(dailySig, "D", false)
    if array.size(activeZones) > _bD
        _dbgPatDCr := _dbgPatDCr + 1
if useWeeklyZ and not na(weeklySig) and weeklySig.zoneTime > lastWeeklyTime
    lastWeeklyTime := weeklySig.zoneTime
    _dbgPatWDet := _dbgPatWDet + 1
    int _bW = array.size(activeZones)
    f_createZone(weeklySig, "W", false)
    if array.size(activeZones) > _bW
        _dbgPatWCr := _dbgPatWCr + 1
if useMonthlyZ and not na(monthlySig) and monthlySig.zoneTime > lastMonthlyTime
    lastMonthlyTime := monthlySig.zoneTime
    _dbgPatMDet := _dbgPatMDet + 1
    int _bM = array.size(activeZones)
    f_createZone(monthlySig, "M", false)
    if array.size(activeZones) > _bM
        _dbgPatMCr := _dbgPatMCr + 1

// --- STRUCTURAL zones: native + HTF (via request.security), like the pattern zones.
// HTF structural pivot zones now PROPAGATE to lower timeframes (a Monthly pivot
// demand shows on the 75/125m chart). Native structural stays suppressed on an
// intraday chart (minor LTF pivots = noise); on Daily+ the native structural draws,
// and D/W/M structural propagate down gated by useDailyZ/useWeeklyZ/useMonthlyZ
// (same TF guardrails as the pattern zones). Dedup vs pattern zones is handled inside
// f_createZone.
// Each call passes ITS OWN timeframe's width band — identical wiring to the pattern-zone
// security calls above (native uses the chart-TF ternary chain; D/W/M hardcode their pair).
structNativeSig  = f_structZone(pivotLeft, pivotRight, structPadBars, structTopThrATR, structDeepThrATR, pivotMinMoveATR, nativeMinW, nativeMaxW, structMinWMult)
structDailySig   = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_structZone(pivotLeft, pivotRight, structPadBars, structTopThrATR, structDeepThrATR, pivotMinMoveATR, minZW_D, maxZW_D, structMinWMult), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
structWeeklySig  = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "W", f_structZone(pivotLeft, pivotRight, structPadBars, structTopThrATR, structDeepThrATR, pivotMinMoveATR, minZW_W, maxZW_W, structMinWMult), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
structMonthlySig = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "M", f_structZone(pivotLeft, pivotRight, structPadBars, structTopThrATR, structDeepThrATR, pivotMinMoveATR, minZW_M, maxZW_M, structMinWMult), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
var int lastStrNativeTime  = 0
var int lastStrDailyTime   = 0
var int lastStrWeeklyTime  = 0
var int lastStrMonthlyTime = 0
// Diagnostics: structural zones DETECTED (survived width band + minMove inside
// f_structZone) vs CREATED (also survived EMA/RS + the same-TF dedup). Cumulative,
// across every TF. Read alongside structL (live count) on the Zones (MTF) panel row:
//   structD=0            → the width band or minMove killed them → lower structMinWMult
//   structD>0, structC=0 → EMA/RS gate or dedup in f_createZone
//   structC>0, structL=0 → removed by ageing / tested / violation
var int _dbgStrDetected = 0
var int _dbgStrCreated  = 0
if useStructural
    // NOTE: dedup is SAME-TF only (see f_createZone), so this M→W→D→native ordering has
    // no cross-TF effect — an HTF structural is never deduped against an LTF one. The
    // order only matters for native-vs-native on a Daily+ chart. Cross-TF overlap is
    // KEPT deliberately: that is confluence, and the HTF level must survive.
    if useMonthlyZ and not na(structMonthlySig) and structMonthlySig.zoneTime > lastStrMonthlyTime
        lastStrMonthlyTime := structMonthlySig.zoneTime
        _dbgStrDetected := _dbgStrDetected + 1
        int _sb = array.size(activeZones)
        f_createZone(structMonthlySig, "M", false)
        if array.size(activeZones) > _sb
            _dbgStrCreated := _dbgStrCreated + 1
    if useWeeklyZ and not na(structWeeklySig) and structWeeklySig.zoneTime > lastStrWeeklyTime
        lastStrWeeklyTime := structWeeklySig.zoneTime
        _dbgStrDetected := _dbgStrDetected + 1
        int _sb = array.size(activeZones)
        f_createZone(structWeeklySig, "W", false)
        if array.size(activeZones) > _sb
            _dbgStrCreated := _dbgStrCreated + 1
    if useDailyZ and not na(structDailySig) and structDailySig.zoneTime > lastStrDailyTime
        lastStrDailyTime := structDailySig.zoneTime
        _dbgStrDetected := _dbgStrDetected + 1
        int _sb = array.size(activeZones)
        f_createZone(structDailySig, "D", false)
        if array.size(activeZones) > _sb
            _dbgStrCreated := _dbgStrCreated + 1
    // Native structural — Daily+ charts only (suppressed intraday).
    if showChartZones and not timeframe.isintraday and not na(structNativeSig) and structNativeSig.zoneTime > lastStrNativeTime
        lastStrNativeTime := structNativeSig.zoneTime
        _dbgStrDetected := _dbgStrDetected + 1
        int _sb = array.size(activeZones)
        f_createZone(structNativeSig, "C", true)
        if array.size(activeZones) > _sb
            _dbgStrCreated := _dbgStrCreated + 1

// ==========================================================================
// S/R LEVELS — per-TF detection, then MANUAL-over-AUTO resolution
// ==========================================================================
// Each TF clusters its OWN pivots at its OWN ATR — a weekly level comes from
// weekly swings, not from squinting at daily ones.
srM = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "M", f_srLevels(sr_pv, sr_pv, sr_pool, sr_tol, sr_minspace, sr_min_touch, sr_wick_touch), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
srW = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "W", f_srLevels(sr_pv, sr_pv, sr_pool, sr_tol, sr_minspace, sr_min_touch, sr_wick_touch), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
srD = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_srLevels(sr_pv, sr_pv, sr_pool, sr_tol, sr_minspace, sr_min_touch, sr_wick_touch), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)

// A manual level is live if the master switch is on, it has been placed (>0), and
// its TF is visible on this chart.
f_lvOn(float px, bool tfOk) => sr_on and d_sr and tfOk and not na(px) and px > 0.0
// ROLE IS DERIVED — never fixed at detection — so a level flips Support↔Resistance
// when price closes through it (the R-flip→S rule) instead of going stale.
f_lvRole(float px) => px > close ? "Resistance" : "Support"
// TESTS GRADE A LEVEL, and MORE IS WORSE (MTTWR). This is the inversion.
// Grade anchors to the MIN-TOUCH count, not to 1. A level does not exist below
// sr_min_touch touches, so minTouch touches IS the fresh state — the level has just
// proved itself and is unspent. More = weakening. >= sr_mttwr_n = primed to break.
// (Keyed to 1 this read "fresh" only for one-touch levels, which are now — correctly —
//  not levels at all, so "fresh" would have become unreachable.)
f_lvGrade(int tests) => tests >= mttwrEff ? "MTTWR" : tests <= sr_min_touch ? "fresh" : "tested×" + str.tostring(tests)
// Does this TF have ANY manual level placed? If so it OWNS that timeframe: the
// auto levels for that TF are suppressed entirely rather than drawn alongside,
// because "your hand-drawn levels ARE the location layer" — a machine guess sitting
// next to your mark on the same timeframe is noise, not a second opinion.
f_tfHasManual(float v1, float v2, float v3, float v4, bool tfOk) => f_lvOn(v1, tfOk) or f_lvOn(v2, tfOk) or f_lvOn(v3, tfOk) or f_lvOn(v4, tfOk)

bool manM = f_tfHasManual(mv1, mv2, mv3, mv4, useLvM)
bool manW = f_tfHasManual(wv1, wv2, wv3, wv4, useLvW)
bool manD = f_tfHasManual(dv1, dv2, dv3, dv4, useLvD)

// --- MANUAL TRENDLINES: TF visibility, live test, projection to the current bar ---
// Same guardrail as the levels (HTF down, never LTF up), driven by the line's own
// TF dropdown rather than the group it sits in.
f_tlVis(string tf) => tf == "Monthly" ? useLvM : tf == "Weekly" ? useLvW : useLvD
// A line is live only when BOTH anchors carry a time AND a non-zero price. A
// half-placed line must draw nothing rather than a line to somewhere arbitrary.
bool tls_live = tl_on and d_tl and tls_t1 > 0 and tls_t2 > 0 and tls_p1 > 0.0 and tls_p2 > 0.0 and tls_t2 != tls_t1 and f_tlVis(tls_tf)
bool tlr_live = tl_on and d_tl and tlr_t1 > 0 and tlr_t2 > 0 and tlr_p1 > 0.0 and tlr_p2 > 0.0 and tlr_t2 != tlr_t1 and f_tlVis(tlr_tf)
// Projected value AT THIS BAR — this is what makes the line machine-readable: a
// trendline is just a level whose price moves, so once projected it flows through
// the same nearest-S/R pickers the horizontals use, and reaches the PLAN and the
// confluence score without any of those consumers knowing it is a diagonal.
// Anchors are in TIME (ms), so the slope is price-per-ms and must be applied to a
// time delta — never mixed with a bar-index slope.
float tls_now = tls_live ? tls_p2 + (tls_p2 - tls_p1) / float(tls_t2 - tls_t1) * float(time - tls_t2) : na
float tlr_now = tlr_live ? tlr_p2 + (tlr_p2 - tlr_p1) / float(tlr_t2 - tlr_t1) * float(time - tlr_t2) : na
string tls_tfTag = tls_tf == "Monthly" ? "M" : tls_tf == "Weekly" ? "W" : "D"
string tlr_tfTag = tlr_tf == "Monthly" ? "M" : tlr_tf == "Weekly" ? "W" : "D"

// Line WEIGHT encodes conviction, because the timeframe a level is drawn on IS its
// weight: Monthly 3px, Weekly 2px, Daily 1px. You should be able to tell a weekly
// floor from a daily one without reading the label.
var array<line>  srLines = array.new<line>()
var array<label> srLbls  = array.new<label>()
var line  lnTlS = na
var line  lnTlR = na
var label lbTlS = na
var label lbTlR = na
var box   bxFlag = na
var label lbFlag = na
var box   bxMan  = na
var label lbMan  = na

f_drawLv(float px, string tfTag, int tests, int firstT, bool originHigh, bool isManual) =>
    if not na(px) and px > 0
        bool isSup = px <= close
        // COLOUR BY ROLE, not by timeframe: GREEN = support, RED = resistance. Role is
        // derived from price, so a flipped R→S turns green by itself the moment price
        // closes above it — no state to keep in sync. The TIMEFRAME is carried by line
        // WIDTH (M 3px / W 2px / D 1px) and by the label, so nothing is lost.
        color lc = isSup ? #26a69a : #ef5350
        int   w  = tfTag == "M" ? 3 : tfTag == "W" ? 2 : 1
        // FLIPPED = the level's ORIGIN disagrees with its current role: born from pivot
        // HIGHS but now sitting below price (old resistance → support), or vice versa.
        // Role alone cannot tell you this — it is derived from price and has forgotten
        // where the level came from. That is why the origin is tracked at detection.
        bool isFlip = (not isManual) and ((originHigh and isSup) or ((not originHigh) and (not isSup)))
        // DASHED = tested and NOT flipped. A flipped level is fresh IN ITS NEW ROLE —
        // an old resistance has never been tested as support — so it draws solid.
        // MTTWR falls out of this for free (tests >= 4 > min_touch → tested → dashed).
        bool tested = (not isManual) and tests > sr_min_touch
        bool dash   = tested and not isFlip
        string g    = isManual ? "manual" : f_lvGrade(tests)
        string ftag = isFlip ? (isSup ? " · R→S" : " · S→R") : ""
        // RAY FROM THE FIRST TOUCH — not from a blind 300-bar back-extension, which
        // drew the level flat through history where it was not yet in play.
        // The line ENDS at the current bar and the label hangs to its RIGHT
        // (style_label_left anchors the body rightward), so the line can no longer run
        // THROUGH the text and render it as struck-through. extend.right is gone for
        // the same reason — it was the thing crossing the label.
        int _t0 = firstT > 0 ? firstT : time[math.min(300, bar_index)]
        array.push(srLines, line.new(_t0, px, time, px, xloc=xloc.bar_time, color=color.new(lc, dash ? 35 : 0), width=w, style=dash ? line.style_dashed : line.style_solid))
        array.push(srLbls,  label.new(time, px, tfTag + " · " + f_lvRole(px) + "  " + str.tostring(px, format.mintick) + ftag + " · " + g, xloc=xloc.bar_time, style=label.style_label_left, color=color.new(lc, 82), textcolor=lc, size=size.small))

// Draw the auto pair for one TF, unless you have marked that TF yourself.
f_drawAutoTf(SRSig s, string tfTag, bool tfOk, bool tfShow, bool hasManual) =>
    if show_sr_lv and d_sr and tfOk and tfShow and not hasManual and not na(s)
        f_drawLv(s.a1, tfTag, s.a1t, s.a1x, s.a1h, false)
        f_drawLv(s.a2, tfTag, s.a2t, s.a2x, s.a2h, false)
        f_drawLv(s.b1, tfTag, s.b1t, s.b1x, s.b1h, false)
        f_drawLv(s.b2, tfTag, s.b2t, s.b2x, s.b2h, false)

// Calendar age cap (days) for a zone, by its own timeframe. Native "C" zones use
// the CHART timeframe. Monthly 4y / Weekly 2y / Daily 6mo / 125m 4w / 75m 3w.
f_ageCapDays(string ztf) =>
    int d = age_75_days
    if ztf == "M"
        d := age_monthly_days
    else if ztf == "W"
        d := age_weekly_days
    else if ztf == "D"
        d := age_daily_days
    else
        // native "C" zone → cap by the CHART timeframe
        d := timeframe.ismonthly ? age_monthly_days : timeframe.isweekly ? age_weekly_days : timeframe.isdaily ? age_daily_days : chartSec >= 7500 ? age_125_days : age_75_days
    d

// #27 RECENCY: a zone's displayed score decays linearly from its FORMATION to its TF's
// ageing cap (the same cap f_ageCapDays returns), so a fresher zone outscores an older
// one of equal intrinsic merit. Floored at 0. z.strength holds the intrinsic (base)
// score; this returns the age-adjusted read used on the label and in the panel grade.
f_recencyScore(int baseScore, string ztf, int originT) =>
    int _out = baseScore
    if recencyDecay and not na(originT)
        float _capMs = f_ageCapDays(ztf) * 86400000.0
        float _frac  = _capMs > 0 ? math.min((time - originT) / _capMs, 1.0) : 0.0
        _out := math.max(baseScore - int(math.round(recencyMaxDrop * _frac)), 0)
    _out

// --- STATE MANAGEMENT with the S4 "tested" rule (reaction + travel/EMA/level) ---
int _MS_DAY = 86400000
if array.size(activeZones) > 0
    for i = array.size(activeZones) - 1 to 0
        z = array.get(activeZones, i)
        // ── AGEING (calendar, per-TF) — zones age out this many days after FORMATION
        // (z.originTime). Monthly 4y / Weekly 2y / Daily 6mo / 125m 4w / 75m 3w — so
        // Daily+intraday zones stop populating indefinitely to the left, while
        // Monthly/Weekly persist for years. Applies to every zone (M/W/D/native).
        float _capMs = f_ageCapDays(z.tf) * _MS_DAY
        if not na(z.originTime) and (time - z.originTime) > _capMs
            if z.tf == "C"
                _rmAge := _rmAge + 1
            z.deleteDrawings()            // remove entirely (no greyed stub) — declutter
            array.remove(activeZones, i)
            continue
        // v3.2 AUDIT FIX: reaction / tested / violation are judged on CLOSED bars
        // ONLY. These rules read the forming bar (and forming HTF EMA/ATR via
        // security) but end in array.remove + deleteDrawings — IRREVERSIBLE. An
        // intraday tick across a forming daily EMA20 was deleting zones that a
        // chart reload would resurrect: the live chart and the reloaded chart
        // disagreed about which zones exist. Confirmation-before-entry applies to
        // the engine too: nothing permanent happens on an unconfirmed bar.
        // #41: a zone already greyed as tested is FROZEN — skip all reaction / tested /
        // violation reprocessing so it stays put for visual verification.
        if barstate.isconfirmed and not z.tested
            // #27: refresh the label with the age-decayed score each confirmed bar. Done
            // before the tested/violation checks below, so a zone about to be deleted just
            // wastes one harmless set_text; a surviving zone shows its current recency read.
            if recencyDecay and showZonesIZE and d_zones and showLabels and not na(z.drawing)
                box.set_text(z.drawing, f_buildLabel(z.tf, z.isDemand, z.pattern, f_recencyScore(z.strength, z.tf, z.originTime), z.nBase, z.confBonus, z.isControlling, z.hasFVG))
            float zW = math.abs(z.proximal - z.distal)
            // "Touched" (z.wasInZone tracks this bar-to-bar) = a wick pierced the proximal
            // line OR the candle closed within the zone — but did NOT close beyond the
            // distal (that is a violation, handled by checkMitigation below).
            bool touchedNow = z.isDemand ? (low <= z.proximal and close >= z.distal) : (high >= z.proximal and close <= z.distal)
            // "Moved out" = this candle is back on the entry side of the proximal.
            bool movedOut   = z.isDemand ? (low > z.proximal) : (high < z.proximal)
            // Reaction = a PRIOR candle touched/closed-within, and THIS candle moved back
            // out past the proximal (Jay's definition of a reaction from the zone).
            if z.wasInZone and movedOut and bar_index > z.originBar + 1
                z.reacted   := true
                z.reactRef  := z.proximal
                // Rule-3 strong S/R = nearest HTF pivot high ABOVE the zone (demand) /
                // pivot low BELOW (supply). If the last HTF pivot is not on the correct
                // side, rule 3 stays inert and rules 1 & 2 carry the tested check.
                z.strongLvl := z.isDemand ? ((not na(lastPH) and lastPH > z.proximal) ? lastPH : na) : ((not na(lastPL) and lastPL < z.proximal) ? lastPL : na)
                z.emaPre    := z.isDemand ? (not na(dailyEMA20) and close < dailyEMA20) : (not na(dailyEMA20) and close > dailyEMA20)
            z.wasInZone := touchedNow
            // TESTED = reacted AND confirmed by ANY of the 3 rules → the zone has done its
            // job, so it is REMOVED from the chart entirely (no greyed tested state — Jay's
            // declutter rule). A fresh, un-reacted zone is the only tradeable one.
            bool _testedOut = false
            if z.reacted
                // RULE 1 — travel. v3.2: measured in ATR by default, not zone-widths.
                // Zone-width scaling is INVERTED: it made the travel needed proportional
                // to the zone's own size, so a 3pt zone died on a 6pt move while a 30pt
                // zone survived it. The narrower (more precise) the zone, the faster it
                // was retired — exactly backwards. ATR is the scale price actually moves in.
                // The zone's OWN timeframe's ATR — a Monthly zone is judged in monthly
                // ATR even when it is drawn on a 75m chart. Native "C" zones use the
                // chart's ATR, which IS their own timeframe by definition.
                float _zAtr = z.tf == "M" ? atrM_tf : z.tf == "W" ? atrW_tf : z.tf == "D" ? atrD_tf : chart_atr
                float _travelNeed = testedTravelMode == "ATR" ? testedTravelATR * nz(_zAtr, chart_atr) : testedTravelMult * zW
                bool c_travel = z.isDemand ? (high >= z.reactRef + _travelNeed) : (low <= z.reactRef - _travelNeed)
                // RULES 2 & 3 — a close across the DAILY EMA20 / a daily-or-weekly pivot.
                // Both are DAILY references, so they are same-TF only for a DAILY zone.
                // #25/#40/#42 FIX: they used to apply to WEEKLY and MONTHLY zones too, which
                // retired them on a DAILY EMA20 cross — far too fast (CoalIndia: 3 of 37
                // weekly zones survived; Caplipoint 3 of 19). A weekly base is not consumed
                // because price crossed the daily EMA20 — the same category error the v3.2
                // note called out for 75m zones, just one tier up. W/M zones are now judged
                // by TRAVEL (in their OWN TF's ATR, rule 1 above) and VIOLATION only, exactly
                // like native intraday zones. Only DAILY (and native-daily) zones consult
                // the EMA/level cross.
                bool _zIsDaily = z.tf == "D" or (z.tf == "C" and timeframe.isdaily)
                bool _emaLvlOk = (not tested_tf_match) or _zIsDaily
                bool c_ema    = _emaLvlOk and (z.isDemand ? (z.emaPre and not na(dailyEMA20) and close > dailyEMA20) : (z.emaPre and not na(dailyEMA20) and close < dailyEMA20))
                bool c_level  = _emaLvlOk and (z.isDemand ? (not na(z.strongLvl) and close > z.strongLvl) : (not na(z.strongLvl) and close < z.strongLvl))
                _testedOut := c_travel or c_ema or c_level
                // v3.2 DIAG: WHICH of the three retired it? The cumulative d/f/m/L funnel
                // proves a zone was created-then-removed but is silent on WHY, which left
                // the last diagnosis as guesswork between three OR'd rules. Attribute it.
                // (Counted per rule that was TRUE, so overlaps show — they are not
                //  mutually exclusive and the sum can exceed the removal count.)
                if _testedOut and z.tf == "C"
                    if c_travel
                        _rmTrv := _rmTrv + 1
                    if c_ema
                        _rmEma := _rmEma + 1
                    if c_level
                        _rmLvl := _rmLvl + 1
            if _testedOut
                // #41: default = delete outright (declutter). With "Show tested zones in
                // grey" ON, the zone is instead recoloured grey and FROZEN (z.tested) so
                // every valid zone that ever formed can be verified on the chart. Either
                // way it is excluded from the trigger (the support scan skips z.tested).
                if show_tested_grey
                    z.tested := true
                    box.set_bgcolor(z.drawing, color.new(color.gray, 90))
                    box.set_border_color(z.drawing, color.new(color.gray, 45))
                    box.set_text_color(z.drawing, color.new(color.gray, 25))
                    box.set_border_style(z.drawing, line.style_dotted)
                    continue
                else
                    z.deleteDrawings()
                    array.remove(activeZones, i)
                    continue
            isMitigated = z.checkMitigation(close, low, high, mitBasis)
            if isMitigated
                if z.tf == "C"
                    _rmVio := _rmVio + 1
                z.deleteDrawings()
                // #4: a small, faint dot marks the break (was a big red ✗ — too cluttered).
                if markViolations
                    if z.tf == "C"
                        label.new(bar_index, z.distal, "", color=color.new(color.red, 45), style=label.style_circle, size=size.tiny, xloc=xloc.bar_index)
                    else
                        label.new(time, z.distal, "", color=color.new(color.red, 45), style=label.style_circle, size=size.tiny, xloc=xloc.bar_time)
                array.remove(activeZones, i)

// --- Per-bar zone scan → the decision values the S4 gate + panel consume ---
float _z_inDZstr = na
bool  z_inDZ = false
bool  z_inDZ_fvg = false      // the fresh DZ price is in is FVG-Polygraph-qualified
bool  z_inDZ_ctrl = false     // v3.2: price is inside a CONTROLLING demand zone (confluence)
bool  z_inSZ = false
// v3.2: the DISTAL (far edge) of the supply zone(s) price is INSIDE. When price is
// inside supply the proximal is BEHIND you — the obstacle is the distal, and you
// are not clear until price closes above it. Overlapping zones merge: the ceiling
// is the HIGHEST distal, because you are not out until you are out of both.
// Without this a supply zone CONTAINING price contributed nothing to overhead
// (z_nearSZprox only ever collected zones strictly ABOVE), so sitting inside two
// monthly supply zones read as "BLUE SKY" — the worst location scored as the best.
float z_inSZdist = na
// v3.2: how many DISTINCT timeframes have a demand zone containing price right now?
// 2+ is real MTF confluence (a daily zone sitting inside a weekly one) and scores.
bool  _dzTfC = false
bool  _dzTfD = false
bool  _dzTfW = false
bool  _dzTfM = false
float z_inDZprox = na
float z_inDZdist = na
float z_nearSZprox = na
float z_nearDZprox = na
float z_nearDZdist = na
int   zc_dz = 0
int   zc_sz = 0
int   zc_ctrl = 0
int   zc_nat = 0
int   zc_struct = 0                 // live structural (PvL/PvH) zones — the structL diagnostic
int   zc_patD = 0                   // live PATTERN (non-pivot) zones per TF — the pat funnel L
int   zc_patW = 0
int   zc_patM = 0
int   _zn = array.size(activeZones)
if _zn > 0
    for i = 0 to _zn - 1
        zz = array.get(activeZones, i)
        // #41: a greyed tested zone is on the chart for verification only — it is NOT a
        // live location. Skip it entirely so it never feeds support, counts, or the trigger.
        if zz.tested
            continue
        if zz.tf == "C"
            zc_nat := zc_nat + 1
        bool _zzPivot = zz.pattern == "PvL" or zz.pattern == "PvH"
        if _zzPivot
            zc_struct := zc_struct + 1
        else if zz.tf == "D"
            zc_patD := zc_patD + 1
        else if zz.tf == "W"
            zc_patW := zc_patW + 1
        else if zz.tf == "M"
            zc_patM := zc_patM + 1
        if zz.isDemand
            zc_dz := zc_dz + 1
        else
            zc_sz := zc_sz + 1
        if zz.isControlling
            zc_ctrl := zc_ctrl + 1
        bool inDemand = zz.isDemand and zz.distal <= close and close <= zz.proximal
        bool inSupply = (not zz.isDemand) and zz.proximal <= close and close <= zz.distal
        if inDemand
            // Every zone still in activeZones IS fresh: tested/violated/aged zones are
            // deleted outright by the state block above. There is no "tested but still
            // drawn" state, hence no touch counter and no separate fresh flag.
            z_inDZ := true
            if zz.hasFVG
                z_inDZ_fvg := true
            if zz.isControlling
                z_inDZ_ctrl := true
            if zz.tf == "C"
                _dzTfC := true
            else if zz.tf == "D"
                _dzTfD := true
            else if zz.tf == "W"
                _dzTfW := true
            else if zz.tf == "M"
                _dzTfM := true
            // #27: the panel grade reads the RECENCY-adjusted score, matching the label.
            int _zzScore = f_recencyScore(zz.strength, zz.tf, zz.originTime)
            if na(_z_inDZstr) or _zzScore > _z_inDZstr
                _z_inDZstr := _zzScore
                z_inDZprox := zz.proximal
                z_inDZdist := zz.distal
        else if inSupply
            z_inSZ := true
            if na(z_inSZdist) or zz.distal > z_inSZdist
                z_inSZdist := zz.distal        // merged ceiling of the zones price is INSIDE
        else
            if zz.isDemand and zz.proximal < close
                if na(z_nearDZprox) or zz.proximal > z_nearDZprox
                    z_nearDZprox := zz.proximal
                    z_nearDZdist := zz.distal
            else if (not zz.isDemand) and zz.proximal > close
                if na(z_nearSZprox) or zz.proximal < z_nearSZprox
                    z_nearSZprox := zz.proximal

// --- SUPPLY BAND MERGE ---------------------------------------------------------
// Overlapping supply zones are ONE obstacle, not several: you are not clear until
// price is above the whole stack. Start from the zones price is inside (z_inSZdist)
// and repeatedly absorb any supply zone that overlaps the band from above, taking
// the higher distal each time. Three passes is a bounded fixpoint — it resolves any
// realistic overlap chain without an unbounded loop in Pine.
float szBandTop = z_inSZdist
if not na(szBandTop) and array.size(activeZones) > 0
    for _pass = 0 to 2
        for _bi = 0 to array.size(activeZones) - 1
            _bz = array.get(activeZones, _bi)
            if (not _bz.isDemand) and _bz.proximal <= szBandTop and _bz.distal > szBandTop
                szBandTop := _bz.distal

// ==========================================
// A1. ANCHOR DATES (daily structure → AVWAP anchors)
// ==========================================
f_anchors() =>
    bool is_low    = low <= ta.lowest(low, low_look)
    float a_low_f  = ta.valuewhen(is_low, time, 0)
    bool bo_cross  = ta.crossover(close, ta.highest(high, bo_look)[1])
    float a_bo_f   = ta.valuewhen(bo_cross, time, 0)
    float _volsma  = ta.sma(volume, 50)
    bool gap_cond  = open > close[1] * (1.0 + gap_pct / 100.0) and volume > _volsma * gap_volx
    float a_gap_f  = ta.valuewhen(gap_cond, time, 0)
    [a_low_f, a_bo_f, a_gap_f]

[anc_low_f, anc_bo_f, anc_gap_f] = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_anchors(), barmerge.gaps_off, barmerge.lookahead_off)
int anc_low = na(anc_low_f) ? na : int(anc_low_f)
int anc_bo  = na(anc_bo_f)  ? na : int(anc_bo_f)
int anc_gap = na(anc_gap_f) ? na : int(anc_gap_f)

// ==========================================
// A2. DAILY PA BATTERY — 17 bull + recovery extras (v67.4.12 / pa_patterns.py port)
// ==========================================
f_daily_pa(float ema10_ref, float ema20_ref, simple bool confirmShift) =>
    float rng     = high - low
    float vol50   = ta.sma(volume, 50)
    float rv      = vol50 > 0 ? volume / vol50 : 0.0
    float sma50   = ta.sma(close, 50)
    float ema10   = ta.ema(close, 10)
    float ema20   = ta.ema(close, 20)
    // EMA20/EMA10 are DAILY anchors (DNA). The daily security call passes na
    // (use this context's own daily EMAs); the chart-TF `loc_*` call passes the
    // DAILY EMAs so the engulf trend-context stays daily even on 75/125m.
    float _e10    = na(ema10_ref) ? ema10 : ema10_ref
    float _e20    = na(ema20_ref) ? ema20 : ema20_ref
    float intrap  = rng > 0 ? (close - low) / rng : 0.0
    float atr10   = ta.atr(10)
    float atr10s  = ta.sma(atr10, 50)
    float vwmaV5  = ta.vwma(volume, 5)               // CORRECT dry-up: vwma of VOLUME
    float rsi14   = ta.rsi(close, 14)
    float hh10    = ta.highest(high, 10)             // hoisted (runs every bar)
    float hh3     = ta.highest(high, 3)
    float ll5     = ta.lowest(low, 5)
    float sma200  = ta.sma(close, 200)
    float body    = math.abs(close - open)
    float uwick   = high - math.max(open, close)
    float lwick   = math.min(open, close) - low
    bool  hammer  = rng > 0 and lwick > body * 2.0 and uwick < body and math.max(open, close) >= low + rng * 0.66
    float l50_1   = ta.lowest(low, 50)[1]            // prior 50-bar low (for Spring)
    float dlockH  = ta.highest(high, 20)[1]          // 20-bar locked resistance (Gap-BO / Breakout-Confirmed)
    // 1. ★★ Power Play (HTF) +4
    float low8w = ta.lowest(low, 40)
    float hi15  = ta.highest(high, 15)
    float lo15  = ta.lowest(low, 15)
    bool p_htf = low8w > 0 and lo15 > 0 and (close - low8w) / low8w > 1.0 and (hi15 - lo15) / lo15 < 0.20 and close > sma50
    // 2. Power Play (Strong Close) +2
    bool p_sc = close > open and (close - low) > (high - close) * 3 and rv > 1.0
    // 3. VCP Breakout +3 (contraction on PRIOR bar → 10d-high break on vol)
    bool vcp_prior = not na(atr10s[1]) and atr10[1] < atr10s[1] * 1.5 and vwmaV5[1] < vol50[1]
    bool p_vcp = vcp_prior and close > hh10[1] and rv > 1.2 and intrap >= 0.60
    // 4. Pocket Pivot +2
    float mdv = 0.0
    for j = 1 to 10
        if close[j] < close[j + 1] and volume[j] > mdv
            mdv := volume[j]
    bool p_pp = close > close[1] and close > open and mdv > 0 and volume > mdv and close > sma50 and (close - low) >= rng * 0.5
    // 5. Bullish Engulfing (gated) +2
    bool raw_eng = close[1] < open[1] and close > open and open <= close[1] and close >= open[1]
    bool p_eng = raw_eng and close < _e10 and _e10 < _e20 and rv > 2.0 and not na(rsi14[1]) and rsi14[1] < 40
    // 6. Liquidity Sweep Reclaim +2
    bool p_liq = ll5 < sma50 and close > sma50 and volume > vol50 * 1.5
    // 7. 3-Bar Bull Reversal +2
    bool p_3b = low[1] < low[2] and low[2] < low[3] and close > hh3[1]
    // 9. Inside-3 (Coil) +2
    bool ins1 = high < high[1] and low > low[1]
    bool ins2 = high[1] < high[2] and low[1] > low[2]
    bool ins3 = high[2] < high[3] and low[2] > low[3]
    bool p_in3 = ins1 and ins2 and ins3
    // 10. True NR7 +1 (current range <= each of prior 6)
    bool p_nr7 = rng > 0 and (high[1]-low[1]) >= rng and (high[2]-low[2]) >= rng and (high[3]-low[3]) >= rng and (high[4]-low[4]) >= rng and (high[5]-low[5]) >= rng and (high[6]-low[6]) >= rng
    // 11. ★ IB-NR7 Coil +2
    bool p_ibnr7 = ins1 and p_nr7
    // 12. Wyckoff Spring +3 — undercut prior 50-bar low, reclaim green, on LOW volume
    bool p_spr  = not na(l50_1) and low < l50_1 and close > l50_1 and close > open and volume < vol50
    // 13. Gap-Up Breakout +3 — gap over prior high, clears 20-bar locked resistance on vol
    bool p_gap  = not na(dlockH) and open > high[1] and close > dlockH and close > open and rv > 1.25
    // 14. 50-SMA Undercut & Reclaim +2
    bool p_u50  = not na(sma50) and low < sma50 and close > sma50 and close > open and rv > 1.25
    // 15. Hammer at 50-SMA +2 (hammer within 1.5% of the 50-SMA, closes above, on vol)
    bool near50 = not na(sma50) and math.abs(low - sma50) / sma50 <= 0.015
    bool p_h50  = hammer and near50 and close > sma50 and rv > 1.0
    // 16. Hammer at 200-SMA +2 (within 2% of the 200-SMA)
    bool near200 = not na(sma200) and math.abs(low - sma200) / sma200 <= 0.020
    bool p_h200 = hammer and near200 and close > sma200 and rv > 1.0
    // 17. Breakout Confirmed +2 — anti-algo: close > 20-bar lock, top-quartile close, on vol
    bool p_bc   = not na(dlockH) and close > dlockH and (close - low) > rng * 0.75 and rv > 1.25
    // --- RECOVERY-mode extras (5 new; Spring/Engulf/3-Bar/Pocket/30-WMA are reused) ---
    float atr14 = ta.atr(14)
    float lo_recent = ta.lowest(low, 10)
    float lo_prior  = ta.lowest(low, 30)[10]         // 30-bar base low ending 10 bars ago
    // R1. Climax Reversal (SC+AR) +3 — a climax down-bar in last 10, midpoint reclaimed
    int climax_j = 0
    for cj = 1 to 10
        if climax_j == 0 and close[cj] < open[cj] and volume[cj] > vol50 * 2.5 and (high[cj]-low[cj]) > atr14 * 2
            climax_j := cj
    bool p_climax = false
    if climax_j > 0
        float cmid = (high[climax_j] + low[climax_j]) / 2.0
        p_climax := close > cmid and close > open
    // R2. Higher-Low / Double-Bottom +3 — recent low RETESTS the prior base low
    // (holds >= 1% undercut, stays within 10% above it) and turns up. The
    // proximity ceiling (v1.9, mirrors pa_patterns.py fix 9-Jul-2026) stops the
    // pattern firing on every green day of an uptrend, where the 10-bar low is
    // trivially above the 30-bar base low.
    bool p_2b = lo_prior > 0 and lo_recent >= lo_prior * 0.99 and lo_recent <= lo_prior * 1.10 and close > open and close > close[1]
    // R3. Base Breakout (SOS/JAC) +3 — wide up-bar over 20-bar base resistance on vol
    float base_res = ta.highest(high, 20)[1]
    bool p_sos = close > base_res and rng > atr14 * 1.3 and rv > 1.5 and close > open
    // R4. Hammer at support +2 — hammer at the 200-SMA or the base low
    bool near_base = lo_prior > 0 and math.abs(low - lo_prior) / lo_prior <= 0.03
    bool p_hsup = hammer and (near200 or near_base) and close > open and rv > 1.0
    // R5. Volume Dry-Up +1 — supply exhausted at the base
    bool p_vdu = rv < 0.5 and rng < atr14 * 0.8
    // AUTO-mode path inference (v1.8): >=10% off the 52-week high (the GM recovery
    // CONTEXT gate) AND the long-term trend not yet repaired — below the 30-WMA proxy
    // (SMA150) OR the proxy still falling. v1.7's "below SMA150" AND-leg was self-
    // defeating: recovery names at Step 5 have confirmed the turn and often reclaimed
    // SMA150, so the best recoveries resolved Bull. Slope catches them: even after a
    // reclaim, a recovering name's SMA150 is flat/falling; a bull leader's is rising.
    float h52    = ta.highest(high, 252)
    float sma150 = ta.sma(close, 150)
    float off52  = h52 > 0 ? (h52 - close) / h52 * 100.0 : 0.0
    bool  bel30w = close < sma150
    bool  s150dn = sma150 <= sma150[10]
    // v2.3 — 200-DMA position: the GM's Bull-vs-Recovery split hinges on it
    // (Bull/accumulation lives ABOVE the 200-DMA; a beaten-down recovery is
    // BELOW it). Used to align Auto with the Golden Matcher's structural path.
    bool  bel200 = not na(sma200) and close < sma200

    // NOTE (v2.1): the OB / FVG / pivot support trackers moved to f_zones()
    // below, so they can be requested on BOTH "D" and "W" (the trading TF is
    // 125/75-min, but demand zones come from Daily + Weekly structure).

    // return as floats (na(series bool) is illegal; guard the float with nz()>0.5).
    // _o = 1 when "Confirmed daily only" is on → return each pattern evaluated on the
    // LAST CLOSED daily bar (no forming-bar repaint); _o = 0 = live developing bar.
    // NOTE (v2.0): the [_o] offset is applied INSIDE the daily-context function, so it
    // is measured in DAILY bars and is timeframe-INDEPENDENT — `expr[1]` is yesterday's
    // confirmed daily value whether the chart is Daily or 75/125-min. A prior edit gated
    // this on `timeframe.isdaily`, which made intraday charts read the DEVELOPING daily
    // bar → the battery repainted through the session (the exact flicker confirm_daily
    // exists to stop). Reverted: for a live developing-daily view, turn confirm_daily OFF.
    // BUGFIX (18-Jul): the [_o] confirm shift must apply ONLY to the DAILY security
    // call. It was applied unconditionally, so the CHART-TF (loc_*) battery was also
    // read one bar back — the battery evaluated a STALE bar while the Golden Matcher
    // evaluated the last closed one (CDSL: Rec Sum +3 in Python vs 0 in Pine, purely
    // from this one-bar offset). Worse, during live hours it compounded with
    // use_closed_candle's own [_so] display shift = up to TWO bars stale, silently
    // eating triggers. confirm_daily's own tooltip already said it "applies only when
    // Use chart timeframe is OFF" — the code just never honoured it. The chart-TF path
    // needs no shift: use_closed_candle is what protects it from the forming bar.
    int _o = (confirmShift and confirm_daily) ? 1 : 0
    [(p_htf?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_sc?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_vcp?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_pp?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_eng?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_liq?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_3b?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_in3?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_nr7?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_ibnr7?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_spr?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_gap?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_u50?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_h50?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_h200?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_bc?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_climax?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_2b?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_sos?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_hsup?1.0:0.0)[_o], (p_vdu?1.0:0.0)[_o], off52[_o], (bel30w?1.0:0.0)[_o], (s150dn?1.0:0.0)[_o], rv[_o], (bel200?1.0:0.0)[_o]]

[d_htf, d_sc, d_vcp, d_pp, d_eng, d_liq, d_3b, d_in3, d_nr7, d_ibnr7, d_spr, d_gap, d_u50, d_h50, d_h200, d_bc, d_climax, d_2b, d_sos, d_hsup, d_vdu, d_off52, d_bel30, d_s150dn, d_rv, d_bel200] = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_daily_pa(na, na, true), barmerge.gaps_off, barmerge.lookahead_off)

// 8. Stage-2 Launch +3 — TRUE weekly close crossover of 30-WMA (+ vol gate)
f_weekly() =>
    float wma30 = ta.sma(close, 30)
    bool wcross = close > wma30 and close[1] <= wma30[1]
    // v2.1: TF-independent — the [_ow] offset is in WEEKLY bars inside the weekly
    // context, so `[1]` = last CLOSED week on ANY chart TF. (A prior `timeframe
    // .isweekly` gate made 75/125-min charts read the DEVELOPING week → repaint.)
    int _ow = confirm_daily ? 1 : 0
    (wcross ? 1.0 : 0.0)[_ow]
w_cross = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "W", f_weekly(), barmerge.gaps_off, barmerge.lookahead_off)

// ==========================================
// A2b. SUPPORT ZONES (OB / FVG / pivot-low) — requested on BOTH "D" and "W"
// One stateful function, two timeframe calls → zero drift with the Golden
// Matcher's pa_patterns.detect_support_zones_dw. Each zone invalidates on a
// close below it. The [_oz] offset is in the requested TF's bar units, so it is
// non-repainting on the 75/125-min trading chart.
// ==========================================
f_zones() =>
    // Order Block — last down-candle before a volume displacement up.
    // ob_tested flips true once price ENTERED the OB and then LEFT (a completed
    // mitigation) — the current first tap still reads fresh; a re-tap is spent.
    var float ob_top = na
    var float ob_bot = na
    var float ob_time = na                 // formation candle time (box left anchor)
    var bool  ob_tested = false
    var bool  ob_in = false
    if not na(ob_top)
        bool _obin = low <= ob_top and high >= ob_bot
        if ob_in and not _obin
            ob_tested := true              // entered then left = TESTED (grey/excluded)
        ob_in := _obin
        if close < ob_bot                  // VIOLATED (close < distal) → delete
            ob_top := na
            ob_bot := na
            ob_time := na
            ob_tested := false
            ob_in := false
    int red_off = -1
    for k = 1 to 5
        if close[k] < open[k]
            red_off := k
            break
    float hi5_prev = ta.highest(high, 5)[1]
    float vol_sma50 = ta.sma(volume, 50)
    bool  is_disp = close > hi5_prev and volume > vol_sma50
    if is_disp and red_off != -1
        ob_top := high[red_off]
        ob_bot := low[red_off]
        ob_time := float(time[red_off])      // the OB candle itself = the zone's origin
        ob_tested := false
        ob_in := false                       // impulse bar leaves the zone; not a test
    // FVG — 3-bar bullish gap (fvg_tested = price traded back into the gap then left)
    var float fvg_top = na
    var float fvg_bot = na
    var float fvg_time = na                // formation (middle candle) time
    var bool  fvg_tested = false
    var bool  fvg_in = false
    if not na(fvg_top)
        bool _fin = low <= fvg_top and high >= fvg_bot
        if fvg_in and not _fin
            fvg_tested := true             // entered then left = TESTED (grey/excluded)
        fvg_in := _fin
        if close < fvg_bot                 // VIOLATED (close < distal) → delete
            fvg_top := na
            fvg_bot := na
            fvg_time := na
            fvg_tested := false
            fvg_in := false
    if high[2] < low
        fvg_top := low
        fvg_bot := high[2]
        fvg_time := float(time[1])           // the 3-bar gap's middle candle = origin
        fvg_tested := false
        fvg_in := false                      // price sits above the gap at formation
    // Pivot support — pivotlow(5,5). A STRUCTURAL level, NEVER deleted (unlike
    // OB/FVG): a tested pivot stays as support; a VIOLATED pivot (close below)
    // FLIPS to resistance (previous-support-now-resistance) and stays — cleared
    // only when price reclaims it (close above). piv = support (price above),
    // piv_res = flipped resistance (price below).
    float p_low = ta.pivotlow(low, 5, 5)
    var float piv = na
    var float piv_res = na
    var float piv_time = na                 // pivot-low candle time (line left anchor)
    var float piv_res_time = na
    if not na(p_low)
        piv := p_low
        piv_time := float(time[5])          // the pivot low is 5 bars back
    if not na(piv) and close < piv        // support violated → flip to resistance (keep)
        piv_res := piv
        piv_res_time := piv_time
        piv := na
    if not na(piv_res) and close > piv_res  // resistance reclaimed → clear
        piv_res := na
        piv_res_time := na
    int _oz = confirm_daily ? 1 : 0
    [ob_top[_oz], ob_bot[_oz], fvg_top[_oz], fvg_bot[_oz], piv[_oz], (ob_tested?1.0:0.0)[_oz], (fvg_tested?1.0:0.0)[_oz], piv_res[_oz], ob_time[_oz], fvg_time[_oz], piv_time[_oz], piv_res_time[_oz]]

[d_ob_top, d_ob_bot, d_fvg_top, d_fvg_bot, d_pivot, d_ob_tested, d_fvg_tested, d_piv_res, d_ob_time, d_fvg_time, d_piv_time, d_piv_res_time] = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_zones(), barmerge.gaps_off, barmerge.lookahead_off)
[w_ob_top, w_ob_bot, w_fvg_top, w_fvg_bot, w_pivot, w_ob_tested, w_fvg_tested, w_piv_res, w_ob_time, w_fvg_time, w_piv_time, w_piv_res_time] = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "W", f_zones(), barmerge.gaps_off, barmerge.lookahead_off)

// ==========================================
// B. ANCHORED VWAPs (accumulated on chart TF from each anchor date)
// ==========================================
f_avwap(int anchor_t) =>
    var float cumV  = 0.0
    var float cumPV = 0.0
    var int   last  = 0                 // sentinel 0, NOT na: `x != na` returns na (falsy) → never sets
    if not na(anchor_t) and anchor_t != last
        cumV  := 0.0
        cumPV := 0.0
        last  := anchor_t
    if last > 0 and time >= last
        cumV  += volume
        cumPV += hlc3 * volume
    cumV > 0 ? cumPV / cumV : na

float avwap_low = show_low ? f_avwap(anc_low) : na
float avwap_bo  = show_bo  ? f_avwap(anc_bo)  : na
float avwap_gap = show_gap ? f_avwap(anc_gap) : na

avs = array.new_float()
if not na(avwap_low)
    array.push(avs, avwap_low)
if not na(avwap_bo)
    array.push(avs, avwap_bo)
if not na(avwap_gap)
    array.push(avs, avwap_gap)

float av_hi = array.size(avs) > 0 ? array.max(avs) : na
float av_lo = array.size(avs) > 0 ? array.min(avs) : na
float pinch_spread = (not na(av_hi) and close > 0) ? (av_hi - av_lo) / close * 100.0 : na
bool  pinched = array.size(avs) >= 2 and not na(pinch_spread) and pinch_spread <= pinch_pct

float nearest_sup = na
if array.size(avs) > 0
    for i = 0 to array.size(avs) - 1
        float a = array.get(avs, i)
        if a <= close and (na(nearest_sup) or a > nearest_sup)
            nearest_sup := a
float sup_dist = (not na(nearest_sup) and close > 0) ? (close - nearest_sup) / close * 100.0 : na

float _tol = tol_pct / 100.0
bool b_low = not na(avwap_low) and low <= avwap_low * (1.0 + _tol) and close > avwap_low and close > open
bool b_bo  = not na(avwap_bo)  and low <= avwap_bo  * (1.0 + _tol) and close > avwap_bo  and close > open
bool b_gap = not na(avwap_gap) and low <= avwap_gap * (1.0 + _tol) and close > avwap_gap and close > open
bool _r2g_x = ta.crossover(close, avwap_bo)
bool _r2g  = not na(avwap_bo) and _r2g_x
bool avwap_trig = b_low or b_bo or b_gap or _r2g

// ==========================================
// C. INTRADAY TRIGGER (chart TF — best on 75/125-min)
// ==========================================
float ema10c = ta.ema(close, ema_len)
bool  ema_reclaim = close > ema10c and ema10c > ema10c[1]
float basis  = ta.sma(close, sqz_len)
float dev    = bb_mult * ta.stdev(close, sqz_len)
float kc_rng = ta.atr(sqz_len)
bool  sqz_on   = (basis + dev) < (basis + kc_mult * kc_rng) and (basis - dev) > (basis - kc_mult * kc_rng)
bool  sqz_fire = not sqz_on and sqz_on[1]
float sqz_mom  = ta.linreg(close - math.avg(math.avg(ta.highest(high, sqz_len), ta.lowest(low, sqz_len)), ta.sma(close, sqz_len)), sqz_len, 0)
bool  sqz_fire_up = sqz_fire and sqz_mom > 0
// v2.5: Relaxed Squeeze Trigger Window — allows entry while momentum is actively rising out of the squeeze
bool  sqz_releasing = (not sqz_on) and sqz_mom > 0 and (sqz_fire or sqz_mom >= nz(sqz_mom[1]))
bool  intraday_trig = ema_reclaim and (not require_squeeze or sqz_releasing)

// Daily EMA10/EMA20 (DNA anchors) to overlay on the chart-TF battery's engulf.
f_daily_ema(int len) =>
    float e = ta.ema(close, len)
    int _oe = confirm_daily ? 1 : 0
    e[_oe]
float daily_ema10 = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_daily_ema(10), barmerge.gaps_off, barmerge.lookahead_off)
float daily_ema20 = request.security(syminfo.tickerid, "D", f_daily_ema(20), barmerge.gaps_off, barmerge.lookahead_off)

// Calculate PA patterns locally on the chart's timeframe (if toggled). Pass the
// DAILY EMAs so the engulf keeps its EMA20 anchor daily even on 75/125m.
[loc_htf, loc_sc, loc_vcp, loc_pp, loc_eng, loc_liq, loc_3b, loc_in3, loc_nr7, loc_ibnr7, loc_spr, loc_gap, loc_u50, loc_h50, loc_h200, loc_bc, loc_climax, loc_2b, loc_sos, loc_hsup, loc_vdu, loc_off52, loc_bel30, loc_s150dn, loc_rv, loc_bel200] = f_daily_pa(daily_ema10, daily_ema20, false)

// ==========================================
// A3. Clean bools (na→false) + tier sum + names + family strings
// ==========================================
float active_htf    = use_chart_tf ? loc_htf     : nz(d_htf, 0.0)
float active_sc     = use_chart_tf ? loc_sc      : nz(d_sc, 0.0)
float active_vcp    = use_chart_tf ? loc_vcp     : nz(d_vcp, 0.0)
float active_pp     = use_chart_tf ? loc_pp      : nz(d_pp, 0.0)
float active_eng    = use_chart_tf ? loc_eng     : nz(d_eng, 0.0)
float active_liq    = use_chart_tf ? loc_liq     : nz(d_liq, 0.0)
float active_3b     = use_chart_tf ? loc_3b      : nz(d_3b, 0.0)
float active_in3    = use_chart_tf ? loc_in3     : nz(d_in3, 0.0)
float active_nr7    = use_chart_tf ? loc_nr7     : nz(d_nr7, 0.0)
float active_ibnr7  = use_chart_tf ? loc_ibnr7   : nz(d_ibnr7, 0.0)
float active_spr    = use_chart_tf ? loc_spr     : nz(d_spr, 0.0)
float active_gap    = use_chart_tf ? loc_gap     : nz(d_gap, 0.0)
float active_u50    = use_chart_tf ? loc_u50     : nz(d_u50, 0.0)
float active_h50    = use_chart_tf ? loc_h50     : nz(d_h50, 0.0)
float active_h200   = use_chart_tf ? loc_h200    : nz(d_h200, 0.0)
float active_bc     = use_chart_tf ? loc_bc      : nz(d_bc, 0.0)
float active_climax = use_chart_tf ? loc_climax  : nz(d_climax, 0.0)
float active_2b     = use_chart_tf ? loc_2b      : nz(d_2b, 0.0)
float active_sos    = use_chart_tf ? loc_sos     : nz(d_sos, 0.0)
float active_hsup   = use_chart_tf ? loc_hsup    : nz(d_hsup, 0.0)
float active_vdu    = use_chart_tf ? loc_vdu     : nz(d_vdu, 0.0)

// HTF is positional ("100% move in 8 weeks + tight flag") — meaningless on an
// intraday TF, so suppress it in chart-TF mode (matches the GM Python's
// intraday=True, which forces HTF off). LAU / 30-WMA-reclaim already stay
// weekly (w_cross), so HTF is the only positional pattern that would leak.
bool kHTF   = show_pa and active_htf > 0.5 and not use_chart_tf
bool kSC    = show_pa and active_sc > 0.5
bool kVCP   = show_pa and active_vcp > 0.5
bool kPP    = show_pa and active_pp > 0.5
bool kENG   = show_pa and active_eng > 0.5
bool kLIQ   = show_pa and active_liq > 0.5
bool k3B    = show_pa and active_3b > 0.5
// v1.9: Stage-2 proxy gate added — Python's Stage-2 Launch requires the name to
// BE Stage 2 ("2" in stage); the Pine proxy is close above a RISING 30-WMA proxy
// (not d_bel30, not d_s150dn). Without it LAU fired on Stage-4 dead-cat bounces.
bool s2_proxy = nz(d_bel30, 1.0) < 0.5 and nz(d_s150dn, 1.0) < 0.5
bool kLAU   = show_pa and nz(w_cross, 0.0) > 0.5 and nz(d_rv, 0.0) > 1.25 and s2_proxy
bool kIN3   = show_pa and active_in3 > 0.5
bool kNR7   = show_pa and active_nr7 > 0.5
bool kIBNR7 = show_pa and active_ibnr7 > 0.5
bool kSPR   = show_pa and active_spr > 0.5
bool kGAP   = show_pa and active_gap > 0.5
bool kU50   = show_pa and active_u50 > 0.5
bool kH50   = show_pa and active_h50 > 0.5
bool kH200  = show_pa and active_h200 > 0.5
bool kBC    = show_pa and active_bc > 0.5
// recovery-mode flags (5 new + reused Spring/Engulf/3-Bar/Pocket + weekly 30-WMA reclaim)
bool kCLIMAX  = show_pa and active_climax > 0.5
bool k2B      = show_pa and active_2b > 0.5
bool kSOS     = show_pa and active_sos > 0.5
bool kHSUP    = show_pa and active_hsup > 0.5
bool kVDU     = show_pa and active_vdu > 0.5
bool kRECLAIM = show_pa and nz(w_cross,  0.0) > 0.5      // weekly 30-WMA reclaim (Stage 1→2)
// Mode resolution — aligned to the Golden Matcher's STRUCTURAL Bull-vs-Recovery
// split (v2.3). GM puts Bull/accumulation ABOVE the 200-DMA and a beaten-down
// recovery BELOW it, so Auto flips to Recovery only when ALL hold:
//   (1) >= auto_dd_floor% off the 52wk high (GM recovery CONTEXT gate),
//   (2) trend not repaired — below the 30-WMA proxy OR its slope still falling,
//   (3) BELOW the 200-DMA — the discriminant that stops a shallow bull PULLBACK
//       (10-15% off highs, still above the 200-DMA) from mis-resolving Recovery.
// A name above its 200-DMA is Bull (matches GM's Bull-by-default). Residual gap:
// Pine can't see RFF, so an early recovery that already reclaimed the 200-DMA
// resolves Bull here while GM (recovery engine) shows Recovery — use the manual
// Mode override for that rare case.
bool auto_rec = nz(d_off52, 0.0) >= auto_dd_floor and (nz(d_bel30, 0.0) > 0.5 or nz(d_s150dn, 0.0) > 0.5) and (not auto_require_below_200 or nz(d_bel200, 0.0) > 0.5)
bool is_rec   = mode == "Recovery" or (mode == "Auto" and auto_rec)

int tsum = is_rec ? ((kCLIMAX?3:0)+(kSPR?3:0)+(k2B?3:0)+(kSOS?3:0)+(kENG?2:0)+(kHSUP?2:0)+(k3B?2:0)+(kPP?2:0)+(kVDU?1:0)+(kRECLAIM?3:0)) : ((kHTF?4:0)+(kSC?2:0)+(kVCP?3:0)+(kPP?2:0)+(kENG?2:0)+(kLIQ?2:0)+(k3B?2:0)+(kLAU?3:0)+(kIN3?2:0)+(kNR7?1:0)+(kIBNR7?2:0)+(kSPR?3:0)+(kGAP?3:0)+(kU50?2:0)+(kH50?2:0)+(kH200?2:0)+(kBC?2:0))
bool any_pa = is_rec ? (kCLIMAX or kSPR or k2B or kSOS or kENG or kHSUP or k3B or kPP or kVDU or kRECLAIM) : (kHTF or kSC or kVCP or kPP or kENG or kLIQ or k3B or kLAU or kIN3 or kNR7 or kIBNR7 or kSPR or kGAP or kU50 or kH50 or kH200 or kBC)
bool pa_fire = any_pa and not any_pa[1]
// PATH-SPECIFICITY of the live trigger (answers "why does GO stay when I flip Bull<->Recovery?").
// Spring/Engulf/3-Bar/Pocket are in BOTH batteries; a GO resting ONLY on those holds in either
// path. A GO that carries a path-EXCLUSIVE pattern drops when you flip away from that path.
bool pa_bull_excl   = kHTF or kSC or kVCP or kLIQ or kLAU or kIN3 or kNR7 or kIBNR7 or kGAP or kU50 or kH50 or kH200 or kBC
bool pa_rec_excl    = kCLIMAX or k2B or kSOS or kHSUP or kVDU or kRECLAIM
bool pa_shared_only = any_pa and not (is_rec ? pa_rec_excl : pa_bull_excl)

// ==========================================================================
// PATTERNS — flag · geometry · manual box
// ==========================================================================
// --- FLAG. Four requirements, because a flag is not "a quiet range after a move":
//   POLE          a real impulse before the consolidation
//   TIGHT         the consolidation is contained
//   COUNTER-DRIFT it slopes AGAINST the pole  ← the defining feature
//   DRY VOLUME    it dries up
//   PROPORTION    it gives back only a fraction of the pole (else it's a reversal)
// Chart Markup required only POLE + TIGHT, so it fired on continuation drifts.
float _flagHi   = ta.highest(high, flag_cons)
float _flagLo   = ta.lowest(low, flag_cons)
float _flagVol  = ta.sma(volume, flag_cons)
float _poleVol  = ta.sma(volume, flag_pole)[flag_cons]
float _poleMove = close[flag_cons] - close[flag_cons + flag_pole]
float _consRng  = _flagHi - _flagLo
float _consDrift= close - close[flag_cons - 1]        // >0 = drifting up
bool  _tight    = _consRng < flag_rngA * chart_atr
bool  _volDry   = not na(_poleVol) and _poleVol > 0 and _flagVol <= _poleVol * flag_volDry
// Bull flag: up-pole, drift DOWN (or flat), retrace within proportion.
bool _bullPole  = _poleMove >  flag_poleA * chart_atr
bool _bullDrift = (not flag_drift) or _consDrift <= 0
float _poleHi   = ta.highest(high, flag_pole)[flag_cons]
bool _bullProp  = _bullPole and (_poleHi - _flagLo) <= math.abs(_poleMove) * flag_retr   // from the pole's HIGH — a close understates the retrace, letting >50% pullbacks pass as flags
bool bullFlag   = show_flag and d_pat and _tight and _bullPole and _bullDrift and _volDry and _bullProp
// Bear flag: down-pole, drift UP (or flat).
bool _bearPole  = _poleMove < -flag_poleA * chart_atr
bool _bearDrift = (not flag_drift) or _consDrift >= 0
float _poleLo   = ta.lowest(low, flag_pole)[flag_cons]
bool _bearProp  = _bearPole and (_flagHi - _poleLo) <= math.abs(_poleMove) * flag_retr
bool bearFlag   = show_flag and d_pat and _tight and _bearPole and _bearDrift and _volDry and _bearProp

// --- GEOMETRY, from PIVOT SEQUENCES. Two recent pivot highs + two pivot lows tell
// you the shape directly — no line-fitting, so none of the "which two pivots"
// ambiguity that made the auto-fitter unconvergeable. This also yields the
// ascending/descending/symmetrical split Chart Markup never had.
var array<float> gphy = array.new<float>()
var array<float> gply = array.new<float>()
float _gph = ta.pivothigh(high, geo_pv, geo_pv)
float _gpl = ta.pivotlow(low,  geo_pv, geo_pv)
var array<int> gpxh = array.new<int>()
var array<int> gpxl = array.new<int>()
if not na(_gph)
    array.push(gphy, _gph)
    array.push(gpxh, bar_index - geo_pv)
    if array.size(gphy) > 6
        array.shift(gphy)
        array.shift(gpxh)
if not na(_gpl)
    array.push(gply, _gpl)
    array.push(gpxl, bar_index - geo_pv)
    if array.size(gply) > 6
        array.shift(gply)
        array.shift(gpxl)
string geom = "—"
// #59: geometry connector lines — cleared each bar, redrawn below only when a fresh
// shape is classified, so the named shape is drawn (not phantom) and never goes stale.
// #31: a Range / rectangle is drawn as a BOX instead of two lines.
var line _geoHi = na
var line _geoLo = na
var box  _geoBox = na
line.delete(_geoHi)
line.delete(_geoLo)
box.delete(_geoBox)
_geoHi := na
_geoLo := na
_geoBox := na
bool _geoFresh = array.size(gpxh) >= 2 and array.size(gpxl) >= 2 and bar_index - math.min(array.get(gpxh, array.size(gpxh) - 2), array.get(gpxl, array.size(gpxl) - 2)) <= geo_maxage
if show_geom and d_pat and _geoFresh and array.size(gphy) >= 2 and array.size(gply) >= 2
    float _h1 = array.get(gphy, array.size(gphy) - 1)   // most recent high
    float _h2 = array.get(gphy, array.size(gphy) - 2)
    float _l1 = array.get(gply, array.size(gply) - 1)   // most recent low
    float _l2 = array.get(gply, array.size(gply) - 2)
    float _ft = geo_flat * chart_atr
    bool _hFlat = math.abs(_h1 - _h2) <= _ft
    bool _lFlat = math.abs(_l1 - _l2) <= _ft
    bool _hDown = not _hFlat and _h1 < _h2
    bool _hUp   = not _hFlat and _h1 > _h2
    bool _lUp   = not _lFlat and _l1 > _l2
    bool _lDown = not _lFlat and _l1 < _l2
    // if/else rather than a wrapped ternary: Pine requires a continuation line to be
    // indented by a NON-multiple of 4 (4/8/12 read as a new block), which a wrapped
    // ternary trips over silently. The shape reads better as a ladder anyway.
    if _hFlat and _lFlat
        geom := "Range / rectangle"
    else if _hFlat and _lUp
        geom := "Ascending triangle"
    else if _hDown and _lFlat
        geom := "Descending triangle"
    else if _hDown and _lUp
        geom := "Symmetrical triangle"
    else if _hUp and _lUp
        geom := "Rising channel / wedge"
    else if _hDown and _lDown
        geom := "Falling channel / wedge"
    else if _hUp and _lDown
        geom := "Broadening"
    else if _hFlat and _lDown
        geom := "Broadening (descending)"
    else if _hUp and _lFlat
        geom := "Broadening (ascending)"
    // #59/#31: draw the classification. A Range / rectangle → a BOX (flat top/bottom at
    // the mean of the two highs / two lows, spanning from the earliest pivot, extended
    // right). Every other shape → the two pivot connectors that produced it.
    if drawGeomLines and geom != "—"
        int _xh1 = array.get(gpxh, array.size(gpxh) - 1)
        int _xh2 = array.get(gpxh, array.size(gpxh) - 2)
        int _xl1 = array.get(gpxl, array.size(gpxl) - 1)
        int _xl2 = array.get(gpxl, array.size(gpxl) - 2)
        if geom == "Range / rectangle"
            int _bxL = math.min(math.min(_xh1, _xh2), math.min(_xl1, _xl2))
            float _bxT = (_h1 + _h2) / 2.0
            float _bxB = (_l1 + _l2) / 2.0
            _geoBox := box.new(_bxL, _bxT, bar_index, _bxB, xloc=xloc.bar_index, border_color=color.new(#9598a1, 10), border_width=1, border_style=line.style_dashed, bgcolor=color.new(#9598a1, 92), extend=extend.right)
        else
            _geoHi := line.new(_xh2, _h2, _xh1, _h1, xloc=xloc.bar_index, color=color.new(#9598a1, 20), width=1, extend=extend.right, style=line.style_dashed)
            _geoLo := line.new(_xl2, _l2, _xl1, _l1, xloc=xloc.bar_index, color=color.new(#9598a1, 20), width=1, extend=extend.right, style=line.style_dashed)

string pats = bullFlag ? "Bull flag" : bearFlag ? "Bear flag" : ""
string pa_names = is_rec ? ((kCLIMAX?"Climax, ":"")+(kSPR?"Spring, ":"")+(k2B?"HigherLow-2B, ":"")+(kSOS?"BaseBO-SOS, ":"")+(kENG?"Engulf, ":"")+(kHSUP?"Hammer-sup, ":"")+(k3B?"3BarRev, ":"")+(kPP?"Pocket, ":"")+(kVDU?"VDU, ":"")+(kRECLAIM?"30WMA-reclaim, ":"")) : ((kHTF?"HTF, ":"") + (kSC?"StrongClose, ":"") + (kVCP?"VCP-BO, ":"") + (kLAU?"Stage2-Launch, ":"") + (kGAP?"Gap-BO, ":"") + (kBC?"Breakout-Confirmed, ":"") + (kPP?"Pocket, ":"") + (kU50?"Undercut50, ":"") + (kLIQ?"LiqSweep, ":"") + (kSPR?"Spring, ":"") + (kENG?"Engulf, ":"") + (k3B?"3BarRev, ":"") + (kH50?"Hammer50, ":"") + (kH200?"Hammer200, ":"") + (kIN3?"Inside3, ":"") + (kNR7?"NR7, ":"") + (kIBNR7?"IB-NR7, ":""))

// --- TRIGGER = the COMBINED entry gate: Event + Volume + Intraday ---
// Event    = a price-action trigger on the chart (AVWAP bounce / R2G>BO).
// Volume   = relative volume >= rv_floor (participation behind the move).
// Intraday = the 10-EMA reclaim + TTM squeeze fired up (momentum confirmation).
// GO (green) = a trigger fired (Event OR Intraday) AND volume is there — NOT all three at
//   once (that would be a rarely-gettable Holy Grail). Intraday is the premium confirmation.
// Close is inside/near a support level — checked on BOTH Daily and Weekly (v2.1).
// f_inzone: is `close` inside [bot,top] or within 1.5% above `top`? f_nearpiv:
// within 1.5% above a pivot line?
f_inzone(float top, float bot) => not na(top) and ((close >= bot and close <= top) or (close > top and (close - top) / top <= 0.015))
f_nearpiv(float p) => not na(p) and close >= p and (close - p) / p <= 0.015
f_nearlvl(float f) => not na(f) and close > 0 and math.abs(close - f) / close <= 0.015
// v3.0: OB is REMOVED as a support source — the Institutional demand/supply zones
// (z_inDZ, from the Zone Engine above) replace it (#8). FVG + pivot lines
// ("other S/R key levels") are KEPT. Only FRESH (untested) zones count.
bool in_d_fvg = f_inzone(d_fvg_top, d_fvg_bot) and nz(d_fvg_tested, 0.0) < 0.5
bool in_d_piv = f_nearpiv(d_pivot)
bool in_w_fvg = f_inzone(w_fvg_top, w_fvg_bot) and nz(w_fvg_tested, 0.0) < 0.5
bool in_w_piv = f_nearpiv(w_pivot)
// v2.0: an AVWAP support is ALSO an automated demand level — an AVWAP bounce (ev_ok)
// happens AT one by definition, so counting it here stops require_support from
// suppressing a valid AVWAP entry that isn't also sitting on a zone/FVG/pivot.
bool near_avwap = not na(nearest_sup) and close >= nearest_sup and (close - nearest_sup) / close <= 0.015
// #10: EMA20 as DYNAMIC support — price sitting just above the EMA20 anchor.
bool near_ema = not na(dyn_ema) and close >= dyn_ema and (close - dyn_ema) / dyn_ema <= 0.015
// #11b: Fibonacci retracement of the last ~120-bar swing — INDICATION ONLY (never
// gates). 38.2 / 50 / 61.8 of the swing high→low. `near_fib`/`fib_tag` are shown
// in the Support Zone panel row but are NOT part of support_pass.
float _fibHi = ta.highest(high, 120)
float _fibLo = ta.lowest(low, 120)
float _fibRng = _fibHi - _fibLo
float fib382 = _fibHi - _fibRng * 0.382
float fib50  = _fibHi - _fibRng * 0.500
float fib618 = _fibHi - _fibRng * 0.618
string fib_tag = f_nearlvl(fib618) ? "61.8" : f_nearlvl(fib50) ? "50" : f_nearlvl(fib382) ? "38.2" : ""
bool near_fib = fib_tag != ""

// ---- Nearest S/R LEVEL each side, manual-over-auto, TF-tagged ----------------
// Resolution order per TF: if you marked that TF, YOUR levels are the only ones
// considered for it (Gate 2 — your hand-drawn levels ARE the location layer). A TF
// you left blank falls back to its auto pair. An MTTWR level is EXCLUDED from
// support: it is spent as a floor, and leaning a stop on a level that is primed to
// break is exactly the mistake the grade exists to prevent.
f_srBelow(float acc, float px) => (not na(px) and px > 0 and px < close) ? (na(acc) ? px : math.max(acc, px)) : acc
f_srAbove(float acc, float px) => (not na(px) and px > 0 and px > close) ? (na(acc) ? px : math.min(acc, px)) : acc
f_srAutoBelow(float acc, SRSig s, bool tfOk, bool tfShow, bool hasMan) =>
    float r = acc
    if d_sr and tfOk and tfShow and not hasMan and not na(s)
        r := s.b1t < mttwrEff ? f_srBelow(r, s.b1) : r
        r := s.b2t < mttwrEff ? f_srBelow(r, s.b2) : r
        // RE-HOME: slots split against the HTF close; on historical bars a level
        // crossed mid-period sits in the "above" slot though now below chart price.
        // f_srBelow re-filters px < close, so live this is a no-op.
        r := s.a1t < mttwrEff ? f_srBelow(r, s.a1) : r
        r := s.a2t < mttwrEff ? f_srBelow(r, s.a2) : r
    r
f_srAutoAbove(float acc, SRSig s, bool tfOk, bool tfShow, bool hasMan) =>
    float r = acc
    if d_sr and tfOk and tfShow and not hasMan and not na(s)
        r := s.a1t < mttwrEff ? f_srAbove(r, s.a1) : r
        r := s.a2t < mttwrEff ? f_srAbove(r, s.a2) : r
        r := s.b1t < mttwrEff ? f_srAbove(r, s.b1) : r    // re-home — see the below mirror
        r := s.b2t < mttwrEff ? f_srAbove(r, s.b2) : r
    r

float sr_below = na
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(mv1, useLvM) ? mv1 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(mv2, useLvM) ? mv2 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(mv3, useLvM) ? mv3 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(mv4, useLvM) ? mv4 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(wv1, useLvW) ? wv1 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(wv2, useLvW) ? wv2 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(wv3, useLvW) ? wv3 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(wv4, useLvW) ? wv4 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(dv1, useLvD) ? dv1 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(dv2, useLvD) ? dv2 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(dv3, useLvD) ? dv3 : na)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, f_lvOn(dv4, useLvD) ? dv4 : na)
// A trendline is just a level whose price moves — once projected to this bar it is
// offered to BOTH sides like any other, and self-selects by which side of price it
// sits on (a support TL that price has broken below IS resistance now).
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, tls_now)
sr_below := f_srBelow(sr_below, tlr_now)
sr_below := f_srAutoBelow(sr_below, srM, useLvM, sr_show_M, manM)
sr_below := f_srAutoBelow(sr_below, srW, useLvW, sr_show_W, manW)
sr_below := f_srAutoBelow(sr_below, srD, useLvD, sr_show_D, manD)

float sr_above = na
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(mv1, useLvM) ? mv1 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(mv2, useLvM) ? mv2 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(mv3, useLvM) ? mv3 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(mv4, useLvM) ? mv4 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(wv1, useLvW) ? wv1 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(wv2, useLvW) ? wv2 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(wv3, useLvW) ? wv3 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(wv4, useLvW) ? wv4 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(dv1, useLvD) ? dv1 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(dv2, useLvD) ? dv2 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(dv3, useLvD) ? dv3 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, f_lvOn(dv4, useLvD) ? dv4 : na)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, tls_now)
sr_above := f_srAbove(sr_above, tlr_now)
sr_above := f_srAutoAbove(sr_above, srM, useLvM, sr_show_M, manM)
sr_above := f_srAutoAbove(sr_above, srW, useLvW, sr_show_W, manW)
sr_above := f_srAutoAbove(sr_above, srD, useLvD, sr_show_D, manD)

// Which TF did the winning SUPPORT come from? This is the point of the whole TF
// split: a stop on a WEEKLY level is a deeper distal → wider stop → SIZE DOWN
// (Gate 4). Reading a stop without its level's weight is how a position is
// mis-sized. Ties resolve UP — conviction takes the higher reading, never the lower.
f_srTf(float lvl) =>
    string t = ""
    if not na(lvl)
        // A manual TRENDLINE carries its own TF tag and must be checked FIRST —
        // otherwise it would fall through to the "D" default and a Weekly trendline
        // would report as a Daily level, understating the stop's weight (Gate 4).
        if tls_live and lvl == tls_now
            t := tls_tfTag
        else if tlr_live and lvl == tlr_now
            t := tlr_tfTag
        else
            bool isM = (f_lvOn(mv1,useLvM) and mv1==lvl) or (f_lvOn(mv2,useLvM) and mv2==lvl) or (f_lvOn(mv3,useLvM) and mv3==lvl) or (f_lvOn(mv4,useLvM) and mv4==lvl) or (not na(srM) and useLvM and sr_show_M and not manM and (srM.a1==lvl or srM.a2==lvl or srM.b1==lvl or srM.b2==lvl))
            bool isW = (f_lvOn(wv1,useLvW) and wv1==lvl) or (f_lvOn(wv2,useLvW) and wv2==lvl) or (f_lvOn(wv3,useLvW) and wv3==lvl) or (f_lvOn(wv4,useLvW) and wv4==lvl) or (not na(srW) and useLvW and sr_show_W and not manW and (srW.a1==lvl or srW.a2==lvl or srW.b1==lvl or srW.b2==lvl))
            t := isM ? "M" : isW ? "W" : "D"
    t
// Is this level one of YOURS (vs an auto-detected one)?
f_srIsMan(float lvl) =>
    bool m = false
    if not na(lvl)
        m := (tls_live and lvl == tls_now) or (tlr_live and lvl == tlr_now) or (f_lvOn(mv1,useLvM) and mv1==lvl) or (f_lvOn(mv2,useLvM) and mv2==lvl) or (f_lvOn(mv3,useLvM) and mv3==lvl) or (f_lvOn(mv4,useLvM) and mv4==lvl) or (f_lvOn(wv1,useLvW) and wv1==lvl) or (f_lvOn(wv2,useLvW) and wv2==lvl) or (f_lvOn(wv3,useLvW) and wv3==lvl) or (f_lvOn(wv4,useLvW) and wv4==lvl) or (f_lvOn(dv1,useLvD) and dv1==lvl) or (f_lvOn(dv2,useLvD) and dv2==lvl) or (f_lvOn(dv3,useLvD) and dv3==lvl) or (f_lvOn(dv4,useLvD) and dv4==lvl)
    m
// Is this level a TRENDLINE? Worth saying out loud in the panel: a stop under a
// rising trendline behaves differently from one under a horizontal shelf — it moves.
f_srIsTl(float lvl) => not na(lvl) and ((tls_live and lvl == tls_now) or (tlr_live and lvl == tlr_now))
// Format one side for the panel: price · TF [· TL|man] (± distance).
f_srTxt(float lvl) =>
    na(lvl) ? "—" : str.tostring(lvl, format.mintick) + " ·" + f_srTf(lvl) + (f_srIsTl(lvl) ? "·TL" : f_srIsMan(lvl) ? "·man" : "")

// Price sitting just above a fresh S/R level = at location, same 1.5% band the
// AVWAP/EMA20 dynamic supports use.
bool near_sr = not na(sr_below) and close >= sr_below and (close - sr_below) / close <= 0.015

bool in_daily_zone  = in_d_fvg or in_d_piv
bool in_weekly_zone = in_w_fvg or in_w_piv
// v3.0 (#11): the Trigger's support consideration = FRESH demand zone (#8) OR FVG
// OR pivot S/R OR AVWAP OR the EMA20 dynamic S/R (#10). Fibs are indication-only.
// v3.2: + a fresh horizontal S/R level (near_sr). NOTE this LOOSENS the GO gate —
// support_pass gains a source, so GO fires on names it previously skipped. That is
// intended (a marked level IS a location), but it is a SIGNAL change, not a drawing
// change: expect more GOs than v3.1.
// near_sr already covers the manual trendline: tls_now/tlr_now are projected into
// the sr_below pool above, so a trendline IS a level for the gate's purposes. No
// separate term here — one source of truth for "am I at a location".
bool inside_support_zone = (d_zones and z_inDZ) or (d_lvls and (in_daily_zone or in_weekly_zone)) or (d_avwap and near_avwap) or near_ema or near_sr
bool support_pass = (not require_support) or inside_support_zone

float vol_sma_50 = ta.sma(volume, 50)
float _v50p = vol_sma_50[1]      // prior-bar average: a 5x volume bar must not inflate its own baseline (~8% RV understatement exactly at the floor)
float chart_rv = _v50p > 0 ? volume / _v50p : 0.0
float swingLo10 = ta.lowest(low, 10)   // recent swing low for the structural Plan SL (hoisted; ta.* can't run in the panel's conditional)
// v2.9: the volume gate uses the TRADING-TIMEFRAME RV (chart_rv) — the exact number
// now shown in the panel RV row — so the gate and the display can NEVER disagree.
// (Was a mix of yesterday's confirmed daily RV and chart RV, which let the panel
// show one RV while the gate tested another.)
bool vol_ok = chart_rv >= rv_floor

bool ev_ok    = avwap_trig
bool intra_ok = intraday_trig
bool timing_ok = ev_ok or intra_ok      // optional TIMING refinement (AVWAP / intraday)
// TRIGGER-BAR QUALITY (B): the GO candle must CLOSE STRONG — green, or a red bar that
// still closed in the UPPER HALF of its range (a shakeout that recovered is OK). A bar
// that closes in the LOWER half (a sold-off / distribution / upthrust candle) is vetoed
// — this blocks the case where a structural pattern (3-Bar, VCP, BC) fires on a big red
// bar that spiked to a new high then closed weak (a failed breakout). Lenient per Jay:
//   bar_ok = green OR close in the upper half of the bar's range.
float _bqRng   = high - low
float _bqClpos = _bqRng > 0 ? (close - low) / _bqRng : 0.5
bool  bar_ok   = close >= open or _bqClpos >= 0.5
// #1 SIGNAL = PA. GO now requires a PA-battery pattern (from the current Bull/Recovery
// mode) to have fired, AT a valid location (support), WITH volume, on a clean bar (B).
// The AVWAP/intraday triggers are no longer required — shown as optional timing (⏱). So
// flipping Bull↔Recovery changes the signal, and the trade signal comes from the PA.
bool go       = any_pa and support_pass and vol_ok and bar_ok

// ==========================================================================
// ARRIVAL STYLE + ORDER-FLOW DELTA (computed before the confluence block so the
// two reads can feed it). request.security_lower_tf runs at GLOBAL scope only.
// ==========================================================================
// Intrabar up/down volume: each sub-bar's volume counted as buy (closed up) or
// sell (closed down); this chart bar's delta = sum(up) - sum(down). Degrades to 0
// (neutral) if the lower-TF data is unavailable.
array<float> _ofUp = request.security_lower_tf(syminfo.tickerid, of_ltf, close > open ? volume : 0.0)
array<float> _ofDn = request.security_lower_tf(syminfo.tickerid, of_ltf, close < open ? volume : 0.0)
float bar_delta = nz(array.sum(_ofUp)) - nz(array.sum(_ofDn))

// Which zone (if any) price is interacting with right now — arrival is only meaningful at one.
bool  _inDmd = z_inDZ
bool  _inSup = z_inSZ and not z_inDZ
// The approach leg: from the recent swing extreme into the zone. Demand = the drop
// from the swing HIGH to the current low; supply = the rally from the swing LOW.
float _swHiA = ta.highest(high, arr_look)
float _swLoA = ta.lowest(low,  arr_look)
int   _hiAgo = math.max(math.abs(ta.highestbars(high, arr_look)), 1)
int   _loAgo = math.max(math.abs(ta.lowestbars(low,  arr_look)), 1)
int   arr_bars = _inSup ? _loAgo : _hiAgo
float arr_dist = _inSup ? (high - _swLoA) : (_swHiA - low)
// Velocity in ATR/bar — the core Arrival-Style metric.
float arr_vel  = (chart_atr > 0 and arr_bars > 0 and (arr_dist > 0)) ? (arr_dist / chart_atr) / arr_bars : na
string arr_style = (not (_inDmd or _inSup)) ? "—" : na(arr_vel) ? "—" : arr_vel >= arr_vel_fast ? "FAST" : arr_vel <= arr_vel_slow ? "GRIND" : "NORMAL"

// Order-flow read: sum the last of_win bar deltas, plus a delta-divergence check.
float of_delta = 0.0
for _di = 0 to of_win - 1
    of_delta := of_delta + nz(bar_delta[_di])
// Bullish divergence at demand: price made a LOWER low but delta made a HIGHER low
// (sellers pushed price down on shrinking net supply — absorption). Mirror at supply.
bool _bullDiv = _inDmd and low < nz(low[of_win], low) and of_delta > nz(of_delta[of_win])
bool _bearDiv = _inSup and high > nz(high[of_win], high) and of_delta < nz(of_delta[of_win])
bool of_absorb = _inDmd ? (of_delta > 0 or _bullDiv) : _inSup ? (of_delta < 0 or _bearDiv) : false
string of_read = _inDmd ? (of_absorb ? "absorbing Δ+" : of_delta < 0 ? "bleeding Δ−" : "neutral Δ") : _inSup ? (of_absorb ? "absorbing Δ−" : "bleeding Δ+") : "—"

// Confluence contributions: a sharp arrival AT a zone, and an absorbing delta.
bool arr_fav = (_inDmd or _inSup) and arr_style == "FAST"

// ==========================================================================
// v3.2 CONFLUENCE SCORE — the things you eyeball, made to COUNT
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Until now AVWAP/intraday were a bare "⏱", Fib was hard-commented "indication
// only, never gates", and the ⚡/controlling/pinch/room tags were labels. They
// were decoration: a 2-confluence GO and an 8-confluence GO rendered identically.
// Now they move a number.
//
// The score GRADES, it does not GATE. GO still fires on P·L·V·B alone — the
// anti-Holy-Grail ruling stands ("GO = (Event OR Intraday) AND Volume — NOT all
// 3"). Requiring more conditions produces a trigger that never fires; that is a
// different failure, not a safer one. The score answers "how strong is this live
// trigger", which is the question the ⏱ was silently refusing to answer.
//
// WEIGHTED BY KIND, because a flat count would be dishonest:
//   TIMING events (+2) — something is HAPPENING right now (AVWAP bounce/reclaim,
//                        intraday leg). These are the entry itself.
//   QUALITY/LOCATION (+1) — something is TRUE about where price is. Necessary
//                        context, but three proximity tags are not worth one real
//                        AVWAP bounce.
// ==========================================================================
// Each term is gated by its layer's master switch: a layer you have taken out of
// service must not keep moving the score from behind a hidden drawing. cf_max is
// gated the same way below, so "8/13" never silently becomes "8 out of a ceiling
// that includes layers you switched off".
int cf = 0
cf := cf + (d_avwap and ev_ok    ? cf_w_avwap : 0)        // AVWAP trigger (timing)
cf := cf + (show_intraday and intra_ok ? cf_w_intra : 0)  // intraday leg (timing; gated by its own switch — the panel said 'off' while the score kept counting it)
cf := cf + (d_zones and z_inDZ_fvg  ? cf_w_fvg   : 0)     // ⚡ zone: leg-out left an imbalance
cf := cf + (d_zones and z_inDZ_ctrl ? cf_w_ctrl  : 0)     // controlling zone = highest-grade demand
cf := cf + (d_sr    and near_sr     ? cf_w_sr    : 0)     // at a FRESH S/R level (MTTWR excluded upstream)
cf := cf + (near_ema             ? cf_w_ema   : 0)        // EMA20 dynamic support (DNA daily anchor)
cf := cf + (d_avwap and near_avwap  ? cf_w_avwl  : 0)     // sitting on an AVWAP
cf := cf + (near_fib             ? cf_w_fib   : 0)        // 38.2/50/61.8 retrace
cf := cf + (d_avwap and pinched   ? cf_w_pinch : 0)       // AVWAPs converging
cf := cf + (chart_rv >= cf_rv_strong ? cf_w_rv : 0)       // volume EXPANDING, not merely present
int _dzTfN = (_dzTfC ? 1 : 0) + (_dzTfD ? 1 : 0) + (_dzTfW ? 1 : 0) + (_dzTfM ? 1 : 0)
cf := cf + (d_zones and _dzTfN >= 2 ? cf_w_mtf : 0)       // a daily zone sitting inside a weekly one
// Price ON the support trendline you drew by hand — a deliberate read, so it counts.
bool near_tl = tls_live and not na(tls_now) and close >= tls_now and (close - tls_now) / close <= 0.015
// Deduped vs near_sr: the projected TL is IN the sr_below pool, so when the TL IS
// the nearest support it already scored cf_w_sr — one location must not score twice.
// It still scores when a DIFFERENT level is nearer (two stacked supports = genuine
// confluence of distinct objects).
bool tl_extra = near_tl and (na(sr_below) or sr_below != tls_now)
cf := cf + (tl_extra ? cf_w_tl   : 0)
// A qualified bull flag. Not in the PA battery, so no double-count with the P gate.
cf := cf + (bullFlag ? cf_w_flag : 0)
// Arrival Style + Order-Flow (gated by show_arrival, so hide = ignore holds).
cf := cf + (show_arrival and arr_fav   ? cf_w_arrival : 0)   // sharp arrival at the zone
cf := cf + (show_arrival and of_absorb ? cf_w_absorb  : 0)   // absorbing delta / bullish divergence
// #10 Daily-battery agreement (MTF grade, intraday charts only): the DAILY battery for
// the ACTIVE path also has a pattern live while the chart-TF trigger fires.
bool _dPAbull = nz(d_sc,0)>0.5 or nz(d_vcp,0)>0.5 or nz(d_pp,0)>0.5 or nz(d_eng,0)>0.5 or nz(d_liq,0)>0.5 or nz(d_3b,0)>0.5 or nz(d_in3,0)>0.5 or nz(d_nr7,0)>0.5 or nz(d_ibnr7,0)>0.5 or nz(d_spr,0)>0.5 or nz(d_gap,0)>0.5 or nz(d_u50,0)>0.5 or nz(d_h50,0)>0.5 or nz(d_h200,0)>0.5 or nz(d_bc,0)>0.5 or nz(d_htf,0)>0.5
bool _dPArec  = nz(d_climax,0)>0.5 or nz(d_spr,0)>0.5 or nz(d_2b,0)>0.5 or nz(d_sos,0)>0.5 or nz(d_eng,0)>0.5 or nz(d_hsup,0)>0.5 or nz(d_3b,0)>0.5 or nz(d_pp,0)>0.5 or nz(d_vdu,0)>0.5
bool daily_pa_agrees = use_chart_tf and timeframe.isintraday and any_pa and (is_rec ? _dPArec : _dPAbull)
cf := cf + (daily_pa_agrees ? cf_w_dailypa : 0)
// #13 Round number (price-scaled step, within 0.3%) — a psychological magnet level.
float _rnStep = close >= 5000 ? 100.0 : close >= 1000 ? 50.0 : close >= 100 ? 10.0 : close >= 10 ? 1.0 : 0.5
bool near_round = math.abs(close - math.round(close / _rnStep) * _rnStep) / close <= 0.003
cf := cf + (near_round ? cf_w_round : 0)
// #3 Over-extension above the daily EMA20 — measured in DAILY ATR to match the daily
// EMA20. BUGFIX (19-Jul, from ABBOTINDIA: verdict read "8.8 ATR" while Price-vs-EMA20
// read "+5.6% Norm"): dividing a DAILY-scale distance by the 75m chart ATR inflated the
// count ~3×. Use atrD_tf (the zone engine's daily ATR) so a 75m chart and a daily chart
// agree, and the ATR read is consistent with the % read.
float _extAtrRef = timeframe.isintraday ? nz(atrD_tf, chart_atr) : chart_atr
float ext_atr = (not na(daily_ema20) and _extAtrRef > 0) ? (close - daily_ema20) / _extAtrRef : na
// The ceiling moves with the weights AND with the layer switches, so "8/13" can
// never mean "8 out of a ceiling that counts layers you turned off" — an
// unreachable maximum would make every score read artificially weak.
int cf_max = (d_avwap ? cf_w_avwap : 0) + (show_intraday ? cf_w_intra : 0) + (d_zones ? cf_w_fvg : 0) + (d_zones ? cf_w_ctrl : 0) + (d_sr ? cf_w_sr : 0) + cf_w_ema + (d_avwap ? cf_w_avwl : 0) + cf_w_fib + (d_avwap ? cf_w_pinch : 0) + cf_w_rv + (d_zones ? cf_w_mtf : 0) + (d_tl ? cf_w_tl : 0) + (d_pat and show_flag ? cf_w_flag : 0) + (show_arrival ? cf_w_arrival : 0) + (show_arrival ? cf_w_absorb : 0) + cf_w_round + ((use_chart_tf and timeframe.isintraday) ? cf_w_dailypa : 0)

// ==========================================================================
// #12 DYNAMIC RISK (ported from Commander_Risk_Allocator_v2.0 §9)
// active_risk% = max(regime_risk × max(vol_discount × kelly, 0.75), 0.25×base)
// ==========================================================================
f_mkt_health() =>
    [mc, m50, m200] = request.security("NSE:CNX500", "D", [close, ta.sma(close, 50), ta.sma(close, 200)], lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)
    not na(mc) and not na(m200) and mc > m200 and m50 > m200
bool mkt_health = f_mkt_health()
// Stage-2 uptrend proxy from the daily battery reads (above 200-DMA, above a rising 150-SMA)
bool  dyn_s2   = nz(d_bel200, 0.0) < 0.5 and nz(d_bel30, 0.0) < 0.5 and nz(d_s150dn, 0.0) < 0.5
bool  dyn_rs   = rsSlope > 0
bool  dyn_vol  = chart_rv > 1.1
int   kelly_pts = (dyn_s2 ? 1 : 0) + (dyn_rs ? 1 : 0) + (dyn_vol ? 1 : 0)
float kelly_mult = kelly_pts >= 3 ? 1.25 : kelly_pts == 2 ? 1.0 : 0.75
float dyn_atr_pct = close > 0 ? nz(atrD_tf, 0.0) / close * 100.0 : 0.0
float vol_disc = dyn_atr_pct > 3.0 ? math.min(3.0 / dyn_atr_pct, 1.0) : 1.0
float regime_risk = mkt_health ? size_risk : math.max(size_risk - 0.25, 0.25 * size_risk)
float active_risk = use_dyn_risk ? math.max(regime_risk * math.max(vol_disc * kelly_mult, 0.75), 0.25 * size_risk) : size_risk
// #2 LAST-CLOSED-CANDLE READ: on the live forming bar (barstate.islast & not confirmed)
// with use_closed_candle ON, shift the DISPLAYED signal to the previous (closed) bar so
// a shortlisted trigger doesn't drop the instant a new bar opens (undeveloped bar / thin
// early volume). The signal then updates only when the current bar CLOSES.
int   _so        = (use_closed_candle and barstate.islast and not barstate.isconfirmed) ? 1 : 0
bool  ev_ok_v    = ev_ok[_so]
bool  intra_ok_v = intra_ok[_so]
bool  timing_v   = timing_ok[_so]
bool  any_pa_v   = any_pa[_so]
bool  vol_ok_v   = vol_ok[_so]
bool  support_v  = support_pass[_so]
bool  go_v       = go[_so]
bool  bar_ok_v   = bar_ok[_so]
bool  avwap_v    = avwap_trig[_so]
float chart_rv_v = chart_rv[_so]
int   tsum_v     = tsum[_so]
bool  is_rec_v   = is_rec[_so]
int   cf_v       = cf[_so]
bool  shared_v   = pa_shared_only[_so]
// TRIGGER row: gate = PA(P) + Location(L) + Volume(V) + clean Bar(B). The confluence
// score GRADES a live GO — "GO ★strong 8/13" vs a bare "GO 2/13". Same gate, but a
// weak GO and a stacked one no longer look identical.
string cf_txt   = show_cf ? ("  " + (go_v and cf_v >= cf_strong ? "★strong " : "") + str.tostring(cf_v) + "/" + str.tostring(cf_max)) : ""
string path_txt = any_pa_v ? (shared_v ? "  ⇄both" : ("  " + (is_rec_v ? "Rec" : "Bull") + "-only")) : ""
string trig_txt = (go_v ? "GO" : not any_pa_v ? "no PA" : not support_v ? "no location" : not vol_ok_v ? "no volume" : "weak/red bar") + "   P" + (any_pa_v?"✓":"·") + " L" + (support_v?"✓":"·") + " V" + (vol_ok_v?"✓":"·") + " B" + (bar_ok_v?"✓":"·") + (timing_v ? "  ⏱" : "") + path_txt + cf_txt
// #61: amber for EVERY waiting state, incl. no-PA (was grey). Matches the STATUS row —
// grey read as "off/inactive"; amber = "live, waiting for the gate". Green only on GO.
color trig_col = go_v ? (cf_v >= cf_strong ? color.new(#00e676,0) : color.new(#26a69a,0)) : color.new(#ff9800,0)
// RV field colour (trading-TF RV): green >=1.25 (strong), amber >=1.0 (average), red <1.0 (thin/dead)
color rv_col = chart_rv_v >= 1.25 ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : chart_rv_v >= 1.0 ? color.new(#ff9800,0) : color.new(#ef5350,0)

// ==========================================
// PLOTS
// ==========================================
// ---- Invisible Candles overlay (chart-level visual, DISPLAY ONLY) ----
// The gap-bridged OHLC the zone engine reads: each bar's open re-anchored at the
// previous close, high/low expanded to cover the gap — so a small-bodied gap day
// shows as the big leg candle it really is. Derivation is IDENTICAL to the eff_*
// series inside f_detectZone / f_structZone, so what you see is what they read.
// To see ONLY these: Chart Settings → Symbol → uncheck Body / Borders / Wick.
// Note this is decoupled from `useInvCandles`, which governs DETECTION.
chart_inv_open = nz(close[1], open)
chart_inv_high = math.max(high, chart_inv_open)
chart_inv_low  = math.min(low,  chart_inv_open)
color _icCol = close >= chart_inv_open ? invCandleUp : invCandleDn
plotcandle(
     drawInvCandles ? chart_inv_open : na,
     drawInvCandles ? chart_inv_high : na,
     drawInvCandles ? chart_inv_low  : na,
     drawInvCandles ? close          : na,
     title       = "Invisible Candles",
     color       = _icCol,
     wickcolor   = _icCol,
     bordercolor = _icCol)

plot(d_avwap ? avwap_low : na, "AVWAP Low",  color=c_low, linewidth=2)
plot(d_avwap ? avwap_bo  : na, "AVWAP BO",   color=c_bo,  linewidth=2)
plot(d_avwap ? avwap_gap : na, "AVWAP Gap",  color=c_gap, linewidth=2)
bgcolor(pinched ? color.new(color.teal, 88) : na, title="Pinch zone")
// #4: the S4 / GO / intraday-leg / PA candle markers only render on the latest 30
// bars — no point cluttering old history with stale triggers.
// #2: when use_closed_candle is ON, markers only appear on CONFIRMED (closed) bars,
// so a forming-bar trigger doesn't flash on then drop when the bar develops.
bool recent30 = (last_bar_index - bar_index) <= 30
bool _mkOK = recent30 and (not use_closed_candle or barstate.isconfirmed)
plotshape(avwap_trig and _mkOK and d_markers,    title="AVWAP trigger",    style=shape.triangleup, location=location.belowbar, color=color.new(#26a69a, 0), size=size.tiny, text="S4")
// v2.9: the on-candle "GO" fires ONLY on the combined gate `go` (= panel TRIGGER
// = GO: a leg fired AND volume >= floor AND price at a fresh support zone) — so a
// chart "GO" ALWAYS means take the trade and can never disagree with the panel.
// v3.2: the marker splits by CONFLUENCE so strength is readable off the chart without
// opening the panel — a stacked GO is a brighter label. Same gate either way; the
// score never decides whether a GO exists, only how strong it is.
plotshape(go and _mkOK and d_markers and cf <  cf_strong, title="S4 GO", style=shape.labelup, location=location.belowbar, color=color.new(#26a69a, 0), textcolor=color.white, size=size.tiny, text="GO")
plotshape(go and _mkOK and d_markers and cf >= cf_strong, title="S4 GO ★strong (high confluence)", style=shape.labelup, location=location.belowbar, color=color.new(#00e676, 0), textcolor=color.black, size=size.small, text="GO★")
// Intraday momentum LEG that fired but the gate is NOT yet met (thin volume / no
// support) — small cyan triangle, NO "GO" text, so it's clearly not a trade.
plotshape(show_intraday and intraday_trig and not go and _mkOK and d_markers, title="Intraday leg (gate not met)", style=shape.triangleup, location=location.belowbar, color=color.new(#00838f, 0), size=size.tiny)
plotshape(show_pa and pa_fire and _mkOK and d_markers, title="Daily PA trigger", style=shape.diamond, location=location.abovebar, color=color.new(#7e57c2, 0), size=size.tiny, text="PA")

// Draw the support zones (v2.4): the LEFT edge is the zone's FORMATION candle
// time (the OB/gap/pivot bar) — so a box begins at the candles that created it,
// not a fixed lookback — and extends RIGHT via extend.right (persists as a
// full-width band on any chart TF). Falls back to a fixed window only if the
// formation time is missing. Daily = dashed/thin, Weekly = solid/thick.
var box d_fvg_box = na
var line d_piv_ln = na
var label d_piv_lbl = na
var line d_pres_ln = na
var label d_pres_lbl = na
var box w_fvg_box = na
var line w_piv_ln = na
var label w_piv_lbl = na
var line w_pres_ln = na
var label w_pres_lbl = na
int _ms_day = 86400000
int _d_left = time - 180 * _ms_day     // fallback window if a formation time is missing
int _w_left = time - 540 * _ms_day
// Left edge = the zone's FORMATION candle time (falls back to the window if na).
int _d_fvg_L  = na(d_fvg_time)     ? _d_left : int(d_fvg_time)
int _d_piv_L  = na(d_piv_time)     ? _d_left : int(d_piv_time)
int _d_pres_L = na(d_piv_res_time) ? _d_left : int(d_piv_res_time)
int _w_fvg_L  = na(w_fvg_time)     ? _w_left : int(w_fvg_time)
int _w_piv_L  = na(w_piv_time)     ? _w_left : int(w_piv_time)
int _w_pres_L = na(w_piv_res_time) ? _w_left : int(w_piv_res_time)

// Tested zones grey out (excluded from the trigger); fresh keep their colour.
bool d_fvg_t = nz(d_fvg_tested, 0.0) > 0.5
bool w_fvg_t = nz(w_fvg_tested, 0.0) > 0.5
color _grey = color.new(color.gray, 88)
color _greyb = color.new(color.gray, 55)

// #1 TF GUARDRAILS: a level only draws when its own TF is >= the chart TF, so LTF
// pivots/FVGs never appear on a HIGHER-TF chart, while HTF ones appear on LOWER TFs.
// Daily levels show on Daily and below; Weekly levels on Weekly and below.
bool showDailyLvl  = chartSec <= dailySec
bool showWeeklyLvl = chartSec <= weeklySec
// #2 label convention (FVG + pivot): 10-space indent, left, vertically centred,
// larger font — matching the zone labels. Pivot lines use a transparent-bubble
// label_right anchored at the formation left so text reads INTO the level.
color _pivBubble = color.new(color.gray, 100)
// ==========================================================================
// S/R LEVELS — render (manual first; auto only where you haven't marked)
// ==========================================================================
if barstate.islast
    // Cleanup is UNCONDITIONAL and up front. Chart Markup kept every delete inside
    // its own `if show_*` gate, so toggling a feature off SKIPPED the delete and
    // froze that drawing on the chart forever — you ended up tuning against ghosts.
    // Deletes belong here; draw calls stay behind their gates.
    if array.size(srLines) > 0
        for i = 0 to array.size(srLines) - 1
            line.delete(array.get(srLines, i))
        array.clear(srLines)
    if array.size(srLbls) > 0
        for i = 0 to array.size(srLbls) - 1
            label.delete(array.get(srLbls, i))
        array.clear(srLbls)

    // MANUAL first — highest TF first so the heavy Monthly line sits under the
    // lighter Weekly/Daily ones rather than burying them.
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(mv1, useLvM) ? mv1 : na, "M", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(mv2, useLvM) ? mv2 : na, "M", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(mv3, useLvM) ? mv3 : na, "M", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(mv4, useLvM) ? mv4 : na, "M", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(wv1, useLvW) ? wv1 : na, "W", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(wv2, useLvW) ? wv2 : na, "W", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(wv3, useLvW) ? wv3 : na, "W", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(wv4, useLvW) ? wv4 : na, "W", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(dv1, useLvD) ? dv1 : na, "D", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(dv2, useLvD) ? dv2 : na, "D", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(dv3, useLvD) ? dv3 : na, "D", 0, 0, false, true)
    f_drawLv(f_lvOn(dv4, useLvD) ? dv4 : na, "D", 0, 0, false, true)
    // AUTO — only on a TF you have NOT marked yourself.
    f_drawAutoTf(srM, "M", useLvM, sr_show_M, manM)
    f_drawAutoTf(srW, "W", useLvW, sr_show_W, manW)
    f_drawAutoTf(srD, "D", useLvD, sr_show_D, manD)

    // --- MANUAL TRENDLINES. Deletes are unconditional and up front (a delete left
    // inside its own `if show_*` gate is how Chart Markup froze drawings on the
    // chart forever). Width by TF, same conviction encoding as the levels.
    line.delete(lnTlS)
    line.delete(lnTlR)
    label.delete(lbTlS)
    label.delete(lbTlR)
    if tls_live
        int _wS = tls_tfTag == "M" ? 3 : tls_tfTag == "W" ? 2 : 1
        lnTlS := line.new(tls_t1, tls_p1, time, tls_now, xloc=xloc.bar_time, color=color.new(#26a69a, 0), width=_wS)   // ends AT the label anchor (collinear by construction) — extend.right ran the ray through the label text
        lbTlS := label.new(time, tls_now, tls_tfTag + " · TL support  " + str.tostring(tls_now, format.mintick), xloc=xloc.bar_time, style=label.style_label_left, color=color.new(#26a69a, 82), textcolor=color.new(#26a69a, 0), size=size.small)
    if tlr_live
        int _wR = tlr_tfTag == "M" ? 3 : tlr_tfTag == "W" ? 2 : 1
        lnTlR := line.new(tlr_t1, tlr_p1, time, tlr_now, xloc=xloc.bar_time, color=color.new(#ef5350, 0), width=_wR)
        lbTlR := label.new(time, tlr_now, tlr_tfTag + " · TL resistance  " + str.tostring(tlr_now, format.mintick), xloc=xloc.bar_time, style=label.style_label_left, color=color.new(#ef5350, 82), textcolor=color.new(#ef5350, 0), size=size.small)

    // --- PATTERNS: the detected flag, and your manual box. Deletes unconditional.
    box.delete(bxFlag)
    label.delete(lbFlag)
    box.delete(bxMan)
    label.delete(lbMan)
    if (bullFlag or bearFlag) and (not use_closed_candle or barstate.isconfirmed)
        color _fc = bullFlag ? #26a69a : #ef5350
        bxFlag := box.new(bar_index - flag_cons + 1, _flagHi, bar_index, _flagLo, xloc=xloc.bar_index, border_color=color.new(_fc, 40), bgcolor=color.new(_fc, 90), border_width=1)
        lbFlag := label.new(bar_index - flag_cons + 1, _flagHi, (bullFlag ? "Bull" : "Bear") + " flag", xloc=xloc.bar_index, style=label.style_label_down, color=color.new(_fc, 75), textcolor=_fc, size=size.small)
    if box_on and d_pat and box_t1 > 0 and box_t2 > 0 and box_hi > 0.0 and box_lo > 0.0
        bxMan := box.new(box_t1, box_hi, box_t2, box_lo, xloc=xloc.bar_time, border_color=color.new(#ffd54f, 40), bgcolor=color.new(#ffd54f, 90), border_width=1)
        lbMan := label.new(box_t1, box_hi, "Consolidation (manual)", xloc=xloc.bar_time, style=label.style_label_down, color=color.new(#ffd54f, 75), textcolor=#ffd54f, size=size.small)

if show_zones and d_lvls and barstate.islast
    // --- Daily (dashed, thin) — FVG + pivots. Drawn on Daily-and-lower TFs only. ---
    if not na(d_fvg_box)
        box.delete(d_fvg_box)
    if showDailyLvl and not na(d_fvg_top) and not na(d_fvg_bot)
        d_fvg_box := box.new(_d_fvg_L, d_fvg_top, time, d_fvg_bot, xloc=xloc.bar_time, extend=extend.right,
             bgcolor=d_fvg_t ? _grey : color.new(color.orange, 92), border_color=d_fvg_t ? _greyb : color.new(color.orange, 45),
             border_style=line.style_dashed, text=d_fvg_t ? "          Daily FVG (tested)" : "          Daily FVG",
             text_color=d_fvg_t ? color.new(color.gray, 20) : color.new(color.orange, 15),
             text_size=size.small, text_halign=text.align_left, text_valign=text.align_center)
    if not na(d_piv_ln)
        line.delete(d_piv_ln)
    if not na(d_piv_lbl)
        label.delete(d_piv_lbl)
    if showDailyLvl and not na(d_pivot)
        d_piv_ln := line.new(_d_piv_L, d_pivot, time, d_pivot, xloc=xloc.bar_time, extend=extend.right,
             color=color.new(color.blue, 30), style=line.style_dashed, width=1)
        d_piv_lbl := label.new(_d_piv_L, d_pivot, "          Daily Pivot", xloc=xloc.bar_time,
             color=_pivBubble, textcolor=color.new(color.blue, 10),
             style=label.style_label_right, size=size.small, textalign=text.align_left)
    // Daily flipped pivot — previous support, now RESISTANCE (maroon)
    if not na(d_pres_ln)
        line.delete(d_pres_ln)
    if not na(d_pres_lbl)
        label.delete(d_pres_lbl)
    if showDailyLvl and not na(d_piv_res)
        d_pres_ln := line.new(_d_pres_L, d_piv_res, time, d_piv_res, xloc=xloc.bar_time, extend=extend.right,
             color=color.new(color.maroon, 20), style=line.style_dashed, width=1)
        d_pres_lbl := label.new(_d_pres_L, d_piv_res, "          Daily Pivot S→R", xloc=xloc.bar_time,
             color=_pivBubble, textcolor=color.new(color.maroon, 0),
             style=label.style_label_right, size=size.small, textalign=text.align_left)
    // --- Weekly (solid, thick) — FVG + pivots. Drawn on Weekly-and-lower TFs only. ---
    if not na(w_fvg_box)
        box.delete(w_fvg_box)
    if showWeeklyLvl and not na(w_fvg_top) and not na(w_fvg_bot)
        w_fvg_box := box.new(_w_fvg_L, w_fvg_top, time, w_fvg_bot, xloc=xloc.bar_time, extend=extend.right,
             bgcolor=w_fvg_t ? _grey : color.new(color.orange, 84), border_color=w_fvg_t ? _greyb : color.new(color.orange, 5),
             border_width=2, text=w_fvg_t ? "          Weekly FVG (tested)" : "          Weekly FVG",
             text_color=w_fvg_t ? color.new(color.gray, 0) : color.new(color.orange, 0),
             text_size=size.small, text_halign=text.align_left, text_valign=text.align_center)
    if not na(w_piv_ln)
        line.delete(w_piv_ln)
    if not na(w_piv_lbl)
        label.delete(w_piv_lbl)
    if showWeeklyLvl and not na(w_pivot)
        w_piv_ln := line.new(_w_piv_L, w_pivot, time, w_pivot, xloc=xloc.bar_time, extend=extend.right,
             color=color.new(color.blue, 0), style=line.style_solid, width=2)
        w_piv_lbl := label.new(_w_piv_L, w_pivot, "          Weekly Pivot", xloc=xloc.bar_time,
             color=_pivBubble, textcolor=color.new(color.blue, 0),
             style=label.style_label_right, size=size.small, textalign=text.align_left)
    // Weekly flipped pivot — previous support, now RESISTANCE (maroon, solid/thick)
    if not na(w_pres_ln)
        line.delete(w_pres_ln)
    if not na(w_pres_lbl)
        label.delete(w_pres_lbl)
    if showWeeklyLvl and not na(w_piv_res)
        w_pres_ln := line.new(_w_pres_L, w_piv_res, time, w_piv_res, xloc=xloc.bar_time, extend=extend.right,
             color=color.new(color.maroon, 0), style=line.style_solid, width=2)
        w_pres_lbl := label.new(_w_pres_L, w_piv_res, "          Weekly Pivot S→R", xloc=xloc.bar_time,
             color=_pivBubble, textcolor=color.new(color.maroon, 0),
             style=label.style_label_right, size=size.small, textalign=text.align_left)

// ==========================================
// ENTRY PANEL
// ==========================================
f_pos(string p) => p == "top_left" ? position.top_left : p == "bottom_right" ? position.bottom_right : p == "bottom_left" ? position.bottom_left : position.top_right
// Dark-theme panel: solid dark bg + TV grid frame so it reads cleanly on dark charts. Updated to 17 rows.
var table pnl = table.new(f_pos(panel_pos), 2, 30, bgcolor=color.new(#131722, 0), frame_color=color.new(#2a2e39, 0), frame_width=1, border_color=color.new(#2a2e39, 0), border_width=1)
f_row(int r, string k, string vv, color vc) =>
    table.cell(pnl, 0, r, k, text_size=size.small, text_color=color.new(#b2b5be, 0), text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 1, r, vv, text_size=size.small, text_color=vc, text_halign=text.align_right)
// one PA-condition token for the compact grid: name + fired(✓) / quiet(·)
f_it(string nm, bool fired) => nm + (fired ? " ✓  " : " ·  ")

if show_panel and d_panel and barstate.islast
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 0, "S4 ENTRY TRIGGER", text_size=size.small, text_color=color.white, bgcolor=color.new(#00838f, 0))
    table.cell(pnl, 1, 0, syminfo.ticker, text_size=size.small, text_color=color.white, bgcolor=color.new(#00838f, 0), text_halign=text.align_right)
    // AVWAP levels — the three curves on one row (L · BO · Gap). Colour by the KEY
    // one (BO): green when price holds above the breakout AVWAP.
    string _avL = na(avwap_low) ? "-" : str.tostring(avwap_low, format.mintick)
    string _avB = na(avwap_bo)  ? "-" : str.tostring(avwap_bo,  format.mintick)
    string _avG = na(avwap_gap) ? "-" : str.tostring(avwap_gap, format.mintick)
    f_row(1, "AVWAP L·BO·Gap", _avL + " · " + _avB + " · " + _avG, close >= nz(avwap_bo, close) ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : color.new(#ef5350,0))
    f_row(2, "Pinch", pinched ? "YES " + str.tostring(pinch_spread, "0.0") + "%" : (na(pinch_spread) ? "-" : "no " + str.tostring(pinch_spread, "0.0") + "%"), pinched ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : color.gray)
    f_row(3, "AVWAP trigger", avwap_v ? ("FIRED" + (_r2g ? " R2G>BO" : " bounce")) : "waiting", avwap_v ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : color.new(#787b86,0))
    // "Nearest AVWAP" — the nearest AVWAP CURVE below price (a dynamic level that moves
    // each bar), NOT a drawn horizontal S/R line. Renamed from "Nearest support": it was
    // being read as a chart level that isn't there. The horizontal S/R levels live in
    // the "S/R (nearest)" row below — a different, static price-memory engine.
    f_row(4, "Nearest AVWAP", na(nearest_sup) ? "-" : str.tostring(nearest_sup, format.mintick) + " (−" + str.tostring(sup_dist, "0.0") + "%)", na(nearest_sup) ? color.gray : color.new(#42a5f5,0))
    string intra_status = not show_intraday ? "off" : (intra_ok_v ? (require_squeeze ? "GO 10EMA+sqz" : "GO 10EMA") : (ema_reclaim[_so] ? "10EMA ok" : (sqz_on[_so] ? "sqz ON, wait EMA" : "wait")))
    f_row(11, "Intraday " + timeframe.period, intra_status, intra_ok_v ? color.new(#00838f,0) : color.new(#787b86,0))
    
    // Support Zone row — v3.0: demand ZONE (Institutional, #8) + FVG/Pivot + AVWAP +
    // EMA20 dynamic S/R (#10). Fresh DZ reads "DZ" (green); in-zone-but-TESTED reads
    // "DZt" (grey, excluded). A ~ Fib tag (#11b) appends as indication only.
    // reads the last-closed bar ([_so]) so it agrees with the TRIGGER's L flag.
    string _dztag = z_inDZ[_so] ? ("DZ" + (z_inDZ_fvg[_so] ? " ⚡" : "")) : "-"
    string d_zt = in_d_fvg[_so] ? "FVG" : in_d_piv[_so] ? "Piv" : "-"
    string w_zt = in_w_fvg[_so] ? "FVG" : in_w_piv[_so] ? "Piv" : "-"
    string _extra = (near_avwap[_so] ? " AVWAP" : "") + (near_ema[_so] ? " EMA20" : "") + (near_fib[_so] ? " ~Fib" + fib_tag[_so] : "")
    string zone_txt = _dztag + " · D:" + d_zt + " W:" + w_zt + _extra
    color zone_col = inside_support_zone[_so] ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : (near_fib[_so] ? color.new(#42a5f5,0) : color.gray)
    f_row(5, "Support Zone", zone_txt, zone_col)

    // --- Zones (MTF): the TRADEABLE read. What is around price RIGHT NOW, and what
    // is on the chart. The detection funnel that used to live here was troubleshooting
    // instrumentation ("why did that zone vanish"), not a trading input — it is behind
    // `show_diag` on its own row now.
    string _zHere = z_inDZ[_so] ? ("IN DEMAND" + (z_inDZ_ctrl[_so] ? " ★ctrl" : "") + (z_inDZ_fvg[_so] ? " ⚡" : "") + (_dzTfN[_so] >= 2 ? " ×" + str.tostring(_dzTfN[_so]) + "TF" : "")) : z_inSZ[_so] ? "IN SUPPLY" : "between zones"
    string zmtf_txt = _zHere + "  ·  " + str.tostring(zc_dz) + " DZ / " + str.tostring(zc_sz) + " SZ live" + (zc_ctrl > 0 ? " · ★" + str.tostring(zc_ctrl) : "")
    color  zmtf_col = z_inDZ[_so] ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : z_inSZ[_so] ? color.new(#ef5350,0) : color.new(#787b86,0)
    f_row(6, "Zones (MTF)", zmtf_txt, zmtf_col)

    // --- S/R levels: nearest each side, TAGGED WITH THE TIMEFRAME THEY CAME FROM ---
    // The TF is the whole point, not decoration. A stop resting on a WEEKLY level is
    // a deeper distal → wider stop → SIZE DOWN (Gate 4); the same number off a DAILY
    // shelf is a tighter stop and a bigger position. Reading "1718.00 −2.1%" without
    // knowing which is how a position gets mis-sized. "man" = your level, and it
    // outranks the auto pair on that timeframe.
    // The horizontal S/R LEVEL engine (static price memory), distinct from "Nearest
    // AVWAP" above (a dynamic curve). A far distance here is honest, not a bug: on a
    // strong trender there may be no 2-touch level nearby, so the nearest qualified
    // support can be well below. It greys when > 8% away — real, but not a stop you
    // would actually use — so it stops competing visually with an actionable level.
    float _srBd = (not na(sr_below) and close > 0) ? (close - sr_below) / close * 100.0 : na
    string sr_txt = "S " + f_srTxt(sr_below) + (na(sr_below) ? "" : "  (−" + str.tostring(_srBd, "0.0") + "%)") + "   |   R " + f_srTxt(sr_above) + (na(sr_above) ? "" : "  (+" + str.tostring((sr_above - close) / close * 100.0, "0.0") + "%)")
    color sr_col = near_sr ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : (not na(_srBd) and _srBd > 8.0) ? color.gray : color.new(#42a5f5,0)
    f_row(7, "S/R (nearest)", sr_txt, sr_col)

    // --- Pattern (trigger-grade) | Geometry (context). Always written: an unwritten
    // row renders BLANK, which reads as "nothing here" rather than "switched off".
    // Pattern = a DRAWN flag (box on the chart). Geometry = an inferred SHAPE from the
    // last 4 pivots — a context read, NOT a drawn pattern — so it is prefixed "~shape"
    // to stop it reading as something you should see on the chart.
    string _geoTxt = geom[_so] == "—" ? "—" : "~shape: " + geom[_so]
    string _patTxt = not d_pat ? "off" : ((str.length(pats[_so]) > 0 ? pats[_so] : "no flag") + "   |   " + _geoTxt)
    f_row(10, "Pattern | Shape", _patTxt, not d_pat ? color.gray : str.length(pats[_so]) > 0 ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : geom[_so] != "—" ? color.new(#42a5f5,0) : color.gray)

    // --- Confluence breakdown: WHICH ones fired, not just how many. A bare score
    // is its own kind of black box — this is the row that replaces eyeballing.
    string cfb = (ev_ok[_so] ? "AVWAP " : "") + (show_intraday and intra_ok[_so] ? "Intra " : "") + (z_inDZ_fvg[_so] ? "⚡ " : "") + (z_inDZ_ctrl[_so] ? "Ctrl " : "") + (near_sr[_so] ? "S/R " : "") + (tl_extra[_so] ? "TL " : "") + (bullFlag[_so] ? "Flag " : "") + (near_ema[_so] ? "EMA20 " : "") + (near_avwap[_so] ? "AVWL " : "") + (near_fib[_so] ? "Fib " : "") + (pinched[_so] ? "Pinch " : "") + (chart_rv[_so] >= cf_rv_strong ? "RV+ " : "") + (near_round[_so] ? "Rnd " : "") + (daily_pa_agrees[_so] ? "D-PA " : "") + (show_arrival and arr_fav[_so] ? "Arrival " : "") + (show_arrival and of_absorb[_so] ? "Δ+ " : "") + (_dzTfN[_so] >= 2 ? "MTF×" + str.tostring(_dzTfN[_so]) : "")
    f_row(13, "Confluence " + (show_cf ? str.tostring(cf_v) + "/" + str.tostring(cf_max) : ""), not show_cf ? "off" : str.length(cfb) == 0 ? "—" : cfb, not show_cf ? color.gray : cf_v >= cf_strong ? color.new(#00e676,0) : cf_v > 0 ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : color.gray)

    // ARRIVAL · Δ (row 26) — how price arrived at the zone (velocity) + intrabar
    // volume-delta absorption read. "— (not at a zone)" when price is in open space.
    if show_arrival
        string _arS = arr_style[_so]
        bool   _arF = arr_fav[_so]
        bool   _arA = of_absorb[_so]
        string _arrTxt = (_arS == "—") ? "— (not at a zone)" : (_arS + (na(arr_vel[_so]) ? "" : " " + str.tostring(arr_vel[_so], "0.00") + " ATR/bar") + " · " + of_read[_so])
        color  _arrCol = (_arS == "—") ? color.gray : (_arF and _arA) ? color.new(#00e676,0) : _arA ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : (_arS == "GRIND") ? color.new(#ff9800,0) : color.new(#9598a1,0)
        f_row(14, "Arrival · Δ", _arrTxt, _arrCol)

    // --- Room for Trade (#5 merged, #9): distance to the nearest OPPOSING overhead —
    // considered across HTF SUPPLY ZONES, flipped-pivot RESISTANCE and the HTF pivot
    // high. Shows the v67-style verdict (BLUE SKY / CLEAR / ⚠ NO ROOM) + the room in
    // % + the risk multiple (reward-to-overhead / demand-zone width; flags >= 2R).
    // v3.2 AUDIT FIX: Room reads the SAME [_so]-shifted bar as the Plan and the
    // TRIGGER row. It previously read the FORMING bar while the Plan read the closed
    // one — two adjacent panel rows describing different bars.
    float _cl_r   = close[_so]
    float _atr_r  = chart_atr[_so]
    float _dzprox = z_inDZ[_so] ? z_inDZprox[_so] : z_nearDZprox[_so]
    float _dzdist = z_inDZ[_so] ? z_inDZdist[_so] : z_nearDZdist[_so]
    float _dzW    = (not na(_dzprox) and not na(_dzdist)) ? math.abs(_dzprox - _dzdist) : na
    float _band_r = szBandTop[_so]
    bool  _inSZ_r = z_inSZ[_so]
    // Combined overhead = the FIRST thing above price that actually stops it, across
    // {the merged supply band price is inside, the nearest supply zone above, the
    //  nearest S/R level above, flipped pivot S→R (D/W), the HTF pivot high}.
    // v3.2 added two sources that were missing and produced a false "BLUE SKY":
    //   • szBandTop — if price is INSIDE supply, the obstacle is the band's DISTAL.
    //     Previously a zone CONTAINING price contributed nothing at all.
    //   • sr_above  — the S/R level engine was wired into the support gate, the plan
    //     and the score, but NOT into Room, so overhead resistances were invisible.
    float _ovh = na
    if not na(_band_r) and _band_r > _cl_r
        _ovh := _band_r
    if not na(z_nearSZprox[_so]) and z_nearSZprox[_so] > _cl_r and (na(_ovh) or z_nearSZprox[_so] < _ovh)
        _ovh := z_nearSZprox[_so]
    if not na(sr_above[_so]) and sr_above[_so] > _cl_r and (na(_ovh) or sr_above[_so] < _ovh)
        _ovh := sr_above[_so]
    if not na(d_piv_res[_so]) and d_piv_res[_so] > _cl_r and (na(_ovh) or d_piv_res[_so] < _ovh)
        _ovh := d_piv_res[_so]
    if not na(w_piv_res[_so]) and w_piv_res[_so] > _cl_r and (na(_ovh) or w_piv_res[_so] < _ovh)
        _ovh := w_piv_res[_so]
    if not na(lastPH[_so]) and lastPH[_so] > _cl_r and (na(_ovh) or lastPH[_so] < _ovh)
        _ovh := lastPH[_so]
    // SECOND overhead = Target 2. Same sources as _ovh, the next one up. Stays na when
    // the first obstacle is the last known one — T2 then reads "open", not a guess.
    float _ovh2 = na
    if not na(_ovh)
        if not na(_band_r) and _band_r > _ovh and (na(_ovh2) or _band_r < _ovh2)
            _ovh2 := _band_r
        if not na(z_nearSZprox[_so]) and z_nearSZprox[_so] > _ovh and (na(_ovh2) or z_nearSZprox[_so] < _ovh2)
            _ovh2 := z_nearSZprox[_so]
        if not na(sr_above[_so]) and sr_above[_so] > _ovh and (na(_ovh2) or sr_above[_so] < _ovh2)
            _ovh2 := sr_above[_so]
        if not na(d_piv_res[_so]) and d_piv_res[_so] > _ovh and (na(_ovh2) or d_piv_res[_so] < _ovh2)
            _ovh2 := d_piv_res[_so]
        if not na(w_piv_res[_so]) and w_piv_res[_so] > _ovh and (na(_ovh2) or w_piv_res[_so] < _ovh2)
            _ovh2 := w_piv_res[_so]
        if not na(lastPH[_so]) and lastPH[_so] > _ovh and (na(_ovh2) or lastPH[_so] < _ovh2)
            _ovh2 := lastPH[_so]
    float _rf_entry = not na(_dzprox) ? _dzprox : _cl_r
    // Risk floor: a hairline zone must not print unlimited R. Without it a 0.1%-wide
    // zone drove _roomR toward infinity and painted "38R" in green.
    float _rf_risk  = (not na(_dzW) and _dzW > 0) ? math.max(_dzW, _atr_r * 0.5) : _atr_r * 2.5
    float _rf_t1    = _rf_entry + _rf_risk * 2.0
    float _roomR    = (not na(_ovh) and _rf_risk > 0) ? (_ovh - _rf_entry) / _rf_risk : na
    string _rtag    = na(_roomR) ? "" : " · " + str.tostring(_roomR, "0.0") + "R"
    string room_txt = "CLEAR"
    color  room_col = color.new(#26a69a,0)
    if na(_ovh)
        // Reachable only when NOTHING is overhead — which INCLUDES a genuine breakout
        // above everything. (The old separate "CLEAR (BO)" branch was unreachable:
        // every _ovh source is filtered > close, so _ovh is never <= close.)
        room_txt := "BLUE SKY 🚀"
    else
        float _distOvh = (_ovh - _cl_r) / _cl_r * 100.0
        // IN SUPPLY is its own verdict, never a flavour of "clear". Price inside a
        // supply band is the WORST location, not the best: the proximal is behind
        // you and the whole band has to be absorbed before there is any room at all.
        // Show what has to be cleared, and the R to it, so the size decision is made
        // against the real obstacle rather than against open sky.
        if _inSZ_r and not na(_band_r) and _ovh >= _band_r - _atr_r * 0.01
            room_txt := "⛔ IN SUPPLY · clear " + str.tostring(_band_r, format.mintick) + " (+" + str.tostring((_band_r - _cl_r) / _cl_r * 100.0, "0.0") + "%)" + _rtag
            room_col := color.new(#ef5350,0)
        else if _inSZ_r
            // Something stops price BEFORE the band's ceiling — report that, and say
            // the band is still overhead behind it.
            room_txt := "⛔ IN SUPPLY · first " + str.tostring(_ovh, format.mintick) + " (+" + str.tostring(_distOvh, "0.0") + "%)" + _rtag + " · band to " + str.tostring(_band_r, format.mintick)
            room_col := color.new(#ef5350,0)
        else if _rf_t1 > _ovh
            room_txt := "⚠️ NO ROOM " + str.tostring(_distOvh, "0.0") + "%" + _rtag
            room_col := color.new(#ff9800,0)
        else
            room_txt := "CLEAR " + str.tostring(_distOvh, "0.0") + "%" + _rtag
            room_col := (not na(_roomR) and _roomR >= 2.0) ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : _distOvh < 5.0 ? color.new(#ff9800,0) : color.new(#26a69a,0)
    f_row(9, "Room for Trade", room_txt, room_col)
    // #1 (Jay, 19-Jul): if the panel/verdict cites a level to clear ("must clear
    // 1439.95"), that level must be ON THE CHART — sensing a level and not drawing
    // it forces a manual hunt. Draw the binding obstacle: the supply-band ceiling
    // when price is inside supply, else the nearest overhead when it blocks room.
    var line  _obsLn  = na
    var label _obsLbl = na
    line.delete(_obsLn)
    label.delete(_obsLbl)
    _obsLn  := na
    _obsLbl := na
    float _obsLvl = _inSZ_r and not na(_band_r) ? _band_r : (not na(_ovh) and _rf_t1 > _ovh ? _ovh : na)
    if not na(_obsLvl)
        _obsLn  := line.new(bar_index - 20, _obsLvl, bar_index, _obsLvl, xloc=xloc.bar_index, extend=extend.right, color=color.new(#ef5350, 15), width=2, style=line.style_dashed)
        _obsLbl := label.new(bar_index, _obsLvl, "clear " + str.tostring(_obsLvl, format.mintick), xloc=xloc.bar_index, style=label.style_label_left, color=color.new(#ef5350, 80), textcolor=color.new(#ef5350, 0), size=size.small)

    // --- Price vs EMA20 proximity (#10; daily EMA20 anchor on 75/125m, chart on Daily) ---
    float _useEma = dyn_ema
    string _emaLbl = timeframe.isintraday ? "Price vs EMA20 (D)" : "Price vs EMA20"
    string ema_txt = "-"
    color  ema_col = color.gray
    if not na(_useEma)
        float _emaDist = close != 0 ? (close - _useEma) / close * 100.0 : 0.0
        float _absDist = math.abs(_emaDist)
        string _ext = _absDist > 15.0 ? "OvrExt" : "Norm"
        if high > _useEma and close < _useEma
            ema_txt := "RESISTANCE (hit head)"
            ema_col := color.new(#ef5350,0)
        else if low < _useEma and close > _useEma
            ema_txt := "SUPPORT (bounced)"
            ema_col := color.new(#26a69a,0)
        else if _absDist < 1.0
            ema_txt := "NEAR (" + str.tostring(_emaDist, "0.0") + "%)"
            ema_col := color.new(#42a5f5,0)
        else if close > _useEma
            ema_txt := "ABOVE +" + str.tostring(_emaDist, "0.0") + "% (" + _ext + ")"
            ema_col := color.new(#26a69a,30)
        else
            ema_txt := "BELOW " + str.tostring(_emaDist, "0.0") + "% (" + _ext + ")"
            ema_col := color.new(#ef5350,0)
    f_row(8, _emaLbl, ema_txt, ema_col)

    // --- RV (volume): its own colour-coded field ---
    f_row(12, "RV (rel vol · " + timeframe.period + ")", str.tostring(chart_rv_v, "0.00") + (chart_rv_v >= 1.25 ? "  strong" : chart_rv_v >= 1.0 ? "  ok" : "  thin"), rv_col)
    // --- TRIGGER: the COMBINED gate = Event + Volume + Intraday (highlighted) ---
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 15, "TRIGGER", text_size=size.small, text_color=color.white, bgcolor=color.new(trig_col, 65), text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 1, 15, trig_txt, text_size=size.small, text_color=trig_col, bgcolor=color.new(trig_col, 84), text_halign=text.align_right)
    // Plan prints ONLY when TRIGGER = GO (a trigger fired AND volume is there).
    // Plan SL = STRUCTURAL invalidation, not the far Stage-1 AVWAP (old bug gave a ~24%
    // stop). Priority: demand-zone distal (in-zone → nearest below) → recent swing low →
    // ATR stop. Then a hard sanity cap at 3×ATR so the stop can never be absurdly far.
    // Values are hoisted so the PLAN row can describe the METHOD in words while the
    // four rows below carry the NUMBERS — the prices are stated once, in the rows that
    // exist to hold them, and never repeated in prose.
    // #12b TRADE TYPE (Risk Shield Active-Exits classifier): VOLATILE (ATR% high), FAR off
    // the 52W high, or BELOW the 200-DMA → SWING clock (tighter stop, nearer targets);
    // else POSITIONAL (wider stop, further targets). S4 also knows Bull vs Recovery.
    float _atrPct  = (not na(chart_atr[_so]) and close[_so] > 0) ? chart_atr[_so] / close[_so] * 100.0 : 0.0
    float _off52v  = nz(d_off52[_so], 0.0)
    bool  _bel200v = nz(d_bel200[_so], 0.0) > 0.5
    bool  tt_swing = use_tradetype_plan and (_atrPct > swing_atr_max or _off52v > swing_off52_max or _bel200v)
    float _slMult  = use_tradetype_plan ? (tt_swing ? tt_sl_swing : tt_sl_pos) : 2.5
    float _t1R     = tt_swing ? tt_t1r_swing : tt_t1r_pos
    float _t2R     = tt_swing ? tt_t2r_swing : tt_t2r_pos
    string tt_lbl  = not use_tradetype_plan ? "" : (tt_swing ? "SWING" : "POSITIONAL")
    float pl_entry = na
    float pl_sl    = na
    float pl_t1    = na
    float pl_t2    = na
    float pl_rr1   = na
    float pl_rr2   = na
    bool  pl_cap   = false
    bool  pl_t1_str = false
    bool  pl_t2_str = false
    string pl_slsrc = ""
    string _plan   = na
    if go_v
        float _cl  = close[_so]
        float _atr = chart_atr[_so]
        // Entry method (#retest A/B): buy-STOP above the trigger HIGH (confirmation,
        // default doctrine) OR buy-LIMIT at the trigger CLOSE (retest the pullback to value).
        pl_entry := use_retest ? close[_so] : high[_so]
        // SL source, in priority order — and NAMED, so the row says what it rests on.
        float _lvl = na
        if not na(z_inDZdist[_so])
            _lvl := z_inDZdist[_so]
            pl_slsrc := "zone distal (in-zone)"
        else if not na(z_nearDZdist[_so])
            _lvl := z_nearDZdist[_so]
            pl_slsrc := "nearest zone distal"
        else if not na(swingLo10[_so])
            _lvl := swingLo10[_so]
            pl_slsrc := "10-bar swing low"
        // Dedicated SL buffer. The old code borrowed `_tol` — the AVWAP TOUCH tolerance
        // (1.0%) — so widening the AVWAP band silently doubled every stop's distance.
        if na(_lvl) or _lvl >= _cl
            pl_sl := _cl - _slMult * _atr
            pl_slsrc := str.tostring(_slMult, "0.0") + "×ATR (no structure below)"
        else
            pl_sl := _lvl * (1.0 - plan_slbuf_pct / 100.0)
        // #12b: the sanity cap is now TRADE-TYPE aware (swing tighter, positional wider) —
        // capping a positional trade at a flat 2.5×ATR was the "tight stop on a long hold
        // gives back edge" mistake. FLAGGED + continuous.
        pl_cap := not na(_atr) and (_cl - pl_sl) > _slMult * _atr
        if pl_cap
            pl_sl := _cl - _slMult * _atr
        // Targets = the real obstacle Room found (structural); when none exists, the
        // TRADE-TYPE R-multiple canon (Risk Allocator: swing 3R/5R · positional 5R/10R;
        // Recovery T2 = the 52W high when nearer). R is against the ACTUAL trade.
        float _rsk = pl_entry - pl_sl
        float _h52v = (_off52v > 0 and _off52v < 100) ? close[_so] / (1.0 - _off52v / 100.0) : na
        pl_t1_str := not na(_ovh) and _ovh > pl_entry
        pl_t1 := pl_t1_str ? _ovh : (_rsk > 0 ? pl_entry + _t1R * _rsk : na)
        pl_t2_str := not na(_ovh2) and _ovh2 > pl_entry
        pl_t2 := pl_t2_str ? _ovh2 : (is_rec_v and not na(_h52v) and _h52v > pl_entry ? _h52v : (_rsk > 0 ? pl_entry + _t2R * _rsk : na))
        pl_rr1 := (_rsk > 0 and not na(pl_t1)) ? (pl_t1 - pl_entry) / _rsk : na
        pl_rr2 := (_rsk > 0 and not na(pl_t2)) ? (pl_t2 - pl_entry) / _rsk : na
        // The PLAN row is the METHOD — no prices (they are in the four rows below).
        string _entryMethodTxt = use_retest ? "Buy-LIMIT at the trigger close (retest the pullback)" : "Buy-stop above the trigger bar"
        _plan := (str.length(tt_lbl) > 0 ? tt_lbl + " · " : "") + _entryMethodTxt + " · SL under the " + pl_slsrc + (pl_cap ? " ⚠cap " + str.tostring(_slMult, "0.0") + "×ATR" : "") + " · T1 " + (pl_t1_str ? "overhead" : str.tostring(_t1R, "0.0") + "R") + " · T2 " + (pl_t2_str ? "overhead" : (not pl_t2_str and is_rec_v and not na(_h52v)) ? "52WH" : str.tostring(_t2R, "0.0") + "R")
    f_row(16, "Plan", na(_plan) ? "wait for GO" : _plan, na(_plan) ? color.new(#787b86,0) : color.new(#26a69a,0))
    // Entry · SL · T1 · T2 — the numbers, on one row, dot-separated. R-multiples ride
    // with T1/T2 so the reward is read where the price is.
    string _lE  = na(pl_entry) ? "" : "E " + str.tostring(pl_entry, format.mintick)
    string _lS  = na(pl_entry) ? "" : " · SL " + str.tostring(pl_sl, format.mintick) + (pl_cap ? "⚠" : "") + " (−" + str.tostring((pl_entry - pl_sl) / pl_entry * 100.0, "0.0") + "%)"
    string _lT1 = na(pl_t1) ? " · T1 —" : " · T1 " + str.tostring(pl_t1, format.mintick) + " (" + str.tostring(pl_rr1, "0.0") + "R)"
    string _lT2 = na(pl_t2) ? (na(pl_t1) ? " · T2 —" : " · T2 open") : " · T2 " + str.tostring(pl_t2, format.mintick) + " (" + str.tostring(pl_rr2, "0.0") + "R)"
    string _lvlTxt = na(pl_entry) ? "wait for GO" : (_lE + _lS + _lT1 + _lT2)
    f_row(17, "Entry · SL · T1 · T2", _lvlTxt, na(pl_entry) ? color.gray : color.new(#26a69a,0))
    // Qty — the last manual step before the GTT, computed from the panel's own Entry/SL.
    // #12: Qty from the DYNAMIC risk% (Risk-Allocator rules), capped by max-allocation.
    float _riskAmt = size_cap * active_risk / 100.0
    int   _qtyR   = (na(pl_entry) or (pl_entry - pl_sl) <= 0) ? 0 : int(math.floor(_riskAmt / (pl_entry - pl_sl)))
    int   _qtyC   = (size_max_alloc > 0 and not na(pl_entry) and pl_entry > 0) ? int(math.floor(size_max_alloc / pl_entry)) : _qtyR
    int   _qtyF   = math.min(_qtyR, _qtyC)
    string _dynTag = not use_dyn_risk ? "" : " (" + str.tostring(size_risk, "0.00") + "b ×" + str.tostring(kelly_mult, "0.00") + "K" + (vol_disc < 1.0 ? " ×" + str.tostring(vol_disc, "0.00") + "V" : "") + (not mkt_health ? " bear−" : "") + ")"
    string _qtyTxt = na(pl_entry) ? "—" : size_cap <= 0 ? "set Capital in Sizing" : ((pl_entry - pl_sl) <= 0 ? "—" : str.tostring(_qtyF) + (_qtyC < _qtyR ? " sh (alloc-capped)" : " sh") + " · risk ₹" + str.tostring(_riskAmt, "0") + _dynTag)
    f_row(18, "Qty @ " + str.tostring(active_risk, "0.00") + "% risk", _qtyTxt, na(pl_entry) or size_cap <= 0 ? color.gray : color.new(#26a69a,0))
    // --- PA CONDITIONS: compact grid, every condition shown fired(✓)/quiet(·); mode-aware ---
    string tf_suffix = use_chart_tf ? timeframe.period : "EOD"
    // #2 fix: the PA header + grid read the SAME (last-closed) bar as the TRIGGER /
    // STATUS via [_so], so the "Sum" / grid can never disagree with the Σ in STATUS.
    string _hdr = (is_rec_v ? "PA · RECOVERY " : "PA · BULL ") + (mode == "Auto" ? (confirm_daily ? "(auto·" + tf_suffix + ")" : "(auto·live*)") : (confirm_daily ? "(" + tf_suffix + ")" : "(live*)"))
    color pa_col_v = tsum_v >= 4 ? color.new(#7b1fa2,0) : tsum_v >= 2 ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : tsum_v >= 1 ? color.new(#ff9800,0) : color.gray
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 19, _hdr, text_size=size.small, text_color=color.white, bgcolor=color.new(#455a64, 0), text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 1, 19, not show_pa ? "off" : ("Sum +" + str.tostring(tsum_v)), text_size=size.small, text_color=color.white, bgcolor=pa_col_v, text_halign=text.align_right)
    color _gc = color.new(#d1d4dc, 0)
    string _g0 = is_rec_v ? f_it("CLIMAX",kCLIMAX[_so])+f_it("SPR",kSPR[_so])+f_it("2B",k2B[_so])    : f_it("HTF",kHTF[_so])+f_it("SC",kSC[_so])+f_it("VCP",kVCP[_so])
    string _g1 = is_rec_v ? f_it("SOS",kSOS[_so])+f_it("ENG",kENG[_so])+f_it("HSUP",kHSUP[_so])      : f_it("LAU",kLAU[_so])+f_it("GAP",kGAP[_so])+f_it("BC",kBC[_so])
    string _g2 = is_rec_v ? f_it("3BR",k3B[_so])+f_it("PP",kPP[_so])+f_it("VDU",kVDU[_so])           : f_it("PP",kPP[_so])+f_it("U50",kU50[_so])+f_it("LIQ",kLIQ[_so])
    string _g3 = is_rec_v ? f_it("30WMA",kRECLAIM[_so])                                              : f_it("SPR",kSPR[_so])+f_it("ENG",kENG[_so])+f_it("3BR",k3B[_so])
    string _g4 = is_rec_v ? "" : f_it("H50",kH50[_so])+f_it("H200",kH200[_so])+f_it("IN3",kIN3[_so])
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 20, _g0, text_size=size.small, text_color=_gc, text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 1, 20, _g1, text_size=size.small, text_color=_gc, text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 21, _g2, text_size=size.small, text_color=_gc, text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 1, 21, _g3, text_size=size.small, text_color=_gc, text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 22, _g4, text_size=size.small, text_color=_gc, text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 1, 22, is_rec_v ? "" : f_it("NR7",kNR7[_so])+f_it("IBN",kIBNR7[_so]), text_size=size.small, text_color=_gc, text_halign=text.align_left)
    // Structure row — off52% + 30-WMA + 200-DMA. ALWAYS written: it was previously
    // inside `if mode == "Auto"`, so on a manual Bull/Recovery setting the row was
    // never written and rendered BLANK — which reads as missing data, not "n/a".
    // The context is worth having whether or not Auto used it to pick the mode.
    // "above 30WMA" (not "repaired"): the else-state is simply price ABOVE a non-falling
    // 30-WMA — a healthy Stage-2 context. It does NOT track a prior below-then-reclaim,
    // so calling it "reclaimed/repaired" would overclaim an event that isn't measured.
    string _wma_st = nz(d_bel30, 0.0) > 0.5 ? "below 30WMA" : nz(d_s150dn, 0.0) > 0.5 ? "30WMA falling" : "above 30WMA"
    string _200_st = nz(d_bel200, 0.0) > 0.5 ? "<200DMA" : ">200DMA"
    string _basis  = str.tostring(nz(d_off52, 0.0), "0.0") + "% off52 · " + _wma_st + " · " + _200_st + (mode == "Auto" ? "  → auto-picked " + (is_rec_v ? "Recovery" : "Bull") : "  (mode set manually)")
    f_row(23, "Structure basis", _basis, is_rec_v ? color.new(#00838f, 0) : color.new(#26a69a, 0))
    // v2.9: STATUS — a verbatim one-line summary of every gate + the blocking reason,
    // so the panel states IN WORDS exactly why it is GO or still waiting.
    string _verdict = go_v ? ("GO" + (cf_v >= cf_strong ? " ★strong" : "") + (use_retest ? " — arm buy-limit @ close on the pullback" : " — arm buy-stop > bar high")) : not any_pa_v ? "NO PA PATTERN" : not support_v ? "NO LOCATION" : not vol_ok_v ? "NO VOLUME" : "WEAK/RED BAR — no entry"
    string _status  = _verdict + " · P" + (any_pa_v?"✓":"·") + " L" + (support_v?"✓":"·") + " V" + (vol_ok_v?"✓":"·") + " B" + (bar_ok_v?"✓":"·") + " ⏱" + (timing_v?"✓":"·") + " · conf " + str.tostring(cf_v) + "/" + str.tostring(cf_max) + " · RV " + str.tostring(chart_rv_v, "0.00") + "/" + str.tostring(rv_floor, "0.00") + " · " + (is_rec_v?"Rec":"Bull") + " Σ+" + str.tostring(tsum_v)
    // Amber for EVERY waiting state, including no-PA (was grey). Grey read as
    // "off/inactive"; amber reads as "armed, waiting for the gate" — the honest state
    // when the engine is live. Green only on a real GO.
    color _status_col = go_v ? color.new(#26a69a,0) : color.new(#ff9800,0)
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 24, "STATUS", text_size=size.small, text_color=color.white, bgcolor=color.new(_status_col, 55), text_halign=text.align_left)
    table.cell(pnl, 1, 24, _status, text_size=size.small, text_color=_status_col, bgcolor=color.new(_status_col, 88), text_halign=text.align_right)

    // ======================================================================
    // ANALYSIS — the trade in words. Everything above is a number; this is the
    // read. Built from the SAME [_so]-shifted values the rows show, so it can
    // never narrate a different bar than the panel it sits under.
    // Multi-line via \n inside one cell: a single long string would stretch the
    // whole panel across the chart.
    // ======================================================================
    // #62: CONTEXT / LOCATION / SETUP / RISK were removed — they restated the Structure,
    // Support/S-R, STATUS and Entry·SL·T1·T2 rows verbatim ("repeat of the field outputs,
    // not useful"). Kept ONLY the VERDICT: swing vs positional decided by the house rules
    // (swing >= 2.0R · positional >= 20% ROI to T1), which no other row states.
    // v4.2: the VERDICT now RULES instead of naming the first failing gate. Naming one
    // gate is actively misleading — "WAIT: volume below floor" reads as "buy it when
    // volume arrives", while the SAME bar may be sitting INSIDE supply with negative
    // room, where clearing volume would not make it a trade at all (CDSL, 18-Jul). So
    // the ruling weighs the GATES together with a QUALITY OVERLAY — room/R, arrival +
    // delta — and states DIRECTION first, then the binding reason, then the
    // disqualifier when one exists.
    string _aVer = ""
    color  _anCol = color.new(#b2b5be, 0)
    // Quality overlay — true regardless of which gate is blocking.
    bool _qSupply  = _inSZ_r
    bool _qThinR   = (not na(_roomR)) and _roomR < 1.0
    bool _qRoomBad = _qSupply or _qThinR
    bool _qArrBad  = show_arrival and arr_style[_so] == "GRIND" and not of_absorb[_so]
    bool _qArrGood = show_arrival and arr_style[_so] == "FAST" and of_absorb[_so]
    // #3: chasing — price too far above the daily EMA20 (in ATRs). Quality, not a gate.
    float _extV   = ext_atr[_so]
    bool  _qExt   = not na(_extV) and _extV > ext_atr_max
    // WEAK LOCATION (ABBOTINDIA, 19-Jul): the GO rests ONLY on the AVWAP/EMA — price is
    // NOT in a demand zone or on a fresh S/R level. Per the house methodology (buy the
    // pullback into a Daily+ demand zone), that is a MOMENTUM/breakout entry, not a
    // pullback to support — the weakest location tier, and the reason the GM (which does
    // not count AVWAP as location) reads "No location".
    bool  _locZone = z_inDZ[_so] or in_daily_zone[_so] or in_weekly_zone[_so]
    bool  _qLocWeak = support_v and not _locZone and not near_sr[_so]
    // BLUE-SKY / BREAKOUT PIVOT (Jay, 19-Jul): a Stage-2 leader (above the 30WMA + 200DMA)
    // consolidating within ath_prox_pct of its 52W high is a CONTINUATION pivot, not
    // distribution — the "supply band" it sits in IS the prior high, meant to break. So an
    // in-supply state near the ATH is NOT a range-logic "no room" reject; it's a breakout
    // to arm ABOVE the band. Only in a Stage-2 uptrend; a Stage 3/4 lower high stays a SKIP.
    bool  _stage2ok = nz(d_bel30[_so], 0.0) < 0.5 and nz(d_bel200[_so], 0.0) < 0.5
    bool  _nearATH  = _off52v >= 0.0 and _off52v <= ath_prox_pct
    bool  _blueSky  = _inSZ_r and _nearATH and _stage2ok
    string _roomWord = _qSupply ? ("price is INSIDE supply" + (na(_band_r) ? "" : " — must clear " + str.tostring(_band_r, format.mintick))) : _qThinR ? ("only " + str.tostring(_roomR, "0.0") + "R of room to the first obstacle") : ""
    // (_roomTag / _arrTag retired — the metrics digest `_mx` below carries both now.)
    // The binding gate, in words, with its number.
    string _blk = not any_pa_v ? "no PA pattern" : not support_v ? "not at a location" : not vol_ok_v ? ("volume below floor (RV " + str.tostring(chart_rv_v, "0.00") + "/" + str.tostring(rv_floor, "0.00") + ")") : "the trigger bar closed weak"
    string _act = not any_pa_v ? "Watch for a closed-bar PA trigger here." : not support_v ? "Needs a pullback into a zone / level." : not vol_ok_v ? "Watch for a volume surge." : "Wait for a bar that closes strong."
    // WHICH location sources are actually holding price up (zone / S-R / AVWAP / EMA20).
    string _locSrc = (z_inDZ[_so] ? "DZ" : "") + (near_sr[_so] ? (z_inDZ[_so] ? "+S/R" : "S/R") : "") + (near_avwap[_so] ? "+AVWAP" : "") + (near_ema[_so] ? "+EMA20" : "")
    if str.length(_locSrc) == 0
        _locSrc := (z_inSZ[_so] ? "IN SUPPLY" : "none")
    // METRICS DIGEST — one compact line carrying every read the ruling weighed, so the
    // verdict is auditable without re-scanning the panel: location sources, room, arrival
    // + delta, RV vs floor, confluence, and the PA sum for the active path.
    // Built with successive assignments, NOT a wrapped expression: a continuation line
    // indented by a multiple of 4 parses as a new block in Pine and breaks silently.
    string _mx = "Loc " + _locSrc
    if z_inDZ_ctrl[_so]
        _mx := _mx + " ★ctrl"
    if _dzTfN[_so] >= 2
        _mx := _mx + " ×" + str.tostring(_dzTfN[_so]) + "TF"
    if not na(_roomR)
        _mx := _mx + " · " + str.tostring(_roomR, "0.0") + "R"
    if show_arrival and arr_style[_so] != "—"
        _mx := _mx + " · " + arr_style[_so] + " " + of_read[_so]
    if str.length(tt_lbl) > 0
        _mx := _mx + " · " + tt_lbl
    if not na(_extV)
        _mx := _mx + " · " + (_extV >= 0 ? "+" : "") + str.tostring(_extV, "0.0") + "ATR vEMA20" + (_qExt ? "⚠" : "")
    _mx := _mx + " · RV " + str.tostring(chart_rv_v, "0.00") + "/" + str.tostring(rv_floor, "0.00")
    _mx := _mx + " · conf " + str.tostring(cf_v) + "/" + str.tostring(cf_max)
    _mx := _mx + " · " + (is_rec_v ? "Rec" : "Bull") + " Σ+" + str.tostring(tsum_v)
    // Ruling assembled as SEPARATE LINES: one long string stretches the panel across the
    // chart (Jay), so headline / reason / disqualifier / metrics / action each get a row.
    string _L1 = ""
    string _L2 = ""
    string _L3 = ""
    string _L5 = ""
    if go_v and not na(pl_entry)
        bool _swingOk = not na(pl_rr1) and pl_rr1 >= 2.0
        float _roiT1  = na(pl_t1) ? na : (pl_t1 - pl_entry) / pl_entry * 100.0
        bool _posOk   = not na(_roiT1) and _roiT1 >= 20.0
        string _rule  = _posOk and _swingOk ? "clears BOTH house gates (>=20% ROI and >=2R)" : _swingOk ? "SWING only — clears 2R, T1 under the 20% positional rule" : _posOk ? "POSITIONAL only — 20%+ room but R:R under 2.0" : "clears NEITHER house gate (R:R < 2.0 and room < 20%)"
        if _blueSky
            _L1 := "BREAKOUT PIVOT — Stage-2 leader at its high"
            _L2 := "Consolidating under the ATH (" + str.tostring(_off52v, "0.0") + "% off 52WH) — the 'supply' here IS the prior high, meant to BREAK. Not distribution, not a range reject."
            _L3 := "Don't buy HERE (into the resistance). Arm a buy-STOP above " + (na(_band_r) ? "the band ceiling" : str.tostring(_band_r, format.mintick)) + " — above it is BLUE SKY (reward = measured move / trail, not the next level)."
            _L5 := "Only valid Stage-2 (above 30WMA+200DMA). If RS fades / it's Stage 3, this same band is real supply → skip."
            _anCol := color.new(#26a69a, 0)
        else if _qRoomBad
            _L1 := "SKIP — clean trigger, no room"
            _L2 := _roomWord
            _L3 := "Buying into overhead supply is not a trade."
            _anCol := color.new(#ef5350, 0)
        else if _posOk or _swingOk
            _L1 := (_qLocWeak or _qExt) ? "CAUTION — momentum/chase" : ("TAKE IT" + (cf_v >= cf_strong ? " ★strong" : "") + (_qArrGood ? " · quality arrival" : ""))
            _L2 := _rule
            _L3 := _qLocWeak ? "Location is the AVWAP/EMA only — NOT a demand zone. A momentum/breakout entry, not a pullback to support (your A+ setup). Size down or wait for a pullback into a zone." : _qExt ? ("Caveat: EXTENDED " + str.tostring(_extV, "0.0") + " ATR above the EMA20 — chasing; size down or wait for a pullback toward value.") : _qArrBad ? "Caveat: GRIND arrival with Δ− — size down or wait for a sharper re-test." : ""
            _L5 := "Buy-STOP above the trigger bar's high. Never buy the touch."
            _anCol := (_qArrBad or _qExt or _qLocWeak) ? color.new(#ff9800, 0) : color.new(#26a69a, 0)
        else
            _L1 := "SKIP — payoff too thin"
            _L2 := _rule
            _L3 := "The entry is clean; the reward does not justify the risk."
            _anCol := color.new(#ef5350, 0)
    else if go_v
        _L1 := "GO — but no plan"
        _L2 := "No structural stop / target could be built."
        _L5 := "Mark the levels by hand before acting."
        _anCol := color.new(#ff9800, 0)
    else if _blueSky
        _L1 := "BREAKOUT PIVOT (arming)"
        _L2 := "Stage-2 leader consolidating under its ATH (" + str.tostring(_off52v, "0.0") + "% off 52WH). Blocked: " + _blk + "."
        _L3 := "Not a 'no room' reject — the band ceiling IS the breakout level. Arm a buy-STOP above " + (na(_band_r) ? "the band ceiling" : str.tostring(_band_r, format.mintick)) + "; above it is blue sky."
        _anCol := color.new(#ff9800, 0)
    else if _qRoomBad
        _L1 := "NOT TRADEABLE"
        _L2 := "Blocked: " + _blk
        _L3 := "Disqualifier: " + _roomWord + " — clearing that gate alone will NOT make this a trade."
        _anCol := color.new(#ef5350, 0)
    else if _qArrBad
        _L1 := "LOW QUALITY — wait for a better tap"
        _L2 := "Blocked: " + _blk
        _L3 := "Arrival is a GRIND with Δ− — momentum is absorbing the level (bleed-through risk)."
        _L5 := _act
        _anCol := color.new(#ff9800, 0)
    else
        _L1 := "ARM" + (_qArrGood ? " — quality setup" : "")
        _L2 := "Waiting on: " + _blk
        _L3 := (not any_pa_v and support_v) ? "At a location with clean volume/bar — only the pattern is missing." : ""
        _L5 := _act
        _anCol := color.new(#ff9800, 0)
    _aVer := _L1 + "\n" + _L2 + (str.length(_L3) > 0 ? "\n" + _L3 : "") + "\n" + _mx + (str.length(_L5) > 0 ? "\n" + _L5 : "")
    if show_analysis
        table.cell(pnl, 0, 25, "VERDICT", text_size=size.small, text_color=color.white, bgcolor=color.new(#37474f, 0), text_halign=text.align_left)
        table.cell(pnl, 1, 25, "➤ " + _aVer, text_size=size.small, text_color=_anCol, text_halign=text.align_left)

    // Engine diagnostics — troubleshooting instrumentation, off by default. This is
    // what used to be bolted onto the Zones (MTF) row: it answers "why did that zone
    // vanish", never "should I take this trade".
    if show_diag
        string _diag = "natC d" + str.tostring(_dbgNatDetected) + " f" + str.tostring(_dbgNatFvgPass) + " m" + str.tostring(_dbgNatCreated) + " L" + str.tostring(zc_nat) + "  |  pat D " + str.tostring(_dbgPatDDet) + "/" + str.tostring(_dbgPatDCr) + "·L" + str.tostring(zc_patD) + "  W " + str.tostring(_dbgPatWDet) + "/" + str.tostring(_dbgPatWCr) + "·L" + str.tostring(zc_patW) + "  M " + str.tostring(_dbgPatMDet) + "/" + str.tostring(_dbgPatMCr) + "·L" + str.tostring(zc_patM) + "  |  struct D" + str.tostring(_dbgStrDetected) + " C" + str.tostring(_dbgStrCreated) + " L" + str.tostring(zc_struct) + "  |  removed: age " + str.tostring(_rmAge) + " · travel " + str.tostring(_rmTrv) + " · emaX " + str.tostring(_rmEma) + " · lvlX " + str.tostring(_rmLvl) + " · violated " + str.tostring(_rmVio)
        f_row(26, "Diagnostics", _diag, color.new(#787b86, 0))

// ==========================================
// ALERTS
// ==========================================
alertcondition(go and (not use_closed_candle or barstate.isconfirmed),            title="S4 GO (PA + Location + Volume)", message="{{ticker}} S4 GO - a PA pattern fired at a valid location WITH volume. Confirm the closed bar → buy-STOP above its high.")
alertcondition(avwap_trig,    title="S4 AVWAP trigger",       message="{{ticker}} S4 AVWAP trigger - bounce / R2G>BO")
alertcondition(intraday_trig, title="S4 Intraday trigger",    message="{{ticker}} S4 INTRADAY trigger - reclaimed rising 10-EMA + TTM squeeze fired up")
alertcondition(pinched,       title="S4 AVWAP pinch",         message="{{ticker}} S4 AVWAPs pinched - high-conviction entry zone")
alertcondition(pa_fire,       title="S4 ANY daily PA pattern", message="{{ticker}} S4 daily PA pattern fired - check panel for which + tier")
// Dynamic runtime alert naming exactly which battery conditions fired + tier sum:
if show_pa and pa_fire
    alert("S4 PA on " + syminfo.ticker + " (Sum+" + str.tostring(tsum) + "): " + str.substring(pa_names, 0, math.max(0, str.length(pa_names) - 2)), alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
// v1.9: Σ-strengthening — ANOTHER pattern joined while one was already live
// (pa_fire only catches the FIRST edge into any-pattern-live).
if show_pa and any_pa and any_pa[1] and tsum > nz(tsum[1])
    alert("S4 PA strengthened on " + syminfo.ticker + " (Sum+" + str.tostring(nz(tsum[1])) + " -> +" + str.tostring(tsum) + "): " + str.substring(pa_names, 0, math.max(0, str.length(pa_names) - 2)), alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
// self-describing GO — mode + the PA pattern(s) that fired (the signal) + location +
// optional timing + RV, so the ping alone tells you what to do without the chart.
if go and not go[1]
    string _pa  = str.substring(pa_names, 0, math.max(0, str.length(pa_names) - 2))
    string _tim = ev_ok and intra_ok ? " (+AVWAP & intraday timing)" : ev_ok ? (_r2g ? " (+AVWAP R2G timing)" : " (+AVWAP bounce timing)") : intra_ok ? " (+intraday 10EMA timing)" : ""
    string _zone = z_inDZ ? "at Demand Zone" : in_d_fvg ? "at Daily FVG" : in_d_piv ? "at Daily pivot" : in_w_fvg ? "at Weekly FVG" : in_w_piv ? "at Weekly pivot" : near_avwap ? "at AVWAP" : "at location"
    alert("S4 GO on " + syminfo.ticker + " (" + (is_rec ? "Recovery" : "Bull") + ") — PA: " + _pa + _tim + " " + _zone + " · RV " + str.tostring(nz(chart_rv, 0.0), "0.00") + " · Sum+" + str.tostring(tsum) + ". Confirm the closed bar -> buy-STOP above its high.", alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)